{"name":"Hush Kit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hush Kit[h3]\nHush kits were originally designed to muffle the sound of ion and rocket engines around urban spaceports. Installed on a starship's engines, these devices dramatically reduces the sound engines produce. Shortly after their introduction, though, it became apparent that hush kits also make it easier to sneak ships and speeders into and out of places they don't belong. They have since become common among criminals, scouts, and intelligence agents. This attachment can be applied to any starship or vehicle. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Incom 44L2 \"Whisperer\" Hush Kit, SoroSuub \"Slipstream\" Stage Ill Hush Kit.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds [SE][SE] to all checks to detect this ship audibly while it is in atmosphere. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":450,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HUSHKIT"}},"_id":"02zBKqTMkDderfnD"}
{"name":"Subminiature Holocam","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Subminiature Holocam[h3]\nSubminiature holocams are small holorecorders equipped with a medium-sized fixed focal length lens. Able to record still images and video in numerous formats, they are often hidden in datapads, eyeglasses, goggles, or jewelry. Due to their size and the nature of the attached lens, they have relatively limited capabilities. The on-board storage can store only a handful of still images or a few minutes of video, and the images are all low-resolution. Unless the subminiature holocam is specifically built for the task, it can only reliably record up to a range of three meters. In addition, miniature holocams rarely, if ever, have networking capabilities; images and video footage must be removed manually by connecting the device to a datapad or computer. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Xonim Holotech VEF22 SubMiniature Holocam.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows a user to take still images and record holos unobtrusively </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":300,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SUBMINHOLO"}},"_id":"07QXLVyf3oKjS3lq"}
{"name":"Cracked Jedha Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Cracked Jedha Crystal[h3]\nWhen a terrible mining accident destroyed Jedha City, the galaxy lost one of the last known sources of kyber crystals. The crystals produced on Jedha held great spiritual significance for the Jedi, the Church of the Force, and a number of other religious traditions. Jedha crystals were among the most popular kyber crystals for the Jedi. As a practical matter, Jedha crystals produce focused, potent lightsaber blades, but many Jedi valued the knowledge that their lightsaber housed an artifact from Jedha. For those who seek to follow in the Jedi's path, kyber crystals have become vanishingly rare in recent years. However, a small number of Jedha crystals have  been recovered from the ruins of Jedha City. Unfortunately, many of these crystals are cracked and damaged, producing unstable, ragged lightsaber beams.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 48 - Knights of Fate[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 3</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Inaccurate Quality - Inaccurate weapons are weapons of a shoddy or inferior construction which means they are less likely to be accurate or precise. Alternatively, the weapon’s nature may inhibit accuracy. Inaccurate weapons add [SE] to the attacker’s dice pool equal to their Inaccurate rating. Count 2</div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Vicious Quality - When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":8000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"te8y3rb0tlahn0lq"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"q49dtyt7p4b8677z"},{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRITSUB"}},"id":"m58mrspo92cwkjpl"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"JEDHACR"}},"_id":"09fzftrJVwe5vM1M"}
{"name":"SmartTranq","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]SmartTranq[h3]\n\nDeveloped in cooperation with CorChemCo, SmartTranq is an adaptable synthetic tranquilizer designed to be used with the Model 77 Air Rifle. When the tranquilizer enters the bloodstream of a target, it immediately begins to mutate, changing constantly and reconfiguring itself to find the quickest, most efficient way to overwhelm the target's defensive systems and render it unconscious. \n\n[P]Upon a successful hit with the Model 77, the target must immediately make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Resilience check[b]. If the target fails, it suffers 5 strain, plus 2 additional strain per [TH] generated on the check. If the check generates [DE], the GM can spend it to make the target check against the tranquilizer again during the next round. If the GM does so, increase the difficulty of the check by one. \n\n[P]Equipping the Model 77 with SmartTranq costs 500 credits. This does not change the weapon's profile—it simply adds the above special rule to the weapon. If the weapon ever runs out of ammo, the user must purchase a reload (also costing 500 credits) before using the SmartTranq again.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Enter the Unknown[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Upon hit, target must make [B]Average ([DIFFICULTY][DIFFICULTY]) Resilience check[b].  If fail, target takes 5 strain, plus 2 strain per [THREAT].  GM may use [DESPAIR] to make target check again next round at increased difficulty. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"M77TRANQ"}},"_id":"0LbEFoI8g1yZGOPt"}
{"name":"All-Terrain Legs","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]All-Terrain Legs[h3]\nAlthough ion drives and repulsorlifts dominate the galaxy, the continued use of walkers by the Empire and certain planetary militias is testament tot eh advantages of such craft. Walkers are stable, implacable and usually intimidating. For those who want true versatility from their craft, speeders and eve starships can be modified with the addition of a number, depending on the size and shape of the vehicle, of sturdy mechanical legs. In some cases, these might be mistaken for simple landing gear - until the vehicle begins to stomp forward. This attachment can be applied to any airspeeder or starship that can land on a planet.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Kuat Drive Yards KR-2 \"Crab\" Auxiliary Locomotion Unit, Alto Industries Variable Combat Kit[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 65 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As a maneuver, pilot may shift in or out of walker mode.  In walker mode, pilot uses Piloting (Planetary) and speed is reduced to 2. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ALLTERLEGS"}},"_id":"0TB2MPb8MgoQzOmF"}
{"name":"Droid Targeting System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Droid Targeting System[h3]\nAlthough droids are most commonly thought of as autonomous mobile constructs, the advanced artificial intelligence of droid brains has been used in a variety of other applications for thousands of years. A specialized droid mind equipped with sensors and miniaturized gyromotors can improve the accuracy of even the most experienced sentient marksman.\n[P]Many soldiers look down on the use of such systems, while others find the vibrations as the droid subtly adjusts their aim to be frustrating, to say the least. Droid targeting systems are known for their often bossy and impatient personalities. This attachment can be applied to any personal ranged weapon.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Fully Operational[h4]","attributes":{"Ranged: Heavy":{"mod":"Ranged: Heavy","modtype":"Skill Rank","value":0},"Ranged: Light":{"mod":"Ranged: Light","modtype":"Skill Rank","value":0}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DROIDTARGET"}},"_id":"0WG4S8AakJ815Kiu"}
{"name":"Mobile Listening Post","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Mobile Listening Post[h3]\nMobile listening posts are a common modification to vehicles used by law enforcement and intelligence agencies. They pack everything an agent or small group of agents needs for a long stakeout. Models commonly include comms interceptors, various powerful sensors and scanners, and of course a small but well stocked caf maker. This attachment can be applied to any enclosed vehicle of silhouette 5 or larger. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases a vehicle's passive and active sensors by one band. Provides extra audio, video, and holographic capabilities. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MOBLISTPOST"}},"_id":"0iXrDZurLQ00iv1a"}
{"name":"Boot Blade","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Boot Blade[h3]\nAn excellent way to ensure an agent is always armed no matter the circumstances, boot blades are small spring-loaded knives that extend from the toes of an individual's shoes or boots to provide an extra edge in hand-to-hand combat. There are various ways to deploy the blades, such as pressing a certain point on the tongue of a shoe or stamping hard with a boot's heel. Retracting them often entails simply (but carefully) pushing them back into their compartment until they catch. This attachment can be applied to any armor that includes boots, shoes, or other footwear.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 57 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BOOTBLADE"}},"_id":"0x1OY1iGKxKh4FBn"}
{"name":"Beam Splitter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Beam Splitter[h3]\nAlliance troopers typically apply this upgrade to\nblaster pistols and other sidearms to achieve results\nsimilar to that of the spread barrel used on larger,\nmore powerful blasters. Beam splitters function by\nmodifying the Galven pattern and carefully mounting\nthree or more emitters into a honeycomb configuration inside a stock blaster barrel. Shots fired from a\nweapon with this modification diffuse into a weaker,\nspread shot rather than the typical blaster bolt, giving a single shot the potential to connect with multiple targets. Rebel troops often use this upgrade to\ntransform weaponry into effective standoff weapons\nused to pin down enemy troops and hold chokepoints\nin narrow starship corridors. This attachment can be\napplied to any blaster or suitable energy weapon that\ndoes not have the Blast quality.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Blast Quality - The weapon has a large spread, an explosive blast, or similar area of effect, like the detonation of a grenade or a warhead fired from a missile launcher. If the attack is successful and Blast activates, each character (friend or foe) Engaged with the original target suffers wounds equal to the weapon’s Blast rating (plus an additional wound per Success as usual).\n\n[P]In a relatively small and enclosed area, the Game Master might decide that everyone in the room suffers damage.\n\n[P]If the Blast quality doesn’t activate, the ordnance still detonates, but bad luck or poor aim on the part of the firer (or quick reactions on the part of the victims) means the explosion may not catch anyone else in its radius. However, the user may also trigger Blast if the attack misses, by spending [AD][AD][AD]. In this case, the original target and every target engaged with the original target suffers damage equal to the Blast rating of the weapon. </div><div>Reduced Range Mod - Decreases weapon's range by one Range Band </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"bsrm46um0nbiwmy3"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BEAMSPLIT"}},"_id":"13AI4yhaw7roZhCJ"}
{"name":"ANQ 3.6 Tracking Computer","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]ANQ 3.6 Tracking Computer[h3]\n\nThe Anq 3.6 is a computer/fire control system that allows the Pathfinder's sensor operator to coordinate fire amongst all ship weapons. The sensor operator must designate one target and make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Computers check[b]. If he succeeds, all combat checks made by ship weapons against his designated target upgrade the ability of their check once. If he has [SU][SU][SU] or [TR] on his check, he may designate an additional target.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Enter the Unknown[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Choose one target and make [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Computers check[b].  If successful, combat checks against target are upgraded once. [SU][SU][SU] or [TR] allows additional target. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":7500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ANQ36"}},"_id":"1cfnaBWYa2Vxegy1"}
{"name":"Stun-Only Blaster Modification","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Stun-Only Blaster Modification[h3]\nAdd this attachment to any blaster pistol or carbine to make it stun-only.  A blaster with this modification costs half the normal price.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 160 - Edge of the Empire Core Rulebook[h4][H4]Page 174 - Age of Rebellion Core Rulebook[h4][H4]Page 167 - Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Stun Damage Quality - Some weapons deal Stun damage instead of regular damage. In this case, the weapon deals damage as strain instead of wounds. This damage is still reduced by a target’s soak.\n\n[P]A variant of this is a Stun setting. As a free action, the wielder can choose to switch the setting of his weapon to “Stun.” In this case, it does stun damage as described above. When weapons with a stun setting are used to deal stun damage, their range changes to short and cannot be increased. </div><div>Item is Half Price Mod - Item costs half its asking price </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STUNONLYBLASTER"}},"_id":"1wyL2VtNdk6cVrXc"}
{"name":"Astromech Droid Socket","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Astromech Droid Socket[h3]\n\nAstromech sockets are typically found in starfighters, shuttles, and the occasional airspeeder. Installed during construction and fully integrated into a vehicle's systems, an astromech droid socket allows an astromech droid, typically one of Industrial Automaton's R-series droids, to access the ship's various systems through its SCOMP interface. A droid installed in an astromech socket acts as co-pilot, engineer, and radio/weapons systems operator, assisting the pilot during combat, monitoring onboard systems, performing astrogation calculations, and repairing damage on the fly. Most ships or vehicles can benefit from the inclusion of an astromech droid, especially those not equipped with an astromech socket. For these ships, Industrial Automaton sells a standalone astromech socket ready for installation in ships not already equipped. \n\n[P]Aftermarket astromech sockets can only be installed on ships or vehicles of silhouette 3 or higher. After a lengthy and involved installation process requiring heavy modifications to both the ship's hull and its onboard systems, the ship and pilot gain all the benefits of an astromech droid when one is installed in the socket. These benefits range from enhanced damage control to the ability to make hyperspace jump calculations. When installed on larger starships, this attachment represents can represent more than a single socket. These ships often employ an entire bay capable of housing multiple astromechs and deploying them to the outer surface of the ship to aid in repairs. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Industrial Automaton Mk. I Astromech Socket.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Stay on Target[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows starship to link to an astromech droid via SCOMP </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ASTROMECH"}},"_id":"2XYFXMLvRzjuTDeB"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Wheeled/Tracked","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Wheeled/Tracked[h3]\n      Converts a wheeled or tracked vehicle to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 3</div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 2</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 </div><div>Adds a medium laser cannon turret </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARAWHEEL"}},"_id":"2c1SJw6zFzGzbrhD"}
{"name":"Ilum Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Ilum Crystal[h3]\n\nThe kyber crystals found deep within the caves of the icy planet Hum were prized by the Jedi as some of the best crystals for constructing a lightsaber. Ilum featured heavily in Jedi tradition, with young Padawans traveling there as part of their training to commune with the Force and use its guidance to seek out the crystal that would go into the construction of their first lightsaber. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":9000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":10,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"4xn3woi4ddb3vyyo"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"swhswtx5pikwqif4"},{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRITSUB"}},"id":"pg0a9o68bcjd61fq"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ILUM"}},"_id":"2gkofdB0AoOvdXlS"}
{"name":"Augmented Spin Barrel","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Augmented Spin Barrel[h3]\n\nUsing an updated and streamlined galven pattern and heavy-duty static pulse adapters, this custom barrel increases both the damage output and armor penetration of blaster rifles and heavy blaster rifles. The trade-off for all this extra stopping power is increased wear and tear on both the frame of the blaster and the barrel, leading to an increase in maintenance and down-time. This attachment can only be used with blaster rifles and heavy blaster rifles.\n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Dolmax 243X \"Penetrator Augmented Spin Barrel, Arakyd HH780 HotShot Barrel, BlasTech Model 213 Perforator Barrel.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 </div><div>Add [SETBACK] to all Mechanics checks when performing\n          maintenance on this weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"cvykx77r0ah613ok"},{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"6eaoi47x0f59j3yx"},{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"9g2pqvkpe08e5jy3"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AUGSPIN"}},"_id":"2jpMH7UtF8PC2reV"}
{"name":"Training Lightsaber Emitter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Training Lightsaber Emitter[h3]\n\nIn the days of the Republic, the Jedi allowed their younglings to train with \"training sabers,\" non-lethal versions of their famous energy blades. A training lightsaber is almost the same as a standard lightsaber; however, the crystal is replaced with a training emitter. The training emitter creates a blade that is completely non-lethal, and at most can generate a stun shock. A training emitter is a lightsaber crystal. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating </div><div>Stun Damage Quality - Some weapons deal Stun damage instead of regular damage. In this case, the weapon deals damage as strain instead of wounds. This damage is still reduced by a target’s soak.\n\n[P]A variant of this is a Stun setting. As a free action, the wielder can choose to switch the setting of his weapon to “Stun.” In this case, it does stun damage as described above. When weapons with a stun setting are used to deal stun damage, their range changes to short and cannot be increased. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"TRAINEMIT"}},"_id":"2rspEl46INzIMome"}
{"name":"Ordnance Impeller","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Ordnance Impeller[h3]\nOver the millennia, tinkerers, weapon designers, and desperate fighters have come up with countless delivery systems for explosives, from missile tubes to combat droids. One less-popular approach that nonetheless endures among certain demolitions experts is the use of a modified grenade or detonite charge capable of self-propulsion. Such modifications are almost always unique, although certain small droids and other devices are a popular basis, despite manufacturer warnings. From a proton grenade with wheels to a hovering thermal detonator, these makeshift devices-when successful-allow unparalleled control of an explosive device from a considerable distance. This is generally achieved via a small holocam and remote-control unit, although the addition of a droid brain detonator can be exceedingly effective. This weapon attachment can be applied to any grenade or explosive device with an encumbrance value of 3 or less.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Explosive can move overland at the rate of a character on foot. </div><div>Includes a holocam and remote-control unit, allowing for movement and detonation from up to extreme range. </div><div>Skill checks to operate device uses either Computers or Piloting (Planetary). </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ORDIMPELL"}},"_id":"2x3JSdsf9OzgvNok"}
{"name":"Lightsaber Hilt Construction Modifications","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Lightsaber Hilt Construction Modifications[h3]\n      Use this attachment to reflect the results of a lightsaber hilt construction check, as required.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Game Master's Kit[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3RFrp6iTus4fudLH","name":"Add Hard Points Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Add One Hard Point","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HPADD"}},"id":"o0aidl6bhqqbhf6t"},{"_id":"Morm48Ch4Soskwq2","name":"Remove Hard Points from Item Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Remove One Hard Point from Item","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HPSUB"}},"id":"qjxkyxg2xrrwigt4"},{"_id":"FIcN4TkIpZPNEqah","name":"Decreases Encumbrance Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Decrease Encumbrance by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"f