{"name":"Electronic Countermeasures Suite (Custom)","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Electronic Countermeasures Suite (Custom)[h3]\n      [P]Blocks sensors within range when active, counting the Tallanx’s silhouette as 2. Immediately notifies all ships in a star system, or within 100 kilometers if planetside, to the Tollonx’s existence.\n      [P][I]This is an optional no-cost attachment for the Tallanx-Class Stealth Fighter and the Darvro-Class Light Freighter.[i][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Strongholds of Resistance[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Blocks sensors within range, counting the ship's silhouette as one smaller when being fired upon. </div><div>Immediately notifies all ships in a star system or within 100 kilometers if planetside to the ship or vehicle's existence. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ECMSUITETALLANX"}},"_id":"3EObY6PKemn7vYM2"}
{"name":"Motion Tracker","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Motion Tracker[h3]\nThe sophisticated device incorporates a full suite of onboard sensors and computers to track and predict the motion of a target, then feed that data back to the user through a variety of means, including a helmet HUD, a hardwired feed  jacked directly into the brain, or other methods. The system might involve motive-actuators within the weapon to subtly adjust aim, or it might interface with motorized gloves. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Heavy) weapon.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] CryonCorp Xv3 \"Surefire\" Motion Predictor, Industrial Automaton A-3 Tracking Computer.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 50 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Remove [SE] due to target movement or use of Guarded Stance. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MOTTRACK"}},"_id":"3R6mmOelhRjBIpt2"}
{"name":"Tholothian Heartwood Hilt","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Tholothian Heartwood Hilt[h3]\nWhile most lightsabers have synthetic hilts, Tholothian Jedi preferred a more organic approach. At their height, they crafted heartwood hilts from the timber of still-living trees The wood was then preserved in a specialized ritual-one more often used when a heartwood tree was dying. The resulting hilt is resistant to decay and can house a lightsaber's apparatus. The resulting lightsabers are beautiful works of art as much as they are weapons. The resins used to preserve the timber increase its weight, and wielders must take appropriate care in using them. This often translates to a stronger and more deliberate strike when this weapon does connect.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Unlimited Power[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 </div><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 Count 2</div><div>GM may spend [TH][TH][TH][TH] or [DE] to damage by one step. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":8000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"THOLOHILT"}},"_id":"3RJAeQvpyDoXjYTP"}
{"name":"Componentization","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Componentization[h3]\nThis mod allows a weapon to be broken down into a number of innocuous-looking pieces so that it can be smuggled into and out of places where weapons are not allowed or are highly regulated. When broken down, a componentized weapon looks like a collection of basic tools, comlinks, glow rods, datapad styluses, and other items any individual might be expected to carry. Each part also functions as that item as well. It takes two maneuvers to assemble or disassemble a weapon with this mod. Loss of or damage to a component ruins the weapon, and another will have to be acquired and modified. This attachment can be applied to any weapon with an encumbrance of 2 or less. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 56 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows a weapon to be broken into pieces and disguised as other items. A character must make a [B]Formidable ([DI][DI][DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics[b] or [B]Skulduggery check[b] to deduce the items are weapon parts. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"COMPONENT"}},"_id":"3V5hSjkhIEQLJxPy"}
{"name":"XCiter Overcharge","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]XCiter Overcharge[h3]\nA common—and dangerous—modification among espionage agents, an XCiter Overcharge allows an individual to empty a blaster's energy cell in a single, extremely powerful shot. This increases the output for an emergency kick, but it runs the risk of destroying the weapon and harming the user. While typically applied to holdout blasters, this attachment can be applied to any personal blaster weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech \"Nova\" Overcharge System.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 57 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As an incidental, shooters may overcharge the XCiter on their blaster. This gives the weapon to Prepare 1 item quality and increases the damage on the next attack by 4. Once it is fired the weapon runs out of ammo and must be recharged. </div><div>GMs may spend [TH][TH][TH] or [DE] from any combat check involving an overcharged shot with this weapon to cause the weapon to explode and deal full damage to the shooter. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"XCITEOVER"}},"_id":"3ym0xf22m7t9dojJ"}
{"name":"Augmented Buffer","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Augmented Buffer[h3]\n\nThis uncommon upgrade installs redundant systems within the electronics of an airspeeder, allowing it to be pushed beyond standard limits without risk of overload. Most teams find it simpler to replace any damaged components between races, ensuring that a pilot has fresh equipment for each race, rather than risk over-complicating the vehicle's systems. Augmented buffer may only be attached to vehicles of silhouette 2 or lower. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Jewel of Yavin[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases System Strain Mod - Increases System Strain by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"kfUbhrn82nL9vXku","name":"Increases System Strain Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADD"}},"id":"8exawqx9j4ro1ycm"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AUGBUFF"}},"_id":"4FVvT3pmyatuSj1Z"}
{"name":"Temperature Control Unit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Temperature Control Unit[h3]\nThis unit comes with\na specialized bodysuit that attaches to the module’s\ncooling or heating system, removing up to [SE][SE] from\nthe user’s checks to resist extreme heat or cold.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Removes up to [SE][SE] from checks to resist extreme heat or cold. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MILMODBACKTEMP"}},"_id":"4JtnzIW88dyGkSu5"}
{"name":"H9 Pistol Grip","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]H9 Pistol Grip[h3]\n\nA pistol grip replaces the stock or other grip on a long arm with one like that of a pistol, allowing it to be fired one-handed. Most blaster rifles feature a pistol-like grip by default, in which case this attachment makes additional modifications to make the weapon better-suited to one-handed use. This attachment can be used with any Ranged (Heavy) blaster rifle, blaster carbine, or slugthrower that does not possess the Cumbersome quality.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Weapon's skill changes to Ranged-Light Mod - Weapon's skill changes to Ranged-Light </div><div>Add [SETBACK] to any combat check made when firing one-handed. </div><div>Reduce Range to Medium Mod - Reduces weapon's range to Medium, if longer </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":400,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PISTOLGRIP"}},"_id":"4SfKlB1dVChr5W1C"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Light Freighter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Light Freighter[h3]\n      Converts a light freighter to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Defense Zone Mod - Increases Defense Zone by 1 </div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 </div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 2</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 Count 2</div><div>Adds two quad laser cannon turrets </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARALTFREIGHT"}},"_id":"4WfxfmQT7ghagQ0D"}
{"name":"Reinforced Magnetic Shielding","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reinforced Magnetic Shielding[h3]\nA delicately tuned magnetic field maintains the coherency of a lightsaber's plasma beam. Though this modification increases the strength of a lightsaber's magnetic shielding, the blade takes on some of the qualities of a solid weapon. With this modification, the wielder gives up some of the lightsaber's legendary penetrative capacity in order to deliver punishing electromagnetic impacts.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 48 - Knights of Fate[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Concussive Quality - The weapon’s attack can leave the target shell­-shocked from mighty blows or punishing shockwaves, unable to perform any but the most basic actions. The target is staggered (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Concussive rating. A staggered target cannot perform actions. </div><div>Knockdown Quality - When knockdown triggers, the target is knocked prone.\n    \n[P]Unless specified otherwise, Knockdown requires [AD][AD] to trigger, plus one additional [AD] per silhouette beyond one. </div><div>Pierce Quality - An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"QQf8B9koRsupvLFr","name":"Concussive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"The weapon’s attack can leave the target shell­-shocked from mighty blows or punishing shockwaves, unable to perform any but the most basic actions. The target is staggered (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Concussive rating. A staggered target cannot perform actions.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONCUSSIVE"}},"id":"sok21vdp9lrzolze"},{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"0xw21adce1ae8d49"},{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"vq88bvbofenbxtzn"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REMAGSH"}},"_id":"4Wwn5YzKYbgj5S0j"}
{"name":"Under-Barrel Flame Projector","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Under-Barrel Flame Projector[h3]\n\nUncommon but highly effective, the Firestorm by Czerka is a small, under-barrel flame projector designed to give an infantryman extra punch at short range. Illegal on many worlds and classified as a terror weapon, these weapons are typically used by only the most desperate or callous individuals. This attachment can only be applied to rifle-sized weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka \"Firestorm\" Under-barrel Flame Projector, Merr-Sonn XR14 Sunsear Flame Projector, SoroSuub \"Inferno\" Auxiliary Flamer.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds a flame projector to the weapon. </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"UBFP"}},"_id":"4oXQPqkBXSbWoUF7"}
{"name":"Sensor Baffler","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sensor Baffler[h3]\nUsing combination of broad-spectrum transmissions and low-power targeted ion pulses, a sensor baffler confuses enemy sensors, preventing them from determining a ship's precise location. A sensor baffler is not a passive system, but actively confuses enemy sensors, providing contradictory and nonsensical readings. As a result, the system does not truly conceal the ship's presence from enemies. Even inexperienced sensor operators can easily see that something is interfering with their system, but they are frustratingly unable to pinpoint the source. A sensor baffler does not include optical camouflage, and it has no effect on visible detection. Despite its shortcomings, a sensor baffler has lower power requirements and requires a less-sophisticated manufacturing process than a true cloaking device. This makes it an attractive alternative to those nearly unheard-of devices, and one available to a wider variety of ship types.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 62 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When active, upgrade difficulty of checks to determine vehicle's location using sensors twice. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":8000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SENSBAFF"}},"_id":"4xG3cqnwFwIcvVIZ"}
{"name":"Night Vision Scope","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Night Vision Scope[h3]\n\nThis attachment uses an optical system similar to a set of electrobinoculars that shows infrared wavelengths of light, effectively allowing the shooter to track heat signatures in dark or concealed areas, or through walls. It does not differentiate between heat generated by life forms and other kinds of heat, whether from natural or manufactured phenomena. (It is blind to life forms that do not give off heat.) This attachment can be used on any ranged weapon, with the exception of single-use weapons and weapons that would not realistically benefit from a scope. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Fabritech LRS Low-Light Scope, Zikon Optics Model 45 Infrascope.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Remove up to [SETBACK][SETBACK] on any checks to use this weapon due to darkness </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":700,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"NIGHTSCOPE"}},"_id":"552Mf8d7CRKGoiQy"}
{"name":"Micro-Rocket Armor Mounting","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Micro-Rocket Armor Mounting[h3]\nMicro-rockets are flexible (if dangerous) weapons favored as secondary arms by many bounty hunters (see [B]Micro-Rockets[b] on page 46), and generally fired from a mount installed in the wielder's armor. This attachment can be installed on any armor.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech Mag-Clip Micro-Rocket Mounting, Goseia HIC \"Last Word\" Launch/Targeter System, countless custom variants.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Enables armor to fire loaded micro-rockets. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"y7cpuTEB0oOqRA5q","name":"Limited Ammo Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Some weapons fire particularly large or complex projectiles that cost significant amounts of credits, or are themselves a complete weapon that once launched is expended. A weapon with the Limited Ammo quality may be used to make a number of attacks equal to its Limited Ammo rating before it must be reloaded with a maneuver. In addition, each shot expends one of a limited number of rounds of ammo, which must be purchased or otherwise obtained before the weapon can be used. This also applies to grenades and other “one use” weapons which have the Limited Ammo 1 quality (here, the user is not “reloading” the grenade, but drawing another to use—but mechanically they are equivalent).","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":5},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LIMITEDAMMO"}},"id":"3508svcf0rb69qec"},{"_id":"oYIf6fg6qw9ccPdH","name":"Remove Setback Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Remove [SETBACK] from all attack checks when using this weapon","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SETBACKSUB"}},"id":"kl2hz29vjhf3zxw4"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MICROROCKARMMOUNT"}},"_id":"59Pk8gBTwSER425L"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Cloud Car","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Cloud Car[h3]\nConverts a cloud car to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 </div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 </div><div>Adds a forward light auto-blaster </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARACLOUD"}},"_id":"5KHi5dY5tTD9IaLf"}
{"name":"Ghostfire Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Ghostfire Crystal[h3]\nThese kyber crystals grow in nearly invisible formations on a handful of far flung Outer Rim worlds. Their precarious spires of entirely transparent stones rise from rocky foundations. They are typically found at the peaks of mountains, when they can be located at all. Finders can use ghostfire crystals to construct a lightsaber with a blade as difficult to detect as the spire from which they harvested the crystal. Lightsabers with ghostfire crystals at their core produce no sound whatsoever, and the blades are dim and translucent compared to the incandescent fire of the other lightsabers. most curious of all are the illusory afterimages of the blades that follow the wielders' motions, disorienting foes and disguising the true position of their blades.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 53 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Wielder may spend [AD][AD][AD][AD] or [TR] to prevent the target from using the Parry talent to reduce damage from this attack. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":14000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"HL9ao4tKeqg0ExvA","name":"Defensive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFENSIVE"}},"id":"8n0c8qtji4sgrh7c"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"pkh7osjnlagk1a76"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GHOSTFIRE"}},"_id":"5ViniaPhO7QWOKSv"}
{"name":"Lorrdian Gemstone","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Lorrdian Gemstone[h3]\n\nLorrdian gemstones arc kyber crystals mined millennia ago by enslaved Lorrdians during the Kanz Disorders. Created by Force-sensitive Lorrdians to supplement the intricate kinetic communication developed among the slave populace, these gemstones were imbued with Force energies that allowed their possessors to read the emotions and actions of others. When installed in a lightsaber, a Lorrdian gemstone allows the wielder to predict the actions of an opponent, giving the wielder a decided edge in melee combat. A Lorrdian gemstone is a lightsaber crystal. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Defensive Quality - Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating. </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":9600,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"HL9ao4tKeqg0ExvA","name":"Defensive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFENSIVE"}},"id":"lz4yckk6eooep7yh"},{"_id":"kHPbGxHGs2JADBrS","name":"Deflection Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"An item with the Deflection quality increases the wearer’s ranged defense equal to its Deflection rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFLECTION"}},"id":"rwxvy01zecdnef3o"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LORRDIAN"}},"_id":"63OJR6OK23fosCNU"}
{"name":"Damping Emitter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Damping Emitter[h3]\nCareful modifications to the power cells and blade emitter allow the owner of a lightsaber to add a stun setting of sorts, drawing on the power of a normal lightsaber crystal, but with less intensity than is normally used. A damped lightsaber can still inflict serious injuries, however, as the emitter can only limit the power of a heavily modified crystal so much.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Nonr; users must custom make each lightsaber attachment.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As a maneuver, my adjust lightsaber to deal Stun damage.  Decrease damage by 2, increase critical rating by 1, lose Breach quality. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMPEMIT"}},"_id":"6McH3Dswh5z0IECv"}
{"name":"T9 Stinger Assault Boarding Tube","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]T9 Stinger Assault Boarding Tube[h3]\n\nPairing a docking tube with a powerful cutting system, the assault boarding tube is an indispensable tool for armed boarding actions. Its legitimate uses include aggressive customs enforcement and naval boarding actions. However, pirates also use the technology to force their way aboard a stricken ship. Pirate mechanisms are often custom-built, as obtaining a manufactured assault boarding tube is difficult for non-governmental entities. This mechanism may be installed on a craft of silhouette 3 or larger.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>May cut a hole in a docked craft's hull or airlock. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"k3obVb9z0RQsf7ud","name":"Decrease time to cut through hull by 1 round Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decrease time to cut through hull by 1 round","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BOARDTUBETIME"}},"id":"u5746b9lpnm12yq7"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BOARDTUBE"}},"_id":"6XJrweeMuXYBy29U"}
{"name":"Podracer Shield Generator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Podracer Shield Generator[h3]\nMost Podracers, whether custom-built racers or one of the many factory customs, mount a small, low-output shield generator in the cockpit. These shield generators are thin and cover primarily the very front. They only protect the driver, and only from exhaust wash from the engines and from debris kicked up from the track surface or flung at the racer by spectators (or other racers). They provide no protection to to the vehicle itself and are generally worthless in the event of a crash or other catastrophic event.\n[P]Some racers, though, value personal safety over tradition, running powerful, full-spectrum shield generators that protect the entire vehicle. These are usually built specifically for Podracing and are tuned for the kinds of environments typically found on Podrace courses. Racing teams that are too poor or too old-fasioned to use factory-built generators still use salvaged units pulled from wrecked starfighters or emplacement shield generators.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Novaldex GA21 Shield Generator, Chempat CED8089Y Shields, Keizar-Volvec Mk VIII Safety Shield, BGRE \"Bug Smasher\" Shield.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Sets Forward Defense Mod - Sets Forward Defense </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Q5hF8yx2DdQIR38p","name":"Increase Defense Zone Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Defense Zone by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFZONEADD"}},"id":"edxiymunhk0qca6y"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PODSHIELD"}},"_id":"6bUeeo40mYbIUrmu"}
{"name":"Cyclic Crystal Array","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Cyclic Crystal Array[h3]\n[P]Lightsabers rely on kyber crystals attuned to the wielder to create energy blades of different types. Under normal circumstances, swapping out one crystal for another is an arduous process requiring the lightsaber to be disassembled first. Unsatisfied with this situation, a handful of enterprising (if unorthodox) Force users have created attachments that allow for two (or more) crystals to be installed in a single lightsaber. With the press of a button, one crystal is swapped for another, granting unprecedented versatility to lightsaber wielders looking for additional functionality from their otherwise traditional weapon. This attachment can only be applied to lightsabers.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Additional Crystal with no HP Cost Mod - Add additional crystal with no HP cost </div><div>When lightsaber is ignited, may choose which active crystal to use.  If already ignited, activating another crystal requires a maneuver. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"qZkJQm7I1zgAp8XL","name":"Add Additional Crystal with no HP Cost Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Add additional crystal with no HP cost","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ADDCRYSTNC"}},"id":"dqwv360uqw3u3zh2"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CCARRAY"}},"_id":"6k0bSSQnh6VjjCwu"}
{"name":"Retrofitted Hangar Bay","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Retrofitted Hangar Bay[h3]\n\nSome starships or vehicles can be converted to carry additional, smaller vehicles within retrofitted holds. May only be used by ships of silhouette 5 and larger. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Retrofits Hangar Bay Mod - Retrofits Hangar Bay </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"P05cDVL99Q1ImQYz","name":"Increase Silhouette Capacity of Hangar Bay by 1 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Silhouette Capacity of Hangar Bay by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":5},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HANGERSIZE"}},"id":"2l7ojcruh5fa7yu9"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HANGAR"}},"_id":"6qnIMsQuzLuOvMGE"}
{"name":"Sensor Unit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sensor Unit[h3]\nThis unit features a raised, rotating\ndish not unlike the similar, smaller unit common to\nastromech droids. The sensor feeds a wrist-mounted\ntouchscreen and can be set to alert a soldier to movement nearby, or scan the area in general up to long\nrange. In addition to receiving narrative benefits such\nas advance warning of movement, the wearer adds automatic [AD] to Vigilance checks.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Forged in Battle[h4]","attributes":{"Vigilance":{"mod":"Vigilance","modtype":"Skill Add Advantage","value":1}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MILMODBACKSEN"}},"_id":"6wuaosWPvZ7cEbp6"}
{"name":"Engine Boost System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Engine Boost System[h3]\nThere are as many ways of boosting the output of a Podracer's engine as there are engines themselves. Afterburners, volatile chemical injectors, overpressure feeders, electro-magnetic wave-pusle generators, even arcane mixtures of highly reactive and dangerous fuels are all used to provide extra thrust from an engine. While these add-on systems do increase an engine's output, often dramatically so, they have a tendency to shorten its operational life and require extra maintenance to keep the engine operational and at peak performance.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Bespin Motors LK Model Afterburner Array, Slayn & Korpil Surgine-Series Fuel Accelerant System, SoroSuub RR-51 Chem-Injector Suite.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PODENGINEBOOST"}},"_id":"6yTV5xHnAL3C7pop"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Airspeeder","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Airspeeder[h3]\n      Converts an airspeeder to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 2</div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 2</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 </div><div>Adds a forward light blaster cannon </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARAAIR"}},"_id":"71JhwS1HUloO6zWq"}
{"name":"Model 2 Wrist Mount","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Model 2 Wrist Mount[h3]\n\nOriginally developed to allow species without opposable thumbs to use pistols, a wrist mount ensures that the user always has a weapon ready while keeping his hands free. Many users choose wrist mounts as a way to pack further firepower, while it is simply an aesthetic choice for some. Wrist-mounted weapons can be fired with a pressure-sensitive palm trigger, a particular wrist motion, or even by neural link. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Light) weapon.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Weapon can be worn on the wrist, freeing user's hands. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":275,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WRISTMOUNT"}},"_id":"75oetc4c7CvLKg6v"}
{"name":"Pseudo-Cloaking Device","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Pseudo-Cloaking Device[h3]\nWhile true cloaking devices are all but unheard of and limited to capital ships, so-called \"pseudo-cloaks\" incorporate an array of electronic masking devices and countermeasures to render a ship almost invisible to sensors. However, such devices have no visual effect, limiting their usefulness in close-range engagements. This attachment can be applied to any vehicle or starship.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Fabritech Gx-3 Sensor Screen, Sienar Intelligence Systems Electronic Masking System[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 66 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase the difficulty of checks to detect the ship with sensors by two. </div><div>Upgrade the difficulty of all combat checks once against the ship at Short range or further. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":12000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PSEUDCLOAK"}},"_id":"7FR6o137HnQOVGAO"}
{"name":"Shadowsheath","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shadowsheath[h3]\n\nBounty hunters, assassins, and other criminals often have a need to conceal weapons on their bodies to sneak them past guards or get close to a target without arousing alarm. A shadowsheath utilizes optical camouflage technology, but rather than conceal an entire body, its smaller projector is specifically designed to conceal a single weapon when kept in a holster or sheath. This attachment may be attached to any weapon with an encumbrance of 2 or less. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Merr-Sonn Shadowsheath WCS.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases the difficulty of any checks made to detect the sheath or the weapon it holds by two </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SHADOWSHEATH"}},"_id":"7MEZXuJjUOVEgcj3"}
{"name":"Ram Attachment","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Ram Attachment[h3]\n\nFor the most part, collisions with other ships, vehicles, or obstacles are to be avoided at all costs. There are times, however, when a desperate situation calls for a desperate measure and a pilot or driver must use his vehicle as a weapon. A number of bolt-on accessories for ships and vehicles are produced by major vehicle manufacturers that protect and reinforce prows or forward sections against collision. Items such as bantha bars, sloped fenders known colloquially as \"nerfcatchers,\" and custom-fit reinforced hull plating are all examples of the rich after market dedicated to protecting a vehicle in case of collision. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Stay on Target[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Treats the starship or vehicle's defense as 2 higher when instigating a collision. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":6500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RAM"}},"_id":"7N76kgEfFJ5brBgL"}
{"name":"Luxury Passenger Compartments","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Luxury Passenger Compartments[h3]\n\nCorrupt Imperial officials and powerful crime lords are more likely than Rebels to enjoy opulent living standards. However, Rebels who have regular contact with the rich and powerful sometimes find a little extravagance to be a purely practical investment. While scented air recyclers, a galley stocked with Corellian brandy, and other luxuries have little measurable effect on the Rebel war effort, the intangible benefits offered by a display of confidence and power should not be underestimated.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Desperate Allies[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add [BO] to all Charm, Deception, and Negotiation checks made against passengers within the vehicle.  Checks made against passengers who are accustomed to opulence and luxury have up to [SE][SE] removed instead. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LUXPASSCOMP"}},"_id":"7rWddxg0qTioRYeT"}
{"name":"Gimmellian Stealth Device","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Gimmellian Stealth Device[h3]\n[P]Reduces the range band of enemy ships’ passive sensors by 1 (to a minimum of close range) for detecting the Tallanx. In order to function, all power from shields and weapons must be channeled into the cloaking device. Rerouting power takes one action.    \n      [P][I]This is an optional no-cost attachment for the Tallanx-Class Stealth Fighter and the Darvro-Class Light Freighter.[i][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Strongholds of Resistance[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduces range band of enemy ships' passive sensors by 1 (to a minimum of close range) for detecting the Tallanx. </div><div>All power for shields and weapons must be rerouted to device for it to work.  Rerouting takes one action. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GIMMELSTEALTH"}},"_id":"7tY1aklobpKnXhCG"}
{"name":"Self-Repair Systems","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Self-Repair Systems[h3]\nSome sentients on the fringes of galactic civilization live a life of near-sonstant battle. For such individuals, a good suit of armor is vital, and keeping it in top condition is nearly as important. Some suits of armor include sophisticated self-repair suites, not dissimilar to the systems found in some droids. Smart materials, laminate extruders, electromagnetic assemblers and other systems work to keep the armor in one piece even under the greatest duress. This attachment can be applied to any armor with melee or ranged defense 1 or higher.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] INdustrial Automato Model 3 Autorepair Suite, AccuTronics Advanced Repair Unit[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Once per encounter as a maneuver, can have armor attempt to repair itself or assist in a repair.  Counts as Intellect 2 and Mechanics 2 ([PR][PR]). </div><div>There is no cost to repair armor, whether using the automatic feature, or personally repairing. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SELFREPSYS"}},"_id":"88YOK39ZptyTl6fZ"}
{"name":"Dart Gun","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Dart Gun[h3]\nThis is a simple device that uses springs or compressed air to fire a tiny alloy dart. While they do very little damage, these darts can be coated with a number of exotic substances, from sedatives to extremely lethal toxins. Dart guns are often concealed in comlinks, glow rods, cigarras, and other cylindrical items, but they can be used anywhere for both offensive and defensive purposes. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Enable the item to fire a single dart with the following profile: (Ranged [Light]: Damage 2; Critical 5; Range [Short]; Limited Ammo 1, Pierce 1). </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DARTGUN"}},"_id":"8VtoqVg47T19XLL7"}
{"name":"Smuggling Compartments","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Smuggling Compartments[h3]\n\nThese are concealed compartments installed in starships, especially freighters and transports, for the transportation of contraband. Used to hide goods and occasionally people from prying eyes, they are incredibly hard to spot. Common places for smuggling compartments are beneath deck plates, behind heavy equipment, or in a thousand other bolt-holes throughout a vessel. This may be added to any ship or vehicle with encumbrance capacity 25 or more. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Edge of the Empire Core Rulebook[h4][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment Mod - Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"V4X7JoVYyeHupNuO","name":"Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SMUGENC"}},"id":"r18toe3sechiyz3u"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SMUG"}},"_id":"8n0lB6f5h9ajMxvI"}
{"name":"Electron Baffled Engine","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Electron Baffled Engine[h3]\nBaffled engines not only offer increased speed due to their vectoring mechanisms, but also add additional defense to the aft sections of a ship.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 81 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 Count 2</div><div>Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod - Increases System Strain by Silhouette Count 5</div><div>Increase Aft Defense Mod - Increase Aft Defense by 1 Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8hDbXBn86M6AJeih","name":"Increases Speed by 2 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Speed by 2","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPEEDADD2"}},"id":"iqp9cyqkkl1pw058"},{"_id":"WzEhZZQs7ZiJaqsh","name":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADDSIL"}},"id":"zinic2wvoxjr4o6n"},{"_id":"6PGA8jqBl5zIX14v","name":"Increase Aft Defense Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Aft Defense by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ADDDEFAFT"}},"id":"wc0u97plz1f42cdr"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRAFTENGINEELECBAFF"}},"_id":"900bVogbUbkCPCvL"}
{"name":"Sensor Shunt","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sensor Shunt[h3]\nSensor shunts are passive stealth systems fitted to ships or vehicles to hide energy signatures. Unlike a scrambler, which draws attention to itself even as it fools sensors, shunts are quiet and unobtrusive. Ships or vehicles with these upgrades are nearly invisible to passive sensors and are difficult to detect with even active scanners. This attachment can be applied to any starship or vehicle.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase the difficulty of checks to detect this vessel using passive sensors by two, and the difficulty of checks to detect this vessel using active sensors by one, while it is traveling at speed 3 or lower. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SENSSHUNT"}},"_id":"9cEDIGxbEkSlvpe9"}
{"name":"Bipod Mount","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Bipod Mount[h3]\n\nLittle more than a pair of folding or collapsible legs mounted beneath the barrel of a long arm, bipods are used to stabilize awkward or heavy weapons to improve their firing characteristics. Especially useful when firing from behind low cover or from a prone position, bipods are typically used on squad support weapons, or by sharpshooters and snipers to better steady their weapons. This attachment can only be applied to rifles, carbines, and light repeating blasters, and takes one preparation maneuver to set up. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Galactic Arms XA Classic Bipod, Czerka M20 Marksman Bipod.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BIPOD"}},"_id":"9htjHoK5XVayoVi8"}
{"name":"Electronic Sighting System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Electronic Sighting System[h3]\n[P]By adding a small electronic device to the top of a blaster or other ranged weapon, a small holographic crosshair is projected a meter out from the weapon’s barrel. This increases accuracy by reducing the time it takes for the user to aim. Unfortunately, the holographic crosshair is readily visible to anyone on the weapon’s receiving end, especially in conditions of darkness or low light. This attachment can be used on any ranged weapon that could logically benefit from the addition of a sight.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Strongholds of Resistance[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows shooter to aim as an incidental once per round at short range.  Decreases the difficulty of Perception checks to locate the shooter in low light conditions by 1. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"o8iq2z289vlzae39"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ELECSIGHTSYS"}},"_id":"A7WQ8Inq6xoodf1Q"}
{"name":"Telescopic Optical Sight","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Telescopic Optical Sight[h3]\n\nPopular with marksmen and snipers, this attachment consists of a long tube attached to the top of a weapon with a number of precisely ground lens elements protected by an impact-resistant housing. The resulting scope magnifies distant images for long-range shooting. This attachment can be used on any ranged weapon (with the exception of one-use weapons like grenades, or weapons like flame projectors that would not realistically benefit from a sight). \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Merr-Sonn 80Z Telescopic Optical Sight, Zikon Optics Model 40 Marksman Scope.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decrease Long and Extreme Range Difficulty Mod - Decrease the difficulty of combat checks at long and extreme range. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"TOS"}},"_id":"AFF9NMQ4GdVyyWU3"}
{"name":"High-Performance Repulsor Cluster","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]High-Performance Repulsor Cluster[h3]\nWhile bulkier than other engines, repulsor clusters can offer high speed and increased protection for vehicles operating within a planetary atmosphere. This engine type cannot be mounted on starships.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 82 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 Count 4</div><div>Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod - Increases System Strain by Silhouette Count 5</div><div>Increase Forward Defense Mod - Increase Forward Defense by 1 </div><div>Increase Port Defense Mod - Increase Port Defense by 1 </div><div>Increase Starboard Defense Mod - Increase Starboard Defense by 1 </div><div>Increase Aft Defense Mod - Increase Aft Defense by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"TfqDzg8fQd6VBG9V","name":"Increase Speed Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Speed by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPEEDADD"}},"id":"1crbowdbnzlwj2l3"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRAFTENGINEREPCLUSTER"}},"_id":"AOA3GEs0bsURO3vd"}
{"name":"Mephite Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Mephite Crystal[h3]\n\nMephite crystals are rare, lustrous kyber crystals found in a handful of places in and around the Adega system. One of five types of crystal known collectively as \"Adegan crystals,\" mephite crystals are well-suited for use in lightsabers due to their internal structure and light-modulating capabilities. Like all Adegan crystals. mephite crystals are Force-reactive and can be infused with a small amount of a Force user's power. When installed in a lightsaber and infused with the Force, mephite crystals give off a small but steady Force signature that can be sensed by any nearby Force user A mephite crystal is a lightsaber crystal. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 8</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Force-sensitive characters using Force powers to sense their surroundings automatically detect a lightsaber using a mephite crystal if it is within the range of the power. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":10000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":10,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"e6b5zcersv6jprme"},{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRITSUB"}},"id":"5qm9yy1n2w9830qb"},{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"ectgcact7nfc1meg"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MEPHITE"}},"_id":"ARThuNOrx3LQwPO0"}
{"name":"Blaster Suppressor","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Blaster Suppressor[h3]\n\nThough generally not as loud as slugthrowers, blasters usually emit an audible crack or zap upon being fired. While military scouts and snipers are usually more concerned that a blaster bolt flash might give away their position or disrupt their night vision, those who operate in the galactic underworld often find the report of a blaster to be more troublesome. In order to address this issue, several arms manufacturers produce sound suppressors for a blaster muzzle, making the blaster virtually silent. This attachment can only be used with blaster pistols. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Merr-Sohn DS9 Blast Suppressor, Czerka \"Whispershot\" Silencer.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Lords of Nal Hutta[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds [SETBACK][SETBACK] to Perception or Vigilance checks made to locate a concealed shooter firing silenced blaster. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BLASTSUPP"}},"_id":"AWwO9aeT9atU3z5Q"}
{"name":"OmniScan 3 Integrated Scanner","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]OmniScan 3 Integrated Scanner[h3]\n\nWarriors must be aware of their surroundings at all times, and ready to respond to any threat. Because a hand-held scanner both requires the user to direct his attention to it and restricts his weapon use, it is common for military forces to integrate scanner systems into helmets. As usual, many Hired Guns follow suit, particularly those with a military background. Most integrated scanner systems utilize a heads-up display, projected on the inside of the helmet's visor. Some systems include a retractable mono-visor that extends only while the scanner is in use.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Built-in general purpose scanner </div><div>Adds [BOOST] to Perception checks to detect movement or hidden enemies. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTSCAN"}},"_id":"AcuHa4IjnclPHzTk"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Walker","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Walker[h3]\n      Converts a walker to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 2</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 Count 2</div><div>Adds a forward medium laser cannon </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARAWALK"}},"_id":"AryEcRTwZBC6ZNV8"}
{"name":"Holo-Tank","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Holo-Tank[h3]\n“Holo-tank” is a catchall term for a type of holoprojection\nsystem used aboard starships and in military facilities.\nProduced by a number of technology firms, holotanks\nare large, circular holoprojectors mounted in\ndecks or floors, typically in the center of large command\ncenters. Real-time tactical data from friendly forces is\nfed directly to the holo-tank, where it creates a threedimensional\nmodel of a battle that can be observed\nat various magnifications. Holo-tanks are instrumental\nin planning and executing large-scale military actions.\nWhen paired with proper tactical data networks, they\nprovide unparalleled battlespace awareness.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Imlok Technologies ARENA-2500,\nBrosso Mk. IX Tactical holoprojector, Chedak Communications\n“Omni-View\" LS-220 holo-tank.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Lead by Example[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Characters utilizing a holo-tank may always use Cool or Knowledge (Warfare)  when making Initiative checks. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HOLOTANK"}},"_id":"B1wcvQ3DijtXJMKj"}
{"name":"Thermal Shielding System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Thermal Shielding System[h3]\n\nUtilizing both active and passive cooling systems, along with an insulated body glove and special coatings on the armor plates, this attachment allows a wearer to withstand dangerously high temperatures. This thermal shielding is proof against open flames, molten rock and steel, intense heat, and even some forms of radiation. This attachment can be installed on any armor that covers the entire body and can be sealed. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Atlas Corp Model 451 Heat Exchanger, Min-Dal 3100 Firebrand Suit, Kaminoan Armorsmiths Thermal Shielding System.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduces the difficulty of Resilience checks made\n          to resist the effects of fire and extreme heat by one.\n          Removes up to [SETBACK][SETBACK] added to checks\n          due to extreme heat or fire. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"TSS"}},"_id":"B2TuJbNEbtYuR6EK"}
{"name":"Ion Shielding","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Ion Shielding[h3]\nRarely encountered in doby armor and more commonly (and usually illegally) applied directly to droid chassis, ion shielding provides protection against ionization blasters. Although the mitigation it grants is far from complete, the energy-dampening effects can keep a droid operational where it would otherwise be shutdown. This attachment can be applied to any armor with soak 2 or higher.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Outlaw Tech Ion Shielding, Industrial Automaton Mk. III Ion Guard[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase soak by 3 against weapons with Ion quality. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"IONSHIELD"}},"_id":"B3koiSpyt2Gy3B3g"}
{"name":"Blade Drain","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Blade Drain[h3]\n The Blade drain attachment works by creating a small power drain when in contact with another lightsaber blade. Once attached to a lightsaber hilt and wired into the power supply, the blade drain attachment draws energy from the power supply of an opponent's lightsaber via the energy blade contact is made. The draw is momentary but significant enough to reduce the effectiveness of an opponent's lightsaber, making it less capable of dealing damage.\n[P]There is, however, a risk that the drawn power could overload the power supply of the weilder's own lightsaber as the excess power is stored, causing a catastrophic failure in the device. Users of this modification consider it a small price to pay for reducing the combat effectiveness of their foes, a tradeoff that could save lives. This attachment can only be applied to lightsabers.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 50 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When making a combat check targeting an opponent with a lightsaber, character may spend [TR] to reduce opponent's lightsaber's base damage by one for remainder of encounter. </div><div>[TH][TH][TH] causes blade to collapse.  Cannot be reignited until character's next turn. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"HL9ao4tKeqg0ExvA","name":"Defensive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFENSIVE"}},"id":"cv8wt5570wjov7wx"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BLADEDRAIN"}},"_id":"BTyiEvqeFIf9kdsM"}
{"name":"Overcharge Valve","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Overcharge Valve[h3]\n\nAn overcharge valve is a simple (if dangerous) modification that allows the wielder of a blaster to discharge the entire ammunition reserve in a single, devastating shot. This attachment can be applied to any blaster or energy weapon that could logically benefit from it. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka \"One-Shot\" Overcharge Valve.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As incidental, weapon gains Prepare 1 quality and +4 damage for next attack.  After firing, weapon runs out of ammo. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"OVRCHARGEV"}},"_id":"BWrylpneDaKtV5b4"}
{"name":"Enhanced Hyperspace Shields","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Enhanced Hyperspace Shields[h3]\nFew things are more dangerous to a ship than colliding with a mass shadow in hyperspace. Although all ships are equipped with sensors intended to detect a mass shadow and automatically drop the ship out of hyperspace, such systems are not infallible. As an added level of protection, some engineers modify a vessel with  enhanced particle Shields designed to potentially save a ship from complete destruction in a case of a hyperspace collision. Many captains consider the drain on ship resources and the cost to be too great for additional protection against such a rare event, but these systems save lives. This attachment can be applied to any ship with a hyperdrive.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 66 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Downgrade difficulty of Astrogation checks made to navigate the ship through hyperspace once. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENHHYPSH"}},"_id":"BeXDCD0jXUYmXggb"}
{"name":"Stun Blaster Attachment","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Stun Blaster Attachment[h3]\nForce sensitives trained or experienced in other fields prior to embarking on their current path may feel more comfortable using a ranged weapon before resorting to their lightsabers. Others may have reason to disguise their lightsabers, yet retain immediate access to them. Still others reason that if the threat of an opponent can be eliminated at range, so much the better for all concerned. While carrying a blaster pistol is one solution, some prefer a melding of blaster and lightsaber, perhaps believing that a personal weapon best reflects the Force user when it represents all aspects of the user's life, both present and past. Still, the tenets of the Jedi Order apply, and life is to be preserved if at all possible. The stun blaster attachment is seen as an acceptable compromise in these situations.\n[P]By stripping down an otherwise functional stun blaster, wiring it into the power supply of a lightsaber hilt, and bolting the resulting device to that hilt, a Force user can make use of the blaster without relinquishing immediate access to the lightsaber. This cannibalized stun blaster has a shorter range. Due to the energy draw on the lightsaber's power supply, it cannot be used simultaneously with the blade, but it is often a useful addition to the wielder's weaponry. This attachment has saved more than one life on both ends of the lightsaber.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"1z9pkjj0d1h1wyt1"},{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"1gzguvq3wdigl65s"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STUNBLAST"}},"_id":"BqyAOPhPOgXpBGRm"}
{"name":"Reflex Grip","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reflex Grip[h3]\nThrough a delicate system of motion sensors and miniaturized motors built into a lightsaber hilt, a craftsperson can alter the lightsaber to respond to adjustments in grip and position with greater responsiveness. The split-second edge granted by this system allows a combatant to more easily parry an opponent's decisive stroke or block each of a hail of blaster bolts. Controlling the system and keeping it from overreacting to minute or inadvertent motions can be difficult to master, but the defensive advantage of a reflex grip can be worth the extra practice.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] None; users must custom make each lightsaber attachment.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When lightsaber is used to Parry or Reflect, suffer 1 additional strain, but count Parry and Reflect ranks as 1 higher. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"HL9ao4tKeqg0ExvA","name":"Defensive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFENSIVE"}},"id":"w25g0wn9ejzyewsl"},{"_id":"kHPbGxHGs2JADBrS","name":"Deflection Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"An item with the Deflection quality increases the wearer’s ranged defense equal to its Deflection rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFLECTION"}},"id":"0zf876q056lsqcs5"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REFLEXGRIP"}},"_id":"C13wlzFVW4UYrjiR"}
{"name":"(AD-15) Sublight Boost Thrusters","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sublight Boost Thrusters for AD-15[h3]\nThe craft's engines can be equipped with sublight boosters which considerably increase their output. Flying at higher speeds also makes the vehicle harder to handle in rough conditions such as asteroid fields, but when outrunning a patrol boat or pirate vessel, it can be the difference between life and death.\n[P][H4]<font size=1>Please see page 63 of the Special Modifications Sourcebook for details.</font>[h4][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":9000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"TfqDzg8fQd6VBG9V","name":"Increase Speed Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Speed by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPEEDADD"}},"id":"c25kvn0f6btr2kiq"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD15BOOSTTHRUST"}},"_id":"C3JPcmwkOdTo08dv"}
{"name":"Stun Pulse","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Stun Pulse[h3]\n\nA stun pulse attachment deals an electric shock to the target, in addition to its weapon's normal damage. Generally attached to truncheons or bludgeoning weapons, stun pulses are often used by law enforcement to disable suspects without killing them. A stun pulse can be attached to any bludgeoning Melee or Brawl weapon. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] CoroTech EV45 Pulse Coil, SoroSuub \"Enforcer\" Stunner.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Stun Quality - A weapon with Stun causes strain to the target. When the Stun quality is activated, it inflicts strain equal to the weapon’s Stun rating. Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"aDvHhRgItEzT7XHl","name":"Stun Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Stun causes strain to the target. When the Stun quality is activated, it inflicts strain equal to the weapon’s Stun rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STUN"}},"id":"sygsww4gvoevipzj"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STUNPULSE"}},"_id":"CRmZluB4ojWkR1rk"}
{"name":"Thisspiasian Stabilizing Coils","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Thisspiasian Stabilizing Coils[h3]\nThisspiasian weaponcraft focused, for centuries, on grace above all else. The antique manners of the Blood Court may embarrass the average citizen, but one can't argue with their results. Traditional weapons from Thisspias correct for even the clumsiest of maneuvers.\n[P]Survivors of the Jedi Purge return to this philosophy to strengthen their weaponry, Thisspiasian stabilizing coils are often stylized as a long tail that wraps itself around the hilt of a lightsaber. Rotating and curling with each movement, this device keeps the blade perfectly balanced.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Unlimited Power[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Remove Setback Mod - Remove [SETBACK] from all attack checks when using this weapon </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"THISSCOIL"}},"_id":"CTffFHWPZK6Ar73x"}
{"name":"Secondary Transponder","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Secondary Transponder[h3]\nAlthough it is possible to modify a ship's transponder signal, doing so is either easily detected or risks damaging the engines, depending on the method used. Mounting a secondary transponder to the engine is a one-time modification that allows the ship's crew to thereafter switch between two identities. When activated the secondary transponder overrides the data signal from the ship's primary transponder, while also generating an energy signature that disguises the activity of the ship's engine (these are the twp parts of a transponder signal). The cost of this attachment includes a false or stolen identity in Bureau of Ships and Services (BoSS) records. This attachment can be applied to any starship.\n[P][B]Models include:[b] Various Illicit Models[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 67 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Crew can switch to the secondary transponder as an action, making an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Computers check[b]. </div><div>An observer who scans the ship can detect discrepancies indicating the presence of a secondary transponder with a [B]Daunting ([DI][DI][DI][DI]) Computers check[b]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":20000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SECTRANSP"}},"_id":"D5OE7MSmgytAjxN9"}
{"_id":"DdOfLh4DoP7h2JMs","name":"Saddlebags","type":"itemattachment","img":"systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Saddlebags[h3]\nMade by purveyors of animal-handling gear such as VeTech and Piccatech, saddlebags are indispensable pieces of equipment for those who make their livings riding or working with beasts. Constructed from hides or reinforced synthetic textiles, saddlebags typically compromise a pair of large containers with sealed flap covers, connected by a broad belt or  a number of cables. Saddlebags are designed to be portable. They can be thrown quickly over a beast's haunches and, if necessary, removed just as quickly to be carried over the shoulder by the beast's rider. Saddlebags fit countless riding animals, and can be customized functionally and cosmetically to meet an individual's particular tastes and needs.\n[P]Saddlebags can only be worn by riding animals. They increase an animal's encumbrance threshold by 4.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 47 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Threshold Mod - Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 1 Count 4</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":25,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0,"isrestricted":false},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"all"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SADDLEBAGS","loaded":false}}}
{"name":"Stun Matrix","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Stun Matrix[h3]\n[P]A stun matrix is an additional defensive option for armor. Instead of enhancing the wearer's defenses directly, it unleashes a punishing pulse of energy that weakens the attacker in the hope of preventing a second strike. Installing this attachment requires the addition of insulation to protect the wearer form the effects of the stun matrix on top of the setup of the self charging battery and of the stun matrix itself. While the device is relatively bulky, it can be concealed if integrated subtly into a heavy armor frame, the better to surprise would-be attackers. This attachment can be applied to any armor that could logically benefit from having a stun matrix added.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 </div><div>When suffering hit from Melee, Brawl, or Lightsaber combat check, may spend [TH][TH] or [DE] to disorient attacker for 2 rounds. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STUNMAT"}},"_id":"DsJIuHQOoWUYAvtR"}
{"name":"(AD-1S) Sublight Boost Thrusters","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sublight Boost Thrusters for AD-1S[h3]\nThe craft’s engines can\nbe equipped with sublight boosters, which considerably increase their output. Flying at higher speeds\nalso makes the vehicle harder to handle in rough conditions such as asteroid fields, but when outrunning a\npatrol boat or pirate vessel, it can be the difference\nbetween life and death.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":9000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"TfqDzg8fQd6VBG9V","name":"Increase Speed Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Speed by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPEEDADD"}},"id":"mj2p5kixc2s4uwmy"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD1SBOOSTTHRUST"}},"_id":"DuEXplyPkXFoYk6b"}
{"name":"Grenade Cling","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Grenade Cling[h3]\nWhile some anti-vehicle explosive devices and some concussion grenades are equipped with an electromagnetic clamp as a standard feature, such capabilities are rare among anti-personnel grenades. With the addition of an electromagnet, adhesive polymer, plastoid webbing, or any of a dozen other measures, nearly any grenade or bomb can be made to latch onto its target, preventing escape and ensuring its destruction. The attachment can be added to any grenade or explosive device.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Grenade immediately adheres to its target and requires an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Athletics check[b] to remove. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":70,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GRENCLING"}},"_id":"EQRvrm32BBPfCbFH"}
{"name":"Water Reclamation Suit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Water Reclamation Suit[h3]\nWater reclamation systems are popular with scouts and hermits, especially those living or working on arid worlds. Produced by a variety of wilderness outfitters, like Survival Equipment Inc. and Gandorthral Atmospherics, these systems collect a body's waste moisture and distill it for drinking. Typically, the consist of a tight bodysuit worn under a suit of armor, that covers a wearer to the neck, wrists, and ankles, along with a matching pair of gloves and a filtermask that covers the mouth and nose.\n[P]Made from layers of synthetic fibermesh, the suit wicks sweat away from the skin and purifies it by means of integrated filtration media. It also collects waste moisture from the mouth and nose by means of the filtermask. The water is then collected in pouches spread across the suit and can either be decanted into a larger container or drunk straight from the suit by means of a long, flexible tube connected to the suit's back. Adding a Water Reclamation System to a suit of armor allows an individual to operate much longer in desolate environments without fear of running out of water. This attachment can be applied to any armor that could logically integrate the necessary pouches and tubing.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Upgrades ability of Resilience and Survival checks made in dry or hot environments due to scarcity of water twice. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WATERRECLSUIT"}},"_id":"EiuYwCP6LHbhf2ys"}
{"name":"Blaster Actuating Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Blaster Actuating Module[h3]\n\nA Blaster Actuating Module is a blaster modification popular with mercenaries, bounty hunters, and anyone needing to make the first strike count. Adaptable to nearly any blaster pistol, this attachment is a simple upgraded blaster actuating module with custom firmware and a stronger electromagnetic accelerator that provides more powerful and more penetrating blaster shots. Unfortunately, this excess power takes its toll on the weapon, and blasters so modified tend to develop reliability problems the longer they are used with this attachment. This attachment is only for use on Ranged (Light) blaster pistols. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] SoroSuub X440 \"Hammer Blaster Actuating Module, Dolmax Heavy Blaster Actuator, Arakyd 97R Enhanced Blaster Actuating Module.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 </div><div>Add Setback Mod - Add [SETBACK] to all attack checks when using this weapon </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"42rumy1txex4paxb"},{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"o31oayfhr6elyb88"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BLASTACT"}},"_id":"Eo55ZJvMCZ2pD6yJ"}
{"name":"Blaster Energy Dampener","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Blaster Energy Dampener[h3]\n\nA blaster, with its focused energy, is one of the most powerful ranged weapons, but those who wish to conceal their shots are often forced to resort to other weapons if they want to pass unnoticed. Some assassins and spies prefer a blaster energy dampener, an attachment that significantly reduces the visibility of a blaster bolt, at the cost of stopping power. While dampened blaster fire is still noticeable in totally dark or very dim environments, an assassin can make a shot in a well-lit environment and not worry about attracting too much attention. This attachment is only for use on Ranged (Light) and Ranged (Heavy) blaster weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka B78 Energy Dampener.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases the difficulty of checks made to detect this weapon's fire by one </div><div>Reduced Damage Mod - Damage -1 Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BLASTDAMP"}},"_id":"ErEldwn0F61w3BGm"}
{"name":"Extended Hilt","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Extended Hilt[h3]\n\nThe idea behind the extended hilt modification is to increase the lightsaber's striking i4 and cutting power by using the leverage of the longer handle and a two-handed grip to help focus the wielder's strength into the force of the blow. The extended hilt modification is also popular among Force users of unusual height or build as a way to capitalize on their size advantage in combat. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"fbolwm6jz64oyctn"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"EXTHILT"}},"_id":"EsnpbYfhOenojhhX"}
{"name":"Laser Focusing Array","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Laser Focusing Array[h3]\nLaser cannons are the mainstay weapons of many ships, and manufacturers constantly compete to outdo each other in their products' power, accuracy, and rate of fire. As well as consistently bringing new models to market, some manufacturers produce aftermarket upgrades to improve performance. Of course, many Technicians find their own ways to improve weapons systems through - often dangerous - tinkering, This attachment can be applied to any starship.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Taim & BAck G-1 Enhanced Laser Focusing Array, Loronar Corporations Mk III Optimized Galven Coils[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 66 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add automatic [AD] to combat checks made with the ship's laser cannons and turbolasers. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LASFOCUS"}},"_id":"FVxvvZWP3p9bOmDO"}
{"name":"Whisperthrust Engine","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Whisperthrust Engine[h3]\n\nProduced by Rendili StarDrive, the WhisperThrust Engine is a sublight drive that uses special supercooled gases and baffles to reduce a starship's sensor signature. Outlawed by the Empire, Rendili still man-ages to sell these engines through its prominent position in the Corporate Sector Authority. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Rendili StarDrive WhisperThrust engine.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases the difficulty of checks to detect this vessel by two while it is traveling at speed 3 or lower. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":7500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WHISPERTHRUST"}},"_id":"FZTTBZIfD7mCDpnX"}
{"name":"Scannerweave","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Scannerweave[h3]\nScannerweave is a passive stealth system consisting of an advanced sensor-blocking textile. Armor modified with scannerweave tends to be quieter thanks to the nature of the soft, flexible fabric. More importantly, its inherent qualities make the wearer nearly invisible to the various scanners and security sensors found in security vaults and data facilities. This attachment can be applied to any armor. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Ayelixe/Krongbing Passive Stealth.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Upgrades the ability of all opposed Stealth checks made against sensor and scanner operators once. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SCANWEAVE"}},"_id":"FbafB4jP5K81Nfnj"}
{"name":"Starhawk Sidecar","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Starhawk Sidecar[h3]\n\nThe Starhawk has an unusual feature: it can be fitted with a sidecar, allowing it to carry an additional passenger or transport extra cargo. The speeder bike also comes equipped with a rear tractor beam coupler to allow it to tow a repulsorsled for even more cargo capacity.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Capacity Mod - Increase Encumbrance Capacity by 1 Count 10</div><div>Increase Passenger Capacity Mod - Increase Passenger Capacity by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STARHWKSIDECAR"}},"_id":"FcekkqbQE3IM0wgW"}
{"name":"Minelayer","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Minelayer[h3]\nMinelayers, and their accompanying ordnance, are anti-ship weapons sold by numerous major galactic arms manufacturers. Mines are typically deployed in defensive positions, used to deny areas to vehicle traffic or to create fire lanes for weapon emplacements, but they can also be used offensively in a manner similar to missile or torpedo launchers. They come in a variety of styles—from simple concussion mines to sophisticated gravity mines—and grant a small vessel such as a starfighter or patrol boat, a damage capacity well out of proportion to its size. This attachment can be installed on any starship.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] GSI M-L4 Seeker. Czerka Arms Mk. IX Proton Mine.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 64 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows vehicle to carry a number of space mines equal to its silhouette. </div><div>Pilot or gunner may make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] to deploy a mine anywhere within close range. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MINELAYER"}},"_id":"FdrnFPcsG62bbBIt"}
{"name":"Shortened Barrel","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shortened Barrel[h3]\n\nShortened barrels are a handy modification used by spies, plain-clothes law enforcement officers, and anyone needing to conceal the fact that they are carrying a weapon. Little more than a replacement barrel shorter than the standard one, this attachment makes concealing a pistol easier, and can improve the speed of a quick draw. This attachment can only be applied to Ranged (Light) pistol weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Arakyd SB4 \"Stubber\", SoroSuub SBSS Reduced Length Barrel.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduces the difficulty of checks made to conceal\n          this weapon by 1. </div><div>Reduced Range Mod - Decreases weapon's range by one Range Band </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SHB"}},"_id":"FhR2YFpQ4zt7fCms"}
{"name":"Power Unit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Power Unit[h3]\nThis portable power can recharge a\ndepleted piece of equipment as an action, or a droid\nor larger piece of machinery in two hours. Once per encounter, it can allow the wearer of the backpack to\nignore an “out of ammo\" [DE] result in the same manner\nas an extra reload (see page 197 of the [B]Age of Rebellion[b] Core Rulebook).[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>May recharge a depleted piece of equipment as an action, or a droid or larger piece of machinery in two hours. </div><div>Once per encounter, wearer may ignore an \"out of ammo\" [DE] result in the same manner as an Extra Reload. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MILMODBACKPOW"}},"_id":"Fid5iBF46ut9biRu"}
{"name":"Weapon Sling","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Weapon Sling[h3]\n\nSlings are lengths of hide or synthetic fabric designed to allow easy handling of long arms like blaster rifles and slugthrower rifles. They come in a dizzying array of styles, from the simple adjustable single-strap sling for carrying a weapon off the shoulder to multi-strap slings made of specialized materials that allow for any number of custom sling configurations. These attachments can only be used with Ranged (Heavy) weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Custom-tooled Bantha hide sling, Tactical three-point sling, Quick-release one-point drop sling.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WEPSLING"}},"_id":"FpfKmL5aABCHyHq6"}
{"name":"Engineering Access","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Engineering Access[h3]\n\nOne of the Explorers more intelligent design features is the network of sub-deck access passages. Granting easy access to nearly any internal system on the ship, the cramped passages allow the engineer to respond quickly to problems. Anyone working on the internal systems of the E-9 Explorer-class vessels, such as the power system, hyperdrive, computers, sensors, etcetera, gains [BO] to any Mechanics or Computers skill checks thanks to the ease of reaching systems that are typically hidden behind bulkheads and sealed beneath deck plates.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Enter the Unknown[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Anyone working on internal systems, such as power systems, hyperdrive, computers, sensors, gain [BOOST] to Mechanics and Computer checks due to the ease of reaching such typically hidden systems. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":7500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENGACCESS"}},"_id":"Fqgy8x6Ay0X6wRjM"}
{"name":"Bio-Support Dispenser","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Bio-Support Dispenser[h3]\nSophisticated medical technology integrated into armor can enhance the effects of in-combat treatments through carefully regulated and distributed dosages. This system applies medication automatically as the wearer's vitals begin to suffer, and It Includes an internal bacta reservoir for sealing the most grievous injuries. This attachment may only be installed on a fully enclosed suit of armor, such as laminate, clone trooper, or heavy battle armor[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 64 - Rise of the Separatists[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When the wearer heals strain at the end of an encounter, they also heal I wound if they suffered any wounds during the encounter. In addition, the first time in an encounter that the character's current wounds exceed half their wound threshold, the armor automatically applies a stimpack to the character </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BIOSUPPORT"}},"_id":"G70QoUBsrKeUbbqQ"}
{"name":"Integrated Slicer Gear","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Integrated Slicer Gear[h3]\nSlicers must often conduct their work under strict time constraints and less than ideal conditions. By integrating a customized computer, dataports and gesture interface circuitry into worn armour, a slicer can ensure that the tools of the trade are always at hand and almost impossible to lose. A visor-mounted heads-up display or holographic image streams the data the slicer needs, while specially designed gloves or gauntlets allow the slicer to manipulate code using nothing more than gestures and brief voice commands. This attachment can be applied to any armor.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] MerenData Mobile XR-1, numerous custom variants[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Counts as having Slicer Gear.  Can be controlled by gesture or voice. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTSLICGEAR"}},"_id":"GAWl3iyIS8srp11y"}
{"name":"Self-Destruct System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Self-Destruct System[h3]\nSelf-destruct systems are found on many pieces of espionage gear, especially bags, attaché cases, and diplomatic pouches. They use small, low-yield, shaped-charge explosives to destroy the item in case of theft, emergency, or improper usage. For example, an attaché case could be equipped with a self-destruct system that activates when an incorrect lock combination is entered. The explosions are usually very contained, but can be modified to deal damage to others nearby when the device detonates. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Equips the item with a single use explosive self-destruct system that inflicts 5 damage to all characters within engaged range </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":550,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SELFDEST"}},"_id":"Gaa2eHywfy8KTDBt"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Bulk Transport","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Bulk Transport[h3]\n      Converts a bulk transport to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Defense Zone Mod - Increases Defense Zone by 1 Count 2</div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 2</div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 5</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 Count 5</div><div>Adds two heavy laser cannon turrets </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARABULK"}},"_id":"Gf4TAZNiejdDiFzj"}
{"name":"Holographic Shell","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Holographic Shell[h3]\nHolographic shells use a combination of optical camouflage and high-resolution holography to create a disguised exterior for a ship or vehicle. A disguise must be programmed into the system's memory in advance, and the memory can hold only one disguise. Once active, a disguise cannot be changed on the fly. Holographic disguises are only effective at distances of several meters or more, however; touching or closely investigating the disguise ruins the illusion. This attachment can be applied to any starship or vehicle.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Provides a ship or vehicle with a holographic disguise. A [B]Daunting ([DI][DI][DI][DI]) Perception check[b] is required to see through the disguise at a distance. Physical examination immediately detects the disguise. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HOLOSHELL"}},"_id":"Gr4lYGvPY9Hw9QX3"}
{"name":"SmartMed 2000 Integrated Med-Systems","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]SmartMed 2000 Integrated Med-Systems[h3]\n\nFor some, it is not enough for their armor to simply prevent injury—it must lessen the effects of those wounds they do suffer. Integrated med-systems range from automated stim-injectors to sophisticated medical computers and full-body bacta baths. Though they can never replace a doctor or medical droid, these med-systems can keep the user alive long enough to get proper treatment, or to continue fighting despite his wounds. This attachment can be added to any armor that covers the majority of the wearer's body, subject to the GM's discretion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Once per session, may apply stimpack as incidental. </div><div>All Medicine checks made to heal wearer gain [BOOST]. </div><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"BED3k4PiTGDgBfG4","name":"Successful Medicine checks heal +1 wound Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Successful Medicine checks heal +1 wound.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HEALPLUSONE"}},"id":"1dw5nonigkh7x0dx"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTMEDSYS"}},"_id":"GwNJ8P6F9WvLGlk2"}
{"name":"Under-Barrel Grenade Launcher","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Under-Barrel Grenade Launcher[h3]\n\nUnder-barrel grenade launchers are designed to give soldiers or squads heavy anti-infantry or light anti-vehicle capabilities in a small package. This attachment consists of a basic, smooth-bore barrel attached to a magazine with an automatic feed system. It carries up to six grenades and is fired by a simple press of a button. It adds extra weight to the weapon it's mounted to, however, which makes the entire assembly quite barrel heavy. This attachment can only be applied to rifle-sized weapons (Ranged (Heavy) weapons). \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka \"Thumper\" Under-barrel Grenade Launcher, SoroSuub XA203 Auxiliary Grenade Launcher, Zone Control \"Viper\" Under-Barrel Grenade Launcher.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Weapon can fire grenades using the grenade profile, Ranged (Heavy) skill, and has Medium range. </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. Count 2</div><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 Count 2</div><div>Limited Ammo Quality - Some weapons fire particularly large or complex projectiles that cost significant amounts of credits, or are themselves a complete weapon that once launched is expended. A weapon with the Limited Ammo quality may be used to make a number of attacks equal to its Limited Ammo rating before it must be reloaded with a maneuver. In addition, each shot expends one of a limited number of rounds of ammo, which must be purchased or otherwise obtained before the weapon can be used. This also applies to grenades and other “one use” weapons which have the Limited Ammo 1 quality (here, the user is not “reloading” the grenade, but drawing another to use—but mechanically they are equivalent). </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"y7cpuTEB0oOqRA5q","name":"Limited Ammo Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Some weapons fire particularly large or complex projectiles that cost significant amounts of credits, or are themselves a complete weapon that once launched is expended. A weapon with the Limited Ammo quality may be used to make a number of attacks equal to its Limited Ammo rating before it must be reloaded with a maneuver. In addition, each shot expends one of a limited number of rounds of ammo, which must be purchased or otherwise obtained before the weapon can be used. This also applies to grenades and other “one use” weapons which have the Limited Ammo 1 quality (here, the user is not “reloading” the grenade, but drawing another to use—but mechanically they are equivalent).","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":5},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LIMITEDAMMO"}},"id":"8c5pi9a2aieg9ifb"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"UBGL"}},"_id":"Hf9QFqbsj447tq59"}
{"name":"Enhanced Prison Lockup","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Enhanced Prison Lockup[h3]\nA prisoner lockup is an aftermarket modification that provides a ship with a comprehensive prisoner handling and transporting system. It includes two cells that hold one human-sized individual each, with sufficient life support and basic necessities. The kit also includes numerous security systems for the lockup itself an the ship at large. Cameras and motion sensors are installed and powerful electronic locks are fitted to hatches and doors throughout the ship. This attachment can be installed on any vessel capable of carrying prisoners.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 64 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Full incarceration and security suite for 2 prisoners. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENPRISONLOCK"}},"_id":"HiahvqOADrwTjaKN"}
{"name":"Storage Unit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Storage Unit[h3]\nThis empty module has a variety of\npockets and pouches designed to store survival gear,\nspare blaster gas canisters, power packs, field rations,\nand a variety of other pieces of equipment used by\nthe Rebel Alliance. This unit increases the wearer’s\nencumbrance capacity by 3.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Threshold Mod - Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 1 Count 3</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":25,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MILMODBACKSTO"}},"_id":"HkXJgCYcemmwQB4L"}
{"name":"Rapid-Recharge XCiter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Rapid-Recharge XCiter[h3]\nSpeciffically modified gas conversion enablers can allow a blaster pistol or rifle to achieve much higher rates of fire than those of a true repeating blaster. Along with modifying or replacing the XCiter, and potentially the blaster actuating module. Technicians making heavy modifications to a blaster also often modify the trigger to allow for fully automatic fire when the user keeps it depressed. Such high rates of fire mean a considerable loss in accuracy. Nevertheless, the advantages offered by a rapid-fire weapon outweigh these drawbacks for some users. This attachment can be applied to any blaster.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech XCelerator, SoroSuub M-3 Recycling Module, various custom models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Auto-Fire Quality - A weapon with Auto-fire can be set to shoot in rapid succession and potentially spray an area with bolts, flechettes, slugs, or other types of projectiles. The advantage in using Auto-fire is that it has the chance to hit multiple targets or hit a single target multiple times.\n\n[P]Attacking with a weapon on Auto-fire is generally less accurate and the attacker must increase the difficulty of the attack check by [DI]. The user may choose to not use the Auto-fire quality on a weapon; in this case, he cannot trigger the quality but also does not suffer the aforementioned penalty.\n\n[P]If the attack hits, the attacker can trigger Auto-fire by spending [AD][AD]. Auto-fire can be triggered multiple times. Each time the attacker triggers auto-fire, it deals an additional hit to the target. Each of these counts as an additional hit from that weapon, and each hit deals base damage plus the number of uncancelled [SU] on the check.\n\n[P]These additional hits can be allocated to the target, or to other targets within range of the weapon. If the attacker wishes to hit multiple targets, he must decide to do so before making the check. Furthermore, if he wishes to hit multiple targets, his initial target must always be the target with the highest difficulty and highest defense (if this is two separate targets, the GM chooses which target is his initial target). The initial hit must always be against the initial target, subsequent hits generated can be allocated to any of the other designated targets.\n\n[P]Auto-fire weapons can also activate one Critical Injury for each hit generated on the attack per the normal cost; the Critical must target the target of the specific hit. </div><div>Inaccurate Quality - Inaccurate weapons are weapons of a shoddy or inferior construction which means they are less likely to be accurate or precise. Alternatively, the weapon’s nature may inhibit accuracy. Inaccurate weapons add [SE] to the attacker’s dice pool equal to their Inaccurate rating. Count 3</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RAPRECXC"}},"_id":"HqlNA5jngF7lVa2k"}
{"name":"Retractable Weapon System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Retractable Weapon System[h3]\nA staple of spies and infiltrators, this simple mechanical apparatus deploys and retracts a weapon from a hidden spot aboard a ship or vehicle. The does not include the weapon, just the retractable mechanism and the work done to make a concealed space for the weapon beneath duralloy or other hull plates. This attachment can be applied to any starship or vehicle.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Provides a vehicle with a hidden compartment and a device for deploying a weapon. Deploying or retracting a weapon requires a maneuver. Discovering a retractable weapon system requires a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Perception check[b] and a thorough search of the ship or vehicle in question. The GM has final say if a weapon is suitable for the retraction system based on the size of the ship or vehicle. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RETWEAPSYS"}},"_id":"IDH2TYdy03HLbUhS"}
{"name":"Sapith Gem","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sapith Gem[h3]\n\nSaid to originate from a strange and mysterious world called Lwhekk in the Unknown Regions, sapith gems are similar to krayt dragon pearls in that they were formed when rocks containing a kyber crystal were consumed by a great beast. In this case, the beast was a massive volice worm, which died out long before the present day. Thus, the only way to find these vanishingly rare crystals is to dig them out from the fossilized remains of a volice worm. Shaped like serpent scales, these smooth, lustrous crystals have an incredibly complex internal structure, which magnifies the intensity of any light that passes through them. When installed in a lightsaber, a sapith gem creates a powerful, intense beam that can pierce nearly anything with ease. A sapith gem is a lightsaber crystal. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":18000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":10,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"uxlR4gKZzxKvzeN1","name":"Breach Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach).","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BREACH"}},"id":"48jmrk9rnj98otgm"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"y1amtxxqfllugrgq"},{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRITSUB"}},"id":"hpabctdqg6saw8zi"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SAPITH"}},"_id":"IDI8PhpSVTDU0l4Q"}
{"name":"Hull/Keel Reinforcement","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hull/Keel Reinforcement[h3]\n\nEven the cheapest, most unreliable starships are durable items built to withstand the incredible amounts of abuse heaped on them by decades in space. Hull or keel reinforcement is an easy way to improve a vehicle or vessel's durability. Extremely old vessels, such as most of those fielded by the Rebel Alliance, can also benefit from a hull or keel reinforcement by shoring up damaged or fatigued hull members and adding support bracing at strategic locations. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Stay on Target[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"98Fa4BI2m8IVJdFp","name":"Increase Hull Trauma Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Hull Trauma by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HULLADD"}},"id":"dl4o40rhq0o03ygw"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HULLREINF"}},"_id":"IJx8rnMWNX0gahrS"}
{"name":"Tainted Nightsister Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Tainted Nightsister Crystal[h3]\nThe Nightsisters rose and fell as a faction untouched by the conflicts between Jedi and Sith. As such, they had little time to adopt the iconic lightsabers as their weapons of choice. This has not stopped dark side Mystics from trying to fuse Nightsister magic with Sith weaponry. Most experiments yield no fruit, but some have made for particularly terrifying advancements. Tainted Nightsister crystals were once pure Kyber crystals. Soaking them in Dathomiri Waters of Life perverts their connection to the Force. The resulting blade emits a choking, putrid green smoke when active.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Unlimited Power[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Disorient Quality - A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs. Count 3</div><div>Vicious Quality - When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result. Count 4</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":13000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":10,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"vxbivv1mv5vhwe40"},{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"rs6m6wptminf9ikk"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"TAINTNIGHT"}},"_id":"IcmoNXcAFZAkyu5i"}
{"name":"Droid Brain Defense System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Droid Brain Defense System[h3]\nAn extremely unusual upgrade generally reserved for powered armor suits, a droid brain defense system uses a full sensor suite to alert wearers to and help them avoid threats. The most basic models simply warn the user of threats and indicate ideal cover positions through a haptic interface or by voice. More advanced models incorporate a system of complex motors or even repulsor generators throughout the armor to literally throw the wearer out of the way of incoming fire. These droids often develop highly paranoid personalities, and their earnest attempts to protect their master even outside of combat can prove highly inconvenient.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 53 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Defense Mod - Increases Defense value by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DROIDBRAINDEF"}},"_id":"IdW8jbraSVZT2A0D"}
{"name":"Enhanced XCiter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Enhanced XCiter[h3]\nOutlaw Techs have long known how to modify the gas\nconversion enabler in a blaster to yield a more highly\nenergetic—and correspondingly more destructive—payload. Such modified XCiter modules are highly\nunstable, however, and are sometimes disparaged as\nbeing just as dangerous to the wielder and anyone\nelse nearby as to the enemy. Despite the risk and the\nillegality of the modification, many outlaws seek out\nsuch customizations to gain an edge in a firefight. This\nattachment can be applied to any blaster.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decrease Critical Mod - Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1 </div><div>GM may spend [DE][DE] to cause blaster to explode, destroying blaster and inflicting automatic Critical Injury on wielder. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"0yee3vccklge1vu3"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENXCITER"}},"_id":"J02ZvUf9N0pdPGD4"}
{"name":"Flickerphase Blade","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Flickerphase Blade[h3]\nConsidered dishonorable and unsporting by most Jedi, so-called flickerphase modifications were never widely adopted. With a few simple modifications, a lightsaber can be made to intermittently and randomly ignite and extinguish its blade, making it appear to fIicker on and off. While this unpredictable element adds some difficulty for the wielder, it is almost impossible for an opponent to time blocks and parries effectively.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 48 - Knights of Fate[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduced Damage Mod - Damage -1 Count 2</div><div>Inaccurate Quality - Inaccurate weapons are weapons of a shoddy or inferior construction which means they are less likely to be accurate or precise. Alternatively, the weapon’s nature may inhibit accuracy. Inaccurate weapons add [SE] to the attacker’s dice pool equal to their Inaccurate rating. Count 2</div><div>When attacking with this lightsaber, targets cannot use the Parry incidental to reduce the damage of the attack </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"5xkp3rqcay54tnvn"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"FLICKERPHASE"}},"_id":"JOqUwDOR4GuWI5Hs"}
{"name":"Droid Brain Detonator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Droid Brain Detonator[h3]\nWeapons manufacturers, combat engineers, and sabotage specialists are constantly inventing new triggers and detonators for explosive devices of all kinds, in order to provide for every conceivable situation. One of the most sophisticated and uncommon triggers makes use of an actual droid brain. Whereas timers, proximity detectors, and other common detonators are all effective within their narrow parameters, a droid brain is adaptable for nearly any situation or plan. A droid brain is able to abide by extremely specific trigger conditions and to follow complex instructions. For instance, users might instruct a detonite charge to wait thirty minutes after several specific individuals have entered a facility before igniting, or tell their frag grenade to avenge them should they fall in battle.\n[P]Droid brain detonators are intensely loyal, even by droid standards, but they tend to develop distinct personality quirks over their relatively short existences. Some are annoyingly chipper and enthusiastic, perhaps owing to additional layers of obedience programming, while others exhibit anything from childlike naivete to nihilistic moroseness. This attachment can be applied to any grenade or explosive device.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Explosive's detonator is controlled by a droid brain that can activate under any predetermined circumstance. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"a