{"name":"(AD-1S) Cargo Pod","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Cargo Pod for AD-1S[h3]\nThe cargo pods for this craft are large, cylindrical affairs, designed for efficiency, not aesthetics. These pods can even be retrofitted to carry passengers, though they do not make for comfortable quarters.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 62 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Capacity Mod - Increase Encumbrance Capacity by 1 Count 50</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1400,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8YgvY9ltV3k1b96u","name":"Increase Passenger Capacity by 2 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Passenger Capacity by 2","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PASSADD2"}},"id":"2jl6n42m2yhl8kcy"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD1SCARGOPOD"}},"_id":"JjHxLWRB5S3xGU96"}
{"name":"Enhanced XCiter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Enhanced XCiter[h3]\nOutlaw Techs have long known how to modify the gas conversion enabler in a blaster to yield a more highly energetic - correspondingly more destructive - payload. Such modified XCiter modules are highly unstable, however, and are sometimes disparaged as being just as dangerous to the wielder and anyone else nearby as to the enemy. Despite the risk and the illegality of the modification, many outlaws seek out such customizations to gain the edge in a firefight. This attachment can be applied to any blaster.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Outlaw Tech Custom XCiter\n[P][H4]<font size=1>Please see page 54 of the Special Modifications Sourcebook for details.</font>[h4].[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decrease Critical Mod - Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1 </div><div>GM may spend [DE][DE] to cause blaster to explode, destroying blaster and inflicting automatic Critical Injury on wielder. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"oom6a6q266k16cep"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"USERATTACH2"}},"_id":"JwEADaNDkrhZnEux"}
{"name":"Multi-Band Comlink","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Multi-Band Comlink[h3]\n\nIt is common practice to incorporate a long-range comlink into a helmet. Many military or otherwise advanced helmets include a comlink as standard, and it is a fairly simple procedure to attach one to nearly any helmet. Some helmet comlinks are activated by tapping a button on the exterior of the helmet or somewhere else on the armor, while others are activated by voice or even a particular head motion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>A long range comlink is integrated into helmet. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MULTICOMLINK"}},"_id":"K4ALeS3IeiBXOtxc"}
{"name":"Reflec Adaptive Skin","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reflec Adaptive Skin[h3]\nReflec is an advanced polymer that possesses adaptive light-warping and sensor-damping properties. When applied to armor, reflec acts as an optical camouflage even in fully illuminated areas. This attachment can be applied to any armor. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] CorChemCo Reflec Treatment.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]","attributes":{"Stealth":{"mod":"Stealth","modtype":"Skill Rank","value":0}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REFLADAPSKIN"}},"_id":"K73S4B7nbv0szZ6e"}
{"name":"Sonic Scope","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sonic Scope[h3]\nOriginally developed to overcome personal cloaking devices and other sensor-baffling defenses, a sonic scope uses ultrasonic sound waves to detect a target and generate a visual representation. With proper calibration, the sonar waves can be set to pass through even duracrete and other solid surfaces. This attachment can be used with any Ranged (Heavy) weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] CryonCorp PL-1 \"Second Sight\" Scope, SoroSuub Model Z Integrated Sonar System[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 56 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>May observe and target enemies who are completely hidden by solid objects. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SONICSCOPE"}},"_id":"K9t1XXeu3PBYYRTO"}
{"name":"Fogger Smoke Generator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Fogger Smoke Generator[h3]\n\nA smoke generator creates thick black or grey smoke that inhibits line of sight. This may only be installed on ground vehicles, landspeeders, or airspeeders, and only works on planets with an atmosphere.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Provides concealment that adds [SETBACK][SETBACK][SETBACK]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"FOGGEN"}},"_id":"KB3YJ6GP7LjNyEhh"}
{"name":"Unstable Kyber Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Unstable Kyber Crystal[h3]\nThe Kyber crystal is the heart of a lightsaber, but as with the hearts of organic beings, there can be imperfections. There are many opportunities between mining and use for a crystal to become unstable. It could develop hairline fractures in initial transit. Its wielder might subject it to extreme stress in use. Either way, power can begin to leak out of the crystal itself.\n[P]Under normal circumstances, these imperfections will not affect a lightsaber's performance. With the right knowledge, however, a Force user can harness the leaking energy for their own ends. By performing a lengthy ritual with the lightsaber, a Mystic can draw some of its power into themselves for a time.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Unlimited Power[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>As maneuver, increase Force rating by 1. This persists until using the extra [FO] to fuel Force talent or Force power. However, GM may spend [TH][TH][TH][TH] or [DE] to cause lightsaber to sputter and fail, if this happens may not reignite lightsaber for one hour. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":16000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":10,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"UNSTKYBER"}},"_id":"KDRMmhXEAk0QJqLq"}
{"name":"Pressurized Gas Cartridge","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Pressurized Gas Cartridge[h3]\nWhile a spray injector does not typically expel its contents with sufficient force to inflict serious harm, there is no particular reason it cannot do so if a tinkerer is willing to change out the factory-standard gas cartridge for one with a bit more kick. Needless to say, making such an alteration voids the multi-goo gun's warranty.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 45 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 5</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"UxVhTRp64V0tvmhT","name":"Burn Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Weapons with Burn inflict damage over time. If the attack is successful, the target continues to suffer the weapon’s base damage for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Burn rating. Damage is applied at the start of each of the target’s actions.\n\n[P]A victim might be able to stop the damage by rolling around on the ground and making an Agility check as an Coordination check action. This is an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Coordination check[b] on hard surfaces such as the hall of a spaceship, or an [B]Easy ([DI]) Coordination check[b] on grass or soft ground. Jumping into a body of water stops the damage immediately. Both situations assume the flame is from actual combustion rather than a chemical reaction. With the latter, there is usually little the victim can do.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BURN"}},"id":"ai8ccyn3lmm5056v"},{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"fujgsn23edomdsge"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MULTIGOOGASCART"}},"_id":"KTKSdeyIiaayljgz"}
{"name":"Scanner-Proof Hardware","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Scanner-Proof Hardware[h3]\nScanner-proof hardware is a collection of upgrades that together make a weapon virtually invisible to scanners. This mod typically replaces a weapon's stock, foregrip, and any other furniture with lightweight poly-carbonates woven with scanner-spoofing fibers. In addition, most if not all metallic parts—frame, trigger group, barrel, etc.—are replaced with fiber-reinforced polycarb pieces. This mod is extremely illegal. Being caught with a weapon that can pass through scanners without being detected is usually a one-way ticket to the nearest Imperial stockade. This attachment can be applied to any weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 57 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>This weapon cannot be detected by standard weapon-detecting technologies. Characters using advanced scanners must make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Computers check[b] to find the weapon as usual. </div><div>Game Masters may spend [TH][TH] or [DE] on a combat check to render the weapon inoperable, requiring a major repair before it can be used again. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FIcN4TkIpZPNEqah","name":"Decreases Encumbrance Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Decrease Encumbrance by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCSUB"}},"id":"vdts24mpd6qii0ik"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SCANPROOF"}},"_id":"KUGZ2EGproL992S1"}
{"name":"Modular Backpack Accessory Pouch","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Modular Backpack Accessory Pouch[h3]\n\nThe Mk. IV Modular Backpack increases the user's encumbrance threshold by 3, plus an additional 1 point of encumbrance threshold for each accessory pouch to a maximum of 3.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Enter the Unknown[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Threshold Mod - Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":15,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"nHSKs58L1WeH9hXW","name":"Increases Encumbrance Threshold Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCTADD"}},"id":"g0025ikqbucwkku5"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MODBKACCPOUCH"}},"_id":"KhK5tCmFqtxEwVY0"}
{"name":"Stripped Down","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Stripped Down[h3]\nBy removing redundant components and stripping down the body, it is possible to significantly reduce the weight and profile of a blaster or other weapon. A weapon modified this way is more easily carried and transported and can be better hidden under a coat or among other equipment. THe attachment can be used with any Ranged (Light) or Ranged (Heavy) weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 56 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Encumbrance Mod - Decrease Encumbrance by 1 </div><div>Add [SE] to Perception checks to find the weapon when hidden. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FIcN4TkIpZPNEqah","name":"Decreases Encumbrance Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Decrease Encumbrance by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCSUB"}},"id":"yco8juyyn7bgw9cb"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STRIPDOWN"}},"_id":"L2qFOesqvte8JlcW"}
{"name":"Serrated Edge","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Serrated Edge[h3]\n\nThe simplicity of this modification belies its viciousness. Adding a serrated edge to a weapon is something almost anyone can do, and giving a bladed weapon tearing edges ensures it does terrible damage to flesh and bone. This modification may be applied to melee weapons that use a cutting edge. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Vicious Quality - When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":50,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SE"}},"_id":"L3Ojl3jRL1hNAVPX"}
{"name":"Comms Unit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Comms Unit[h3]\n This pack functions as a comms hub,\nrouting Alliance communications up to long range\non the planetary scale. Its encryption adds [SE][SE] to\nchecks made to unscramble the signal.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>May route communications up to long range on the planetary scale. </div><div>Adds [SE][SE] to checks made to unscramble the unit's signal. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MILMODBACKCOM"}},"_id":"LEiS0Kq23JhnyihT"}
{"name":"Combat Plating","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Combat Plating[h3]\nCombat plating offers perhaps the best protection a hull can provide, but reduces the steering to glacial levels of responsiveness.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 83 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 3</div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 Count 3</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FoiIrJw9E5Rj1mtN","name":"Increase Armor Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Armor value by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ARMORADD"}},"id":"mothz2ljdl4lwl52"},{"_id":"44ELNMkPjfPot5Nm","name":"Add to Massive Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Add to Massive Setting","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MASSIVEADD"}},"id":"jp4e5k3vi1axhjqx"},{"_id":"qzOIl6xENHjd36pO","name":"Increase Hull Trauma by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Hull Trauma by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HULLADDSIL"}},"id":"bb4d0ionmlbdenud"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRAFTHULLCOMBATPLATE"}},"_id":"LIBat5ULoJm7vyiK"}
{"name":"Maneuvering Thrusters","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Maneuvering Thrusters[h3]\n\nSmall thrusters attached to the exterior chassis of a vehicle increase how responsive it is during flight. The application of these varies considerably, from the crude strapping of rocket or jet packs to the outside of a vehicle to the careful addition of a completely separate fuel line to grant extended use. Maneuvering thrusters may only be attached to vehicles of silhouette 2 or lower. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Arakyd Aerodrive Thruster Augmentation System, SoroSuub CornerTech Maneuvering Thruster.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Jewel of Yavin[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Handling Mod - Increases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MANTHRUST"}},"_id":"LKfHCVRfcVZRe06F"}
{"name":"Set Trigger","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Set Trigger[h3]\n\nCommonly known as a \"hair-trigger,\" this weapon retooling allows a blaster or slugthrower to fire with barely a touch of the trigger. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Light) or Ranged (Heavy) weapon. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Custom variants.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Automatic [SU][TH] to the first combat check made with this weapon each encounter. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":450,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SETTRIGGER"}},"_id":"LZZMvSvWNh8WTKaB"}
{"name":"Seeker Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Seeker Crystal[h3]\nNo one seems to know where these crystals come from or how they make their way into the hands of their users. Rumors persist of markets so dark that none but a handful of beings know about them. Other rumors suggest that these crystals have an entirely different purpose and only incidentally happen to function as lightsaber crystals with unusual properties. Still others say they come from the deepest edges of the galaxy, from stars yet unknown. Whatever the case may be, those few that are known to exist have served their users well, allowing them to avoid ambush and surprise attack. Users of these crystals seem to instinctively know when they are being secretly observed or when their charges are in danger from hidden assassins. When ignited, blades produced by these crystals glow a soft pink color and connect users to the Force in such a way that they are able to detect those who hide nearby. While it is not a compass pointing the way to hidden beings, a wielder will know without a doubt that a concealed foe is near. A seeker crystal is a lightsaber crystal.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 53 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Force-sensitive wielders my add [AD][AD] to Perception or Vigilance checks to detect a hidden being within short range. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":16000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"5bvxdu38qpdoowle"},null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SEEKERCRYS"}},"_id":"MG2FpLActdcnf3c1"}
{"name":"Multi-Optic Sight","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Multi-Optic Sight[h3]\n\nA complex and sophisticated piece of equipment, the multi-optic sight is a wonder of modem sensor technology. Marketed to the discriminating professional soldier, each consists of a bulky on-weapon optic equipped with numerous sensors including low-light, thermal, ultrasound, millimeter wave emitters, video capture, and common optical enhancements. The optic is connected to a pair of goggles worn by the user by a reinforced fiber optic cable that transmits the vision enhancements directly to the user in real time. This allows the user to see around corners and over obstacles. This attachment can be fit to any ranged weapon. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Galactic Arms Model 44 Combat Optical Enhancer, SoroSuub XAD Omnisight, Merr-Sonn 480.z1 \"Beholder\" Multi-Optic Sight.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Removes up to [SETBACK][SETBACK]  on any checks\n          to use this weapon due to smoke, darkness, or other\n          environmental conditions that obstruct vision. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MOS"}},"_id":"MN3BqARhFO4dTw4t"}
{"name":"Shield Discharge Pack","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shield Discharge Pack[h3]\n[P]Despite being nearly as ancient as warfare, shields continue to be popular weapons, serving as trusted defenders of warriors on low-tech planets and protecting life and limb of security forces in densely populated areas. While shields are useful weapons already, adding discharge packs to them can allow the wielder to deliver a debilitating shock when deflecting a hit. Further, just the sight of a crackling arc of energy wreathing a shield can disturb many would-be attackers, making their strikes far more timid - and far less lethal - than they would have been otherwise. This attachment can only be applied to a shield or buckler.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When wielder suffers hit from Melee, Brawl, or Lightsaber combat check, may spend [TH][TH] or [DE] to cause attacker to suffer 3 strain, ignoring soak. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"pi7ls0pd7tenbsp7"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SHDISCH"}},"_id":"MVDCrMpD6lOBlGJb"}
{"name":"Superior Weapon Customization","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Superior Weapon Customization[h3]\n\nEven the simplest weapon can benefit from a craftsman's touch. A skilled weaponsmith can tweak a weapon to its owner's exacting specifications, turning a blunt instrument into a honed and deadly weapon of war. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Superior Quality - A Superior item is a sterling example of its kind, representing masterful craftsmanship. A Superior weapon generates automatic [AD] on all checks related to its use, and has its base damage increased by one. Superior armor has its encumbrance reduced by one and its soak value increased by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SWC"}},"_id":"Mutmu25MRvSaDdTX"}
{"name":"Weighted Head","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Weighted Head[h3]\n\nWeapons designed to bludgeon foes to unconsciousness or death often benefit from extra weight added to the striking surface. This can be accomplished through using heavier materials in the construction, or just by adding metal bands or studs to the business end. Reinforced \"knuckles\" can be added to some brawling weapons for similar effect. This attachment can only be added to bludgeoning Melee or Brawl weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"a84tr2jupqn3ike3"},{"_id":"QQf8B9koRsupvLFr","name":"Concussive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"The weapon’s attack can leave the target shell­-shocked from mighty blows or punishing shockwaves, unable to perform any but the most basic actions. The target is staggered (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Concussive rating. A staggered target cannot perform actions.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONCUSSIVE"}},"id":"qmukk8i02khpd8xx"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WEIGHTHEAD"}},"_id":"MyqFFLbBwiPoaMa5"}
{"name":"Spread Barrel","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Spread Barrel[h3]\n\nCommonly applied to blaster rifles and carbines, BlasTech's \"Scattergun\" Spread Barrel is a common modification among spacers and fringers. Designed with close-quarters combat in mind, this attachment replaces a blaster's stock barrel with one shorter, bulkier, broader, and equipped with a built-in flash hider. Using a stepped array of prismatic crystals located at the end of the barrel as well as a reconfigured galven pattern, this barrel splits the blaster's beam into a number of smaller beams that exit the barrel in a spray pattern. Used in a tightly packed space, these beams can strike multiple targets with one pull of the trigger. The trade-off for this, however, is a reduction in the weapon's range. This attachment can only be applied to blaster rifles and blaster carbines. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech 8405 \"Scattergun\" Spread Barrel, SoroSuub 800 \"Blunderbuss\" barrel, Arakyd Model 70 \"Chain Lightning\" Spread Barrel.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduced Range Mod - Decreases weapon's range by one Range Band </div><div>Blast Quality - The weapon has a large spread, an explosive blast, or similar area of effect, like the detonation of a grenade or a warhead fired from a missile launcher. If the attack is successful and Blast activates, each character (friend or foe) Engaged with the original target suffers wounds equal to the weapon’s Blast rating (plus an additional wound per Success as usual).\n\n[P]In a relatively small and enclosed area, the Game Master might decide that everyone in the room suffers damage.\n\n[P]If the Blast quality doesn’t activate, the ordnance still detonates, but bad luck or poor aim on the part of the firer (or quick reactions on the part of the victims) means the explosion may not catch anyone else in its radius. However, the user may also trigger Blast if the attack misses, by spending [AD][AD][AD]. In this case, the original target and every target engaged with the original target suffers damage equal to the Blast rating of the weapon. Count 4</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1725,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"tgAhC4L1QPCVAswN","name":"Blast Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"The weapon has a large spread, an explosive blast, or similar area of effect, like the detonation of a grenade or a warhead fired from a missile launcher. If the attack is successful and Blast activates, each character (friend or foe) Engaged with the original target suffers wounds equal to the weapon’s Blast rating (plus an additional wound per Success as usual).\n\n[P]In a relatively small and enclosed area, the Game Master might decide that everyone in the room suffers damage.\n\n[P]If the Blast quality doesn’t activate, the ordnance still detonates, but bad luck or poor aim on the part of the firer (or quick reactions on the part of the victims) means the explosion may not catch anyone else in its radius. However, the user may also trigger Blast if the attack misses, by spending [AD][AD][AD]. In this case, the original target and every target engaged with the original target suffers damage equal to the Blast rating of the weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BLAST"}},"id":"ba36i6haoohoi7sk"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SB"}},"_id":"N71nLCc2v91wHRWP"}
{"name":"Reflec Shadowskin","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reflec Shadowskin[h3]\n[P]An advanced, light-absorbing polymer that can be applied to armor, reflec shadowskin coating can enhance the stealth abilities of its wearer - anyone wearing armor covered in this substance can easily blend into the shadows. While this coating does not make the wearer invisible, it does mean that observers who only catch a glimpse are far less likely to register what they saw or believe it to be anything more than a trick of the light. This attachment can only be applied to armor with a soak of 2 or lower.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]","attributes":{"Stealth":{"mod":"Stealth","modtype":"Skill Add Advantage","value":1}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REFSHAD"}},"_id":"NL0n7F70uG7k9DjZ"}
{"name":"Mk. III Modular Backpack Accessory Pouch","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Mk. III Modular Backpack Accessory Pouch[h3]\nCreshaldyne Industries' Mk. III Modular Backpack is a civilian version of its popular Mk. IV military reconnaissance pack. Like the Mk. IV, the Mk. III MB is a large, sturdy, internally supported backpack constructed of hard-wearing, weatherproof textiles. It has a single large interior space and two smaller external pockets that are sealed against the environment with a silent, tear away textile sealing system.. The Mk. III is also equipped with a system of hooks and fasteners that allows up to six smaller pouches to be attached to better tailor the backpack to the wearer's needs.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 46 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Threshold Mod - Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":15,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"nHSKs58L1WeH9hXW","name":"Increases Encumbrance Threshold Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCTADD"}},"id":"njwtrvg6xkph54wq"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MODBKACCPOUCH3"}},"_id":"NM7wzftbYxflN4YA"}
{"name":"Component Alteration (Weapon)","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Component Alteration (Weapon)[h3]\nA more drastic, but more effective, option is to alter a weapon or other device so that it can be broken down into several smaller parts that can be reassembled later. This method is typically used when a Rebel needs to get a larger item into a secure location or to avoid scanning devices that are likely to detect standard weapons regardless of any concealment alterations. This is called a component alteration.\n[P]Characters wishing to break a weapon or other item down into several parts in this fashion need to spend time dismantling the device into smaller components. This requires a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] and takes a number of hours equal to the item's encumbrance, or a minimum of one hour. If the check is successful, the device is broken down into a number of components equal to its encumbrance plus 1. So, a blaster pistol is broken down into two components, while a blaster rifle is broken down into five.\n[P]Note that this differs from the more advanced componentization weapon attachment, which requires no check for use once it is installed and is designed to allow the user to openly carry a weapon, rather than consisting of a simple mechanical disassembly. Characters can try, though, to use component alteration to physically disguise these individual parts to look like code cylinders, comlinks, fusion lanterns, and other mundane objects. While this allows a part to take on the rough appearance of the desired object, it does not gain the functionality of that object. This is generally a taxing and tricky process, and so upgrades the difficulty of the Mechanics check once or more as per the GM's discretion.\n[P]Each [SU] or [TR] on the initial Mechanics check lets a character carrying the components from a component alteration add [BO] to [B]opposed Stealth vs. Perception checks[b] when an observer attempts to notice the true nature of the disassembled device. If the component alteration was designed to make the items appear mundane, he gains [BO][BO] instead.\n[P]Assembling a weapon or other item with a component alteration requires two maneuvers or two minutes of narrative time per component, and the character must make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. All components must be present to make the check. Failure means the components are damaged and the device requires a major repair to be properly reassembled again and returned to function. \n[P]Component alterations have a strong impact on a item's reliability, as most weapons or other complex devices simply aren't meant to be broken down into smaller pieces and reassembled. The GM may spend [TH][TH][TH] as [DE] when a character makes a skill check while using an item with this alteration. \n[P]A character can only attempt a component alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 80 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Characters wishing to break a weapon or other item down into several parts in this fashion need to spend time dismantling the device into smaller components. This requires a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] and takes a number of hours equal to the item's encumbrance, or a minimum of one hour. If the check is successful, the device is broken down into a number of components equal to its encumbrance plus 1. </div><div>Characters can try to use component alteration to physically disguise these individual parts to look like code cylinders, comlinks, fusion lanterns, and other mundane objects. While this allows a part to take on the rough appearance of the desired object, it does not gain the functionality of that object. This is generally a taxing and tricky process, and so upgrades the difficulty of the Mechanics check once or more as per the GM's discretion. </div><div>Each [SU] or [TR] on the initial Mechanics check lets a character carrying the components from a component alteration add [BO] to [B]opposed Stealth vs. Perception checks[b] when an observer attempts to notice the true nature of the disassembled device. If the component alteration was designed to make the items appear mundane, he gains [BO][BO] instead. </div><div>Assembling a weapon or other item with a component alteration requires two maneuvers or two minutes of narrative time per component, and the character must make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. All components must be present to make the check. Failure means the components are damaged and the device requires a major repair to be properly reassembled again and returned to function. </div><div>The GM may spend [TH][TH][TH] as [DE] when a character makes a skill check while using an item with this alteration. </div><div>A character can only attempt a component alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"COMPALTERWEAPON"}},"_id":"NkwkpCjVCDtWYyC7"}
{"name":"Balanced Barrel","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Balanced Barrel[h3]\nAdding a functional barrel to a rivet gun can give it dramatically more range and accuracy as a shooting weapon. Of course, such an addition also makes it obvious that the device is liable to be fired at range, as few Technicians can make a coherent case that they legitimately need to be able to bolt hull plates onto a ship with pinpoint accuracy at a distance of several meters.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 46 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Range Mod - Increases weapon's range by one Range Band </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":150,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RIVETGUNBALBAR"}},"_id":"NnndM4IbjVXt0Zgy"}
{"name":"Nishalorite Stone","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Nishalorite Stone[h3]\nNishalorite stones are found on worlds with particularly strong magnetic fields. Usually dark gray or blue-black in color, and possessing powerful magnetic properties, these stones are often used in electronics and magnetic navigation equipment. once properly cleaned and refined, they also make for excellent lightsaber crystals, as discovered generations ago by a wandering Jedi Seeker.\n[P]While installed in a lightsaber, this stone creates a dense crackling blade with a subdued color that intensifies in the direction of a planet's magnetic north. It can detect natural and artificially generated magnetic fields such as those produced by generators of powerful electronic systems.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 3</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Add automatic [AD] to checks made to location position, navigate terrain, or find power sources or active technology. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":12500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"v5siazeywdo19kf1"},{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"bw4canoymvc5qo56"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"NISHSTONE"}},"_id":"Nsx2Tcbw9d03O5GD"}
{"name":"(AD-1S) Hyperdrive Class 4 Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hyperdrive Class 4 Module for AD-1S[h3]\nInstalling a hyperdrive, even a relatively low-grade one, in an AD-IS takes up a good deal of space inside of the craft, but also allows\nit to operate independently. For many mercenaries, bounty hunters, and other frequent travelers, such an upgrade is well worth the cost.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Class 4 Hyperdrive Mod - Add Class 4 Hyperdrive </div><div>Add astromech droid socket. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"0HibaLcBPREmA3Wv","name":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of .5 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVESUB5"}},"id":"ik5xaatniephfjcr"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD1SHYPER4"}},"_id":"ODzWhwRRUfjJDonO"}
{"name":"Balanced Hilt","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Balanced Hilt[h3]\n\nBalance is key in a well-constructed melee weapon. Professional weaponsmiths can use modem ultra-light materials to create a sword or axe that is not only lighter, but also more accurate in the hands of a skilled warrior. This attachment can be used with any melee weapon. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Accurate Quality - Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FIcN4TkIpZPNEqah","name":"Decreases Encumbrance Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Decrease Encumbrance by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCSUB"}},"id":"it9jz6ggyrkvo4bu"},{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"bn0kbv06jj8ve4dh"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BALHILT"}},"_id":"OKaMFQlEBf46GqUC"}
{"name":"Armored Computer Core","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Armored Computer Core[h3]\nIt's a tragic fact that all too often, the brave members of the Alliance fail to return from a mission. Nevertheless, even a failed mission can provide useful data for the cause and prevent such deaths in the future. In such cases, an armored computer core provides an opportunity for the Rebellion to recover a record of the mission from even the most devastated wrecks. Layers of laminamium plating, redundant data backups, and sometimes even an ejection failsafe ensure the survival of a computer core storing astrogation data, a record of ship activity, and-assuming mission leaders fulfill their duty-a log of the mission. Should the worst come to pass, the armored computer core can survive the ship's complete destruction, and is practically indistinguishable from the debris.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Incorporates a computer core that records flight and system data and backs up any logs or records entered into the ship's computer. </div><div>Computer core remains intact even if the ship suffers a \"Vaporized\" Critical Hit. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ARMCOMCORE"}},"_id":"ONIn47s0yXWP0Nlp"}
{"name":"Physical Countermeasures","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Physical Countermeasures[h3]\n\nLike electronic countermeasures, physical counter-measures are designed to fool scanners and make a ship or vehicle harder to hit. Whereas electronic countermeasures affect an opposing ship or vehicle's sensors, physical countermeasures are specifically designed to help a ship or vehicle evade incoming missiles or torpedoes. Countermeasures come in three basic varieties—chaff, flares, and anti-warhead missile pods. Chaff is a collection of small, highly reflective alloy streamers packed into a tube with a small explosive charge. When detonated, the chaff tube creates a cloud of glittering shrapnel that clouds detection systems and confuses most basic missile guidance systems. Flares are deployed in groups from special launchers, and consist of small incendiary devices that mimic the heat produced by a ship or vehicle's engines, fooling incoming missiles into following the super-hot flare instead of the vehicle. Anti-warhead missile pods are similar to flares, but they fire a cluster of small, low-yield missiles designed to intercept and destroy incoming ordnance. \n\n[P]While any ship equipped with physical counter-measures carries enough to get them through most encounters, engaging in a long, drawn-out fight can quickly deplete a launcher's store of countermeasures. Game Masters may spend [AD][AD] or [TR] on Gunnery checks made using missiles, rockets, or torpedoes targeting the starship to cause a countermeasure launcher to run out of its load of flares, chaff, or anti-warhead missiles, effectively disabling it until the end of the encounter. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Loronar Defense Industries A4M \"Pepperbox\" anti-warhead micro-missile pack, Oriolanis Defense Systems XM-130 chaff dispenser, Conner Ship Systems MJU-9G \"Phoenix\" Flare Dispenser.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Stay on Target[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds [SETBACK] to all Gunnery checks made using missiles, rockets, or torpedoes targeting the starship. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PHYSCOUNT"}},"_id":"OTvnpPf1XKPuuFEo"}
{"name":"Secondary Ion Blaster","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Secondary Ion Blaster[h3]\nA secondary ion blaster provides an extra level of offense for those expecting run-ins with droids. Many Technicians prefer to take enemy droids intact, the better to \"recruit\" them or even scavenge for parts later. An ion blaster mounted alongside another weapon provides just that option. This attachment can be used with any Ranged (Heavy) weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] SoroSuub Droid Defender, BlasTech Model 9 Under-Barrel Ion Blaster[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 56 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds an ion blaster to the weapon. </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":400,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"4xwaf2pzu3ky4s2b"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"IONBLAST"}},"_id":"Of146A394nFIjbfI"}
{"name":"(AD-15) Hyperdrive Class 8 Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hyperdrive Class 8 Module for AD-15[h3]\nInstalling a hyperdrive, even a relatively low-grade one, in an AD-15 takes up a good deal of space inside of the craft, but also allows it to operate independently. For many mercenaries, bounty hunters and other frequent travelers, such an upgrade is well worth the cost.\n[P][H4]<font size=1>Please see page 63 of the Special Modifications Sourcebook for details.</font>[h4][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Class 8 Hyperdrive Mod - Add Class 8 Hyperdrive </div><div>Add astromech droid socket. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"0HibaLcBPREmA3Wv","name":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of .5 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVESUB5"}},"id":"ppyp1mqsxyoo8b1t"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD15HYPER"}},"_id":"OvTCHm5tBIZYTObM"}
{"name":"Briefing Auditorium","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Briefing Auditorium[h3]\nMost dedicated warships, especially those in service\nwith the Imperial Navy, have special compartments set\naside for the briefing and debriefing of fighter, gunboat,\nand shuttle pilots, ground vehicle drivers, and ground\ncombat forces. Before and after missions, pilots, soldiers,\nand support staff gather in these large, well-lit\ncompartments to be briefed on their missions by a\nsenior officer, or to report on their missions and learn\nhow their success or failure affected the larger strategic\nsituation. Typically located close to hangars, barracks,\nor berth decks, a standard briefing auditorium features\nplenty of seating, access to power and shipboard networks\nfor datapads, a lectern or speaking platform, and\naudio/video/holo equipment. These rooms and equipment\nallow senior officers to issue orders en masse and\nto make sure that all of their subordinates are properly\nprepared for the mission at hand.\n[P]While the Alliance to Restore the Republic fields some\ndedicated warships, either decommissioned vessels\nfrom the Clone Wars or stolen Imperial Navy vessels,\nmost Alliance ships began life as civilian vessels and\nwere militarized in an ad hoc fashion to fit the needs\nof specific Rebel cells or fleets. Ships of silhouette 5 or\nlarger can be fitted with a briefing auditorium, giving\nCommanders a venue in which to issue orders personally\nand en masse to the troops and pilots under their\ncommand.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Lead by Example[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Characters briefed in this auditorium prior to a mission remove [SE] due to known mission conditions from skill checks for the duration of the mission. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BRAUD"}},"_id":"P2qQleYSIOmtq0fw"}
{"name":"Marked-Target Firing Lock","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Marked-Target Firing Lock[h3]\nIn the chaos of a firefight, shots can go astray, damaging property or bystanders. While some hunters do not care about the carnage they cause, this kind of haphazard damage is a liability, courting attention from the law or revenge from those who suffer in the crossfire. To mitigate this risk, some bounty hunters invest in firing locks on their blasters, allowing them to designate specific targets for the weapons. Once the systems' sensors have recognized a target, the weapons refuse to fire without a clear shot, minimizing the chance of collateral damage. This attachment can be installed on any ranged weapon that does not posses the Blast or Auto-fire quality.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech \"Surefire\" Safety Sensor, Cadregg Armory Model-87 Weapon Sensor.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Cancel Threat from Check Mod - Cancel One [THREAT] from Check </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":900,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8Qv5y0BAOQvWC1rV","name":"Cancel Threat from Check Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Cancel One [THREAT] from Check","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"THRCANCEL"}},"id":"7p6yrhqdmahyjdhq"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MKTARGLOCK"}},"_id":"PLCKKWm0o1BHPntg"}
{"name":"Solari Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Solari Crystal[h3]\nAs rare as this type of kyber crystal is, some do find their way into the hands of Force sensitives highly attuned to the light side of the Force. Tales of solari kyber crystals come from the ancient past, and they have long been thought to be mere myths. However, they do exist, and it is a lucky Force user who can find one and make use of it. Or perhaps it is the will of the Force that those most in tune with the light side should happen upon them. They are not put to use lightly, though, for they demand much of their wielder. In exchange, they provide unparalleled protection against incoming fire. A solari crystal causes a lightsaber's blade to widen, thereby making much more effective at deflecting blaster bolts. A solari crystal is a lightsaber crystal.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 53 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Defensive Quality - Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating. </div><div>Reduce strain from Reflect incidental by 1. </div><div>Crystal ceases to function if wielder's Morality is reduced below 50. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":16000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"3qx8lu5gu4therlt"},{"_id":"HL9ao4tKeqg0ExvA","name":"Defensive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFENSIVE"}},"id":"3dyts0hxphx91fbi"},null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SOLARICRYS"}},"_id":"PNjNjwdU8OkwKyEC"}
{"name":"Etaan Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Etaan Crystal[h3]\nThese unusual kyber crystals from in the deep caverns of the Mid Rim world of Etai. Given that the crystals rarely form fewer than five hundred meters below the surface and usually at over twice the depth, the formation can be extremely difficult to locate. However, the raw crystals echo any nearby sound with a humming resonance, guiding searchers who draw near.\n[P]Harvested etaan crystals retain this resonant property causing the activated blades of lightsabers using them to thrum in harmony with the motion of the blade, and to chime at nearby sounds. The blades respond especially spectacularly to a clash with another lightsaber or blaster bolt, emitting a near-deafening crack and a bright flare of energies. A clash of blades involving etaan crystals usually results in the lightsabers being forced apart, but reflected blasted bolts draw in the resonant energies from the reaction and intensify on their new trajectory.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>If wielder uses the Improved Reflect talent to inflict an automatic hit, increase damage by 2. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":12000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"7z8yff26cmcknblz"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"wi6ykcjax5e689mp"},{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X