{"name":"Security Measures","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Security Measures[h3]\nThere are few things to befall a ship owner more dreaded than to have a craft disappear from an unsecured landing pad. Even aside from the threat of theft, there are many reasons why a crew might want to keep uninvited guests off their ship while it's unattended - especially for any crew engaged in less-than-legal pursuits. Upgraded mag-locks, decoy control panels, reinforced hatches and enhanced security protocols can ensure that a ship goes undisturbed while at port. This attachment can be applied to any vehicle or starship.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Corellian Engineering Corporation SecurePro, Kuat Drive Yards LockDown Plus[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 67 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Upgrade the difficulty Computers and Skulduggery checks made to gain unauthorized access to the ship twice. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SECMEAS"}},"_id":"Q3TkL7scB7FG3Sop"}
{"name":"Portable Plasma Shield","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Portable Plasma Shield[h3]\nArmor and weapon designs oppose one another in a cycle of endless escalation. Not surprisingly, many warriors seek out means to enhance their defenses in hopes that it will leave them free to make additional attacks. A small defensive shield can provide a substantial upgrade. energy Shields take this a step further, offering a near-inpenetrable defense while requiring much less weight and bulk than a more traditional shield.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Collapse of the Republic[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Defensive Quality - Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"kHPbGxHGs2JADBrS","name":"Deflection Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"An item with the Deflection quality increases the wearer’s ranged defense equal to its Deflection rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFLECTION"}},"id":"izj93rjzjpbpdic7"},{"_id":"HL9ao4tKeqg0ExvA","name":"Defensive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Defensive weapons are particularly good at fending off incoming melee attacks. A character wielding a weapon with the Defensive quality increases his melee defense by the weapon’s Defensive rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFENSIVE"}},"id":"9be7ce2ofhol7y15"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PORTPLASHLD"}},"_id":"QxlLHheEWOLjgc1g"}
{"name":"Energy Overclock Setting","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Energy Overclock Setting[h3]\n[P]As deadly and dangerous as they are, vibroweapons can be even deadlier with the inclusion of an overclock setting. By replacing several internal components with precision analogs, a qualified technician can exponentially increase the speed and frequency of a vibroblade's blade action. The result is a vibroweapon that can be charged for amplified cutting power, but at the expense of causing unpredictable power fluctuations. This attachment can be applied to any vibroweaponand any other powered Melee or Brawl weapon.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Once per turn, spend a maneuver to add Vicious +3 to weapon until end of round.  [TH][TH][TH] or [DE] causes weapon to cease functioning until end of encounter. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"EOVERSET"}},"_id":"R5zzGGIuXKww9LDo"}
{"name":"Single Ion Coil","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Single Ion Coil[h3]\nPerhaps the most basic of sublight drives, these engines are still attractive due to their price.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 81 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod - Increases System Strain by Silhouette Count 3</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"TfqDzg8fQd6VBG9V","name":"Increase Speed Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Speed by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPEEDADD"}},"id":"d9yffw82gn8tsug3"},{"_id":"WzEhZZQs7ZiJaqsh","name":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADDSIL"}},"id":"2npb7sjfjziwwu3q"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRAFTENGINESINGION"}},"_id":"RFsIyf3IMVLO0e6j"}
{"name":"Podracer Control Cables","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Podracer Control Cables[h3]\nIf Podracing evolved from ancient beast-drawn chariot and cart racing, as many historians suppose, then control cables are analogous to a set of reins. These long, flexible durasteel cables tether a Podracer's powerful engines to its cockpit. Along with keeping the engines and the cockpit connected, they also house the wiring that connects the controls to the engines. Steelton produces most Podracer control cables, but smaller companies have cropped up lately in an attempt to take away some of its market share.\n[P]Nearly all Podracers use control cables, only a few small-production outliers, such as FG 8T8-T and a handful of one-offs and prototypes, mount the engines directly to the cockpit via spars. Control cables are the most fragile part of a Podracer, as even the stoutest set can be snapped or sliced through. A Podracer who loses her control cables through accident or sabotage loses control over her vehicle and must either eject or ride the cockpit to a stop and hope she survives.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Steelton Perfect-Series control cables, Moriales Systems SC-4.x control tether.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - Endless Vigil[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PODCONTCAB"}},"_id":"Rhw7tNEgcGzHEZO5"}
{"name":"\"Final Word\" Secondary Missile System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]\"Final Word\" Secondary Missile System[h3]\n\nThis uncommon attachment provides the user with the option for a single explosive attack, useful either as a last resort or as an opening salvo. The attachment holds a single rocket. This attachment can be used with any rifle that uses the Ranged (Heavy) skill.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Enables weapon to fire rockets, using missile's profile. </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. Count 3</div><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 Count 3</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MISSILESYS"}},"_id":"RqBcocOaXlQlEicW"}
{"name":"Marksman Barrel","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Marksman Barrel[h3]\n\nMerr-Sonn's KX765 Marksman Barrel was designed to meet the needs of the finger for whom long-range accuracy is a necessity. Popular among bounty hunters and assassins, this barrel is nearly two meters long and made of lightweight materials. It features upgraded static pulse adapters as well as a denser galven circuitry pattern that not only increases the weapon's range, but also its accuracy. The trade-off for this increased range and accuracy is a weapon that's slightly awkward to use and nearly impossible to conceal due to the length of the barrel. This modification may only be applied to blaster rifles. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Merr-Sonn KX756 Marksman Barrel, SoroSuub WQ80 \"Long-shot\" Barrel, Arakyd 3300 Hawkeye Sharpshooter's Barrel.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Range Mod - Increases weapon's range by one Range Band </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"stvch78kffy0ytu6"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MB"}},"_id":"S2qfQaNt3qWR7u9K"}
{"name":"Holonet Pirate Array","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Holonet Pirate Array[h3]\n\nLife in the galaxy has arisen in all manner of biomes, from the deep seas of Mon Cala to the Ithorian jungles, and every possible climate in between. Most starship life-support systems create an environment in the median range, neither too hot nor too cold, neither too humid nor too dry. When members of a particular species need unique accommodations, they must turn to their own shipwrights, or modify acquired ships appropriately. Diplomats often take the additional step of adapting their ships to be capable of replicating a wide range of environments, the better to make passengers and guests feel at home.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Desperate Allies[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Transmissions sent with this attachment can reach any facility that has access to interstellar communications.  Transmissions can be intercepted with a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Computers check[b], provided someone is aware of the transmission. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":25000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HNPA"}},"_id":"SCSpNseGaY8y4Iyv"}
{"name":"MB-7 \"Ranger\" Range Finder","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]MB-7 \"Ranger\" Range Finder[h3]\n\nA system incorporating a simple computer and visual sensors, a range finder calculates the distance to any spot in the user's field of vision, feeding him precise information to a visor HUD. With this information, the wearer can push his weapon to its limits, while knowing when to hold his fire on an impossible shot. The most sophisticated systems interface directly with the user's weapon for increased effect.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RANGEFIND"}},"_id":"SHpHpcmraLwBbEFj"}
{"name":"Hyperdrive Generator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hyperdrive Generator[h3]\n\nUpgraded hyperdrive generators increase a vessel's speed through hyperspace, allowing it to complete journeys in a fraction of the time. May be installed on any ship with hyperdrive. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Isu-Sim SSPO5 Hyperdrive Generator, SFS S/ig-30 Hyperdrive System, KDY JumpStar Hyperdrive Generator.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of 1 Mod - Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":6400,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"0HibaLcBPREmA3Wv","name":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of .5 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVESUB5"}},"id":"mxt6wr3ybpb6nipt"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVE"}},"_id":"SRp3CAquqMMZew19"}
{"name":"Gyrostabilizer","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Gyrostabilizer[h3]\nA gyrostabilizer, or repulsorlift harness, artificially reduces the weight of  the weapon, allowing a user to heft and aim a heavy weapon with decreased difficulty. With such a modification, a single combatant can operate a weapon that normally requires a team of two. These sophisticated devices are comparatively expensive and rare, and thus are seldom seen outside of elite forces. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Heavy) or Gunnery Weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] TaggeCo Type 2 Repulsorlift Harness, BlasTech Mk. IV Gyrostabilization Unit[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Special Modifications[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GYROSTAB"}},"_id":"STR4EeHGXpvFiX91"}
{"name":"Mono-Molecular Edge","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Mono-Molecular Edge[h3]\n\nEven vibroweapons can benefit from an edge sharpened to molecular thickness and toughened through laser-forging techniques. This modification may be applied to melee weapons that use a cutting edge. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None listed.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decrease Critical Mod - Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"od174p30zeqrba6e"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MME"}},"_id":"ShBdDrMihLZg2mXM"}
{"name":"Expanded-Capacity Holds","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Expanded-Capacity Holds[h3]\nUsed for freighters, this hull allows for additional cargo space and the promise of paying passengers.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 83 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FoiIrJw9E5Rj1mtN","name":"Increase Armor Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Armor value by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ARMORADD"}},"id":"3eia7i11cb8ysr5i"},{"_id":"P75gU7FhziudROeP","name":"Increases Encumbrance Capacity by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Encumbrance Capacity by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":10},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCCADDSIL"}},"id":"5x5txt3olvpz5hbn"},{"_id":"lY51wtno6V2QsEZM","name":"Increase Passenger Capacity by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Passenger Capacity by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":8},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PASSADDSIL"}},"id":"q79vbf1rccsoz1fs"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRAFTHULLEXPCAP"}},"_id":"SmJmUndBtOYwtl77"}
{"name":"Weapon Signature Reduction","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Weapon Signature Reduction[h3]\n[P]Both the Empire and the galactic security industry use weapon scanners that are capable of detecting a wide variety of weapon components. Even when broken down into several pieces, blasters and other ranged weapons are still liable to be detected, due to the specific technologies and substances that allow them to function as lethal weapons.\n[P]In order to skirt such inspection and ensure that hidden weapons remain obscured from prying eyes, covert agents have devised modifications that mask or otherwise diminish such signatures in a weapon’s components. Though physical searches still pose some risk of discovery, weapon signature reduction guarantees that scanning equipment used to detect weapons is rendered less effective. Unfortunately, weapon signature reduction is only effective on weapons with an encumbrance rating of 5 or less.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Strongholds of Resistance[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase the difficulty checks using scanners to search for this weapon by 2.  Add [SE] to all Mechanics checks to perform maintenance on this weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SIGRED"}},"_id":"T3FNdcAbkdKrxHDM"}
{"name":"High-Output Repulsor Coils","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]High-Output Repulsor Coils[h3]\nBasic Podracer cockpits come equipped with low-output repulsor coils of the kind typically found on repulsorsleds and speeder trucks. Considered a secondary system at best, and really only equipped to keep the Podracer at altitude when standing still or at low speeds, a racer's repulsor coils are rarely given a second thought. Savvy racers, or veterans with years of racing and building experience under their belts, know that a good repulsorlift engine can often mean the difference between first and last place, or finishing or crashing. Upgraded repulsor coils increase a Podracer's maximum altitude, allowing it to clear obstacles more easily and even hop over lower flying opponents.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Incom TX-2, Bespin Motors Ponrez/Arc Repulsorlift, Karydee KD49 Drive Unit.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Altitude by 50 Mod - Increases Altitude by 50 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"DJTSlK7SFJP5XGAF","name":"Increase Altitude by 50 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Altitude by 50","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ADDALT50"}},"id":"tx1xnssgi83lpk8u"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PODCOILS"}},"_id":"TXzLIb71kXHFCgP9"}
{"name":"Environmental Simulators","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Environmental Simulators[h3]\nLife in the galaxy has arisen in all manner of biomes,\nfrom the deep seas of Mon Cala to the Ithorian jungles, and every possible climate in between. Most\nstarship life-support systems create an environment\nin the median range, neither too hot nor too cold, neither too humid nor too dry. When members of\na particular species need unique accommodations,\nthey must turn to their own shipwrights, or modify\nacquired ships appropriately. Diplomats often take\nthe additional step of adapting their ships to be capable of replicating a wide range of environments, the\nbetter to make passengers and guests feel at home.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Desperate Allies[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Can replicate up to three different planetary environments, one at a time.  When making Charm or Negotiation checks against members of species native to replicated environment, add an automatic [AD][AD] to pool. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":7500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENVSIM"}},"_id":"Tcp9QEv60pW8XzGB"}
{"name":"Superior Hilt Personalization","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Superior Hilt Personalization[h3]\n\nWhile most lightsabers are austere and utilitarian, some Jedi have been known to personalize their weapons to better suit their tastes and styles. Numerous cosmetic or practical enhancements can be applied to a lightsaber, from rare metals and precious gemstones to customized grips and locking activating switches. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Superior Quality - A Superior item is a sterling example of its kind, representing masterful craftsmanship. A Superior weapon generates automatic [AD] on all checks related to its use, and has its base damage increased by one. Superior armor has its encumbrance reduced by one and its soak value increased by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SUPHILT"}},"_id":"TepLB6r0RT2AObfz"}
{"name":"Foreign Debris Ejector","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Foreign Debris Ejector[h3]\nPodracing attracts a wide range of pilots, from those who delight in testing their skill against fellow speed enthusiasts to those who are only interested in winning, no matter what it takes. For the latter, one method is not to boost their own vehicles performance but to instead hamper their opponents Podracers. Using concealed compartments (known more informally as \"dirty trick kits\"), pilots can release small nails, reactive chemicals or other debris-designed to foul the engines of a training vehicle, slowing it down or even knocking it out of the running. Though illegal, when used out of the sight of officials these compartments can decide the fate of many a race.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various (pilots and their crew typically craft them secretly).[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Ejects debris into the air behind podracer.  Any racer within close range and behind must make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Piloting (Planetary) check[b] to avoid debris.  Failure reduces speed by 1 for 2 rounds, plus 1 round per [TH].  [TH][TH][TH] or [DE] can inflict Critical Hit on target vehicle. </div><div>May only be used once per race. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":900,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"POSFORDEB"}},"_id":"Th9eWqv3o0P0RyWi"}
{"name":"Staged Rocket Booster","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Staged Rocket Booster[h3]\nThe limitations of size mean that most micro-rockets lack the fuel capacity to reach distant targets. However, high-yield fuel cells, advanced filtration systems, or staged boosters added to the rockets can all increase a rocket's effective range substantially. Of course, the term \"effective range\" becomes something of a misnomer with rockets modified in this way, as the additional fuel risks unbalancing the rocket's flight path, and the increased range comes with an increased chance of misjudgment on the part of the user. However, the chance to deliver a hefty payload beyond the reach of equivalent retribution is worth the risk to many. This attachment can be installed on any micro-rocket.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] SoroSuub HV-33 Fuel Filter.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 47 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Range Mod - Increases weapon's range by one Range Band </div><div>Inaccurate Quality - Inaccurate weapons are weapons of a shoddy or inferior construction which means they are less likely to be accurate or precise. Alternatively, the weapon’s nature may inhibit accuracy. Inaccurate weapons add [SE] to the attacker’s dice pool equal to their Inaccurate rating. Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":25,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"fOrUrQzRol74uYVi","name":"Additional Range Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Increases weapon's range by one Range Band","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RANGEADD"}},"id":"di8c4xrk3gnubfrp"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MICROROCKBOOST"}},"_id":"U4PGx1NoJxuLY3Kp"}
{"name":"Heating System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Heating System[h3]\n\nLike thermal shielding, cold shielding is installed in armor to protect the wearer against dangerously low temperatures and frigid environments. Equipped with small, efficient heating elements and double-insulated against the cold, this attachment allows a wearer to survive in places where the ambient temperature can be dozens of degrees below freezing. Perhaps the most famous type of cold shielding is that built into the custom laminate armor worn by the Imperial Army's snowtroopers. This attachment can be installed on any armor that covers the entire body and can be sealed. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Atlas Corp DL87 \"Frostback\" Armor Enhancement, Min-Dal Model 00 Heating System.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduces the difficulty of Resilience checks made\n          to resist the effects extreme cold by one.\n          Removes up to [SETBACK][SETBACK] added to checks\n          due to extreme cold. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HEAT"}},"_id":"U4tyQKtLYuGFtqOm"}
{"name":"Corrupted Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Corrupted Crystal[h3]\nEven the best of the Jedi can fall. The Empire scours the galaxy looking for the Force sensitives to enfold in the dark side. Untutored pupils wander far from the light, lost on dark paths from which they may never return. Many of them have either found or constructed lightsabers of their own with such crystals as they could and, in the course of their fall or their time astray, have committed heinous acts suffused with the dark side of the Force. They bend the kyber crystals in their lightsabers to their will, leading to the bloody red hue or are redeemed, they leave behind a weapon and a crystal strongly associated with the dark side of the Force. These crystals must be purged of their evil to avoid letting them fall into other hands and corrupt them as well. Thus, a Force user may take on the task of reclaiming these crystals. A corrupted crystal is a lightsaber crystal.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Vicious Quality - When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result. Count 2</div><div>When character wielding this lightsaber makes a Force check, add [DA] to the check. </div><div>When wielder's Morality rises to 70 or more, [DA] is no longer added to Force checks, and the crystal loses the Vicious quality. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"iz9ugwyffvs6c43o"},{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRITSUB"}},"id":"h6grsjtqfys0s52s"},{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"s8mqqbykms6wk5di"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CORRUPTCRYS"}},"_id":"U53Mh6CskYGEej1o"}
{"_id":"UQreREDEpPQAnibw","name":"Riding Tack","type":"itemattachment","img":"systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Riding Tack[h3]\nRiding tack is a catchall term for the assorted bits of equipment needed to ride or control a beast. Produced by companies like Piccatech Ltd. and VeTech, tack comes in a variety of styles tailored to the physiology of nearly every known domesicable beast in the galaxy. Riding tack includes a sturdy comfortable saddle designed for a specific beast and riding style, stirrups, headgear (bridle, halter, bit, reins, etc,), and a breastplate. Tack made for working animals replaces the saddle with a heavy duty harness that allows a creature to pull cargo sleds or implements such as plows.\n[P]Tack can only be worn by riding or working animals. Using tack allows a character to ride the beast without suffering the bareback riding penalties detailed on page 73.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 47 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Characters may ride beast without suffering bareback riding penalties. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0,"isrestricted":false},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"all"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RIDINGTACK","loaded":false}}}
{"name":"Overcharged Ion Engines","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Overcharged Ion Engines[h3]\nPeople living on the fringes of galactic society - and those involved in criminal pursuits, in particular - often need to move more quickly when things turn bad. Overcharged ion engines allow a ship to accelerate more quickly, but tend to be damaging to ship systems over time. Many shipwrights view the use of such modifications as mistreatment of their works, but some pilots swear by the edge it gives them. This attachment acan be applied to any starship of silhouette 3 or smaller.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Gallofree Yards Option-3 Acceleration Optimizer, Various Custom Models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 66 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":9500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"OVERCHIONENG"}},"_id":"UZxqx16oPsVcofTx"}
{"name":"Armor Insert","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Armor Insert[h3]\nArmor inserts are thin, flexible, plasteel and ballistic gel plates that can be sewn into clothing to give the wearer concealed armor protection. They can be added to any garment that is suitably large and alter- able, and they can be installed by any skilled tailor for a moderate fee. This attachment can be applied to any armor with a defense no greater than 0 and a soak of 1 or less. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Creshaldyne \"Slimline\" Armor Plates.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 57 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Turns any article of clothing into armored clothing. </div><div>Characters can notice the inclusion of armor inserts in clothing by making an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Perception check[b]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":450,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"7RTxEBs3ctUXrgHl","name":"Increase Soak Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"Increases Soak value by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"armor","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SOAKADD"}},"id":"t6ywk69d7xso12ou"},{"_id":"spBjRtHXxPgDBX1A","name":"Increase Defense Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"Increases Defense value by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"armor","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFADD"}},"id":"9iuekqeqeid0uio4"},null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ARMINS"}},"_id":"Uc7hCa4bXTKH40mE"}
{"name":"Podracer Engine","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Podracer Engine[h3]\nPodracer engines come in three varieties rocket motors, turbine engines, and high-performance ion engines. In the early days of Podracing, engines were salvaged and rebuilt by talented amateurs. Single-stage heavy lift rockets, ion engines from crashed starfighters, air breathing turbojets from performance airspeeders, and even more exotic engine types were hauled out of scrapyards or dug out of old military depots and put to use on the racing circuits. Today most Podracer engines are either hand-built custom jobs built by big racing teams to their own exact specifications or mass produced engines from one of the major manufacturers. No matter their provenance, they are all too big, too fast and too loud for civilized racing, which is what makes them so appealing for Podracers.\n[P]Podracer engines must be installed in matched sets usually in multiples of two. Doing otherwise makes for a poorly balanced, finicky, unreliable Podracer that is  by its mismatched nature, even more dangerous than usual.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] TurboDyne 99-U, Manta RamAir Mk. IV Flat Twin Turbojet, JAK Racing J930 Dash-8, Radon-Ulzer 620C S&K JZ-5 Fusial Thrust Engine, Incom 2a Fission Engine.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - Endless Vigil[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PODENGINE"}},"_id":"UdiGa1KtkygBdU7i"}
{"name":"Cloaked Smuggling Compartments","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Cloaked Smuggling Compartments[h3]\n\nAn improvement on secret compartments used by smugglers throughout the galaxy, cloaked smuggling compartments are even more difficult to discover than more \"standard\" models. Lined with nightshadow, cloaked smuggling compartments can foil all but the most sensitive sensor scans. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Arakyd Industries Nightshadow compartment liners.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment Mod - Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment </div><div>Increases difficulty of checks made to find compartment by 3. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"V4X7JoVYyeHupNuO","name":"Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Convert 25 encumbrance capacity to smuggling compartment","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SMUGENC"}},"id":"gimvp13fqe461g3z"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CLOAKSMUGG"}},"_id":"Uor4EUlfbZwIbJDc"}
{"name":"Dantari Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Dantari Crystal[h3]\n\nAs their name suggests, Dantari crystals are found on the Outer Rim world of Dantooine. Discovered within the eggs of the kinrath—giant, venomous, cave-dwelling arachnids—it is unknown how Dantari crystals come into existence. However, these multihued kyber crystals were once extremely popular among the Jedi. When installed in a lightsaber, a Force-reactive Dantan crystal helps the wielder maintain focus and calm. A Dantari crystal is a lightsaber crystal. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 2</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>When making a Force power check as part of a combat check, may spend [FORCEPOINT] to recover 2 strain. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":