{"name":"Kiirium Coating","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Kiirium Coating[h3]\n      [P] An obsolete shielding material once processed in abundance in the Si'klaata Cluster, kiirium was at one time vital to the manufacture of heavy weapons and starships. While largely supplanted by cheaper, more durable alloys, kiirium has properties that make it useful to armorsmiths, who can apply a coating of kiirium to armored plating as a relatively effective thermal shielding. This attachment can only be applied to armor that has hard or solid parts around which the allow can be coated, such as with laminate armor, heavy battle armor, and similar types of armor at the GM's discretion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>+1 soak vs. blaster and flame attacks </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"KIIRCOAT"}},"_id":"VDQRh6I2EjxrdI1C"}
{"name":"Weapon Harness","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Weapon Harness[h3]\n\nDesigned to allow a single sentient to field even the heaviest man-portable weapons with no support, weapon harnesses are rare among the Outer Rim territories. Worn over the shoulders and belted around the midsection or torso, weapon harnesses consist of a series of load-bearing straps and harnesses connected to a gyro-stabilized, power-assisted boom arm attached to a heavy weapon. Powered by a tiny rechargeable power pack, the harness offers its user enhanced stability and strength when using heavy weapons. This attachment can only be used with Ranged (Heavy) and Gunnery weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Arakyd WW480 \"Goliath\" Weapon Harness, Galactic Arms HR12 Power Harness, SoroSuub \"Little Giant\" Heavy Weapon Power Assist.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WEPHARN"}},"_id":"VRNCp4KoqSN0s55B"}
{"name":"Vibro-Bayonet","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Vibro-Bayonet[h3]\nAlthough most fights are resolved with exchanges of blaster fire, a close-range firefight can quickly turn into a melee. When this happens, it pays to be prepared. Because the time it takes to draw a blade can mean the difference between life and death, some spacers equip their blasters with vibro-bayonets, essentially vibroblades mounted on the barrel of a gun. While a vibro-spear is not many Technicians' weapon of choice, having one at hand is considerably better than being effectively unarmed when combat takes place in such cramped quarters as the belly of a starship. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Heavy) weapon that could be logically mount a bayonet.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka Arms \"Last Resort\" Vibro-Bayonet, Merr-Sonn Model 3 Combat Attachment[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 56 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds a vibro-bayonet to the weapon </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"i7mntzzo0wm7sj66"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VIBBAY"}},"_id":"VYZ6hzbfnvWAU7po"}
{"name":"Hidden Compartment","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hidden Compartment[h3]\nThese are typically very small, easily concealed compartments hidden in places such as the hollowed-out handle of a blaster pistol or the heel of a shoe. Due to size constraints, they can typically only hold items with an encumbrance of 0, such as mem-stiks and credit chips. Compartments that can hold items with an encumbrance of 1 or 2 can be built into larger items, such as a false bottom in a document case.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds a small hidden compartment to a personal item. Finding the compartment requires a thorough once-over and a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Perception check[b]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":50,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HIDDENCOMP"}},"_id":"WPZbjYVhBfDzYiud"}
{"name":"Automated Weapon Mounting","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Automated Weapon Mounting[h3]\nUsed by elite special forces across the galaxy-and the occasional bounty hunter-an automated weapon mounting is a sophisticated pseudocybernetic that allows the user to fire a blaster or other handheld weapon while keeping both hands free, possibly for additional weapons. Automated harnesses are most commonly shoulder mounted, although a variety of models are available, some incorporating articulated appendages of up to a half meter in length. Sappers and combat engineers often find automated weapon mountings particularly useful , particularly when combined with a droid brain targeting system, as the mountings allow them to effect battlefield repairs without leaving themselves vulnerable. An automated weapon mounting may be activated by voice or neural link. For obvious reasons, these attachments are rarely seen outside of a battlefield, and they are outlawed on most worlds.\n[P]A weapon must also be modified in order to be armor-mounted, requiring one hard point.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 53 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Mount Weapon up to Encumbrance 3 Mod - Mount Weapon up to Encumbrance 3 </div><div>Once per encounter, may spend maneuver to make a combat action with mounted weapon.  Difficulty of check is upgraded once. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,{"_id":"X2ADhuYj0JGpTNVj","name":"Increase Allowable Mounted Weapon Encumbrance by 1 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"Increase Allowable Weapon Encumbrance by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"armor","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MOUNTADDL"}},"id":"t89dzcfuo6p9v0x0"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AUTOWEAPMOUNT"}},"_id":"WfUppwrYwOGX74sK"}
{"name":"Hunting Barrel","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hunting Barrel[h3]\nDesigned to increase range and accuracy, a hunting barrel can turn any blaster rifle into a dedicated hunting weapon. This two-meter-long replacement barrel is constructed of lightweight materials and packed with upgraded pulse adapters and denser, more aggressive galven circuitry. The increased accuracy and range come at the cost of the base weapon's weight and size, however. The extra-long barrel makes the weapon awkward to handle and fire without proper support, as well as making it almost impossible to conceal. A hunting barrel can only be used on a blaster rifle.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka Model 2 \"Huntsman\" Precision Barrel, SoroSuub WQ60 \"Sure-shot\" Barrel, Arakyd 3100 \"Deadeye\" Barrel.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 50 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Range Mod - Increases weapon's range by one Range Band </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. Count 2</div><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"4q115nbpq57ezth0"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HUNTBARREL"}},"_id":"WfZZqPhyYZxLVDuJ"}
{"name":"Vacuum Sealed","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Vacuum Sealed[h3]\n\nFull body armor can be designed to be sealed against a vacuum, allowing the user to operate in space. This modification provides the armor with enough air and insulation to survive for up to 10 minutes, and obviously also protects against adverse atmospheric environments. This can only be applied to laminate or battle armor. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Numerous Variants.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows the user to ignore the effects of\n          vacuum or poisonous atmospheric environments\n          for up to 10 minutes. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VACUUM"}},"_id":"WpvhzU7pMkfgkG6A"}
{"name":"Built-In Blaster Sight","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Built-In Blaster Sight[h3]\nA typical modification used by the Rebellion’s SpecForce troops, this attachment allows a harmless beam\nof energy to trickle out of the barrel on a half-trigger pull to \"paint” the target, letting the wielder see\nexactly where she is aiming Most models illuminate\nbeams in the human visual spectrum, but some use\nlight wavelengths invisible to the naked eye, which\nrequire special goggles to spot, to ensure the agent's\nposition remains uncompromised. This attachment\ncan only be applied to energy ranged weapons.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Remove [SE] added by the Called Shot use of the Aim maneuver from Ranged Light and Ranged Heavy checks. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":150,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BLASTSIGHT"}},"_id":"X5AeARl7ZYOo3vj6"}
{"name":"Tactical Command, Control, and Communications Suite","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Tactical Command, Control, and Communications Suite[h3]\nMounted to ships and vehicles piloted by designated\nsquadron leaders, the TC3 suite allows the sharing\nof data and sensor telemetry between networked\nships or vehicles. Built for use mainly in tanks, walkers,\nairspeeders, and starfighters, TC3 suites facilitate\nmore efficient communications between members of\na squadron, and they provide the squadron leader\nwith a number of command and control options to\nenhance the squadron’s performance.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Lead by Example[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>While active, a force commander in the vehicle upgrades the ability of all Mass Combat checks once </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"TACCOMM"}},"_id":"XWRY0KSVAP4KwVli"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Yacht","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Yacht[h3]\n      Converts a yacht to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Defense Zone Mod - Increases Defense Zone by 1 </div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 2</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 Count 5</div><div>Adds two forward light laser cannons and one aft light laser cannon </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARAYACHT"}},"_id":"XZ5rL5NfyfycBqQc"}
{"name":"Helmet Comlink","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Helmet Comlink[h3]\n\nRather than rely on a separate piece of equipment that can be broken, lost, or stolen, some mercenaries and bounty hunters prefer to install a micro comlink directly into their armor. A micro-comlink can comprise anything from a complete in-helmet system to a simple small microphone and speaker attached to a wristplate or near the shoulder. A micro-comlink can be installed in any armor.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Beta Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>A long-range comlink is integrated into the helmet </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HELMETCOM"}},"_id":"XdBjaqQBtUAHWF9R"}
{"name":"Enhanced Repulsorlift","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Enhanced Repulsorlift[h3]\nAs one might well guess from their name, speeders are swift craft by nature. For some pilots, however, there is no such thing as a enough speed. Enhancements and modifications to repulsorlift systems can often coax extra acceleration out of factory-standard models, despite the fact that manufacturers caution against making such dangerous customizations to their vehicles. The attachment can be applied to any airspeeder or landspeeder.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Ubikkian Transports Ultralift 2000[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 65 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENHREPULS"}},"_id":"XgOlLHK9Fw3M8Lk9"}
{"name":"(AD-1S) Shield Generator Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shield Generator Module  forAD-1S[h3]\nMany fightercraft lack\nshields, including most of the Galactic Empire's TIE\nseries. Of course, many pilots view going into battle\nwithout shields as a sure sign of a death wish. Soldiers\nof fortune and others who fight for credits rather than\nideology tend to prefer the thought of living to get paid\nto the prospect of dying gloriously for some intangible\nideal, and so the highly customizable AD-1 S can be\nfitted with shield generators to improve its durability.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Defense Zone Mod - Increases Defense Zone by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":8000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Q5hF8yx2DdQIR38p","name":"Increase Defense Zone Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Defense Zone by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFZONEADD"}},"id":"jbn13jjf5syzadd1"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD1SSHIELD"}},"_id":"YI2Gr1Uz2uwBjLvg"}
{"name":"Rapid Cargo Evacuation Chute","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Rapid Cargo Evacuation Chute[h3]\n\nThough no corporation officially acknowledges making a product with this functionality, many smugglers nonetheless rig their cargo bays to be able to rapidly dump their payloads (regardless of whether or not the vehicle is in motion, ideally). Though no smuggler ever wants to use this feature, dumping one's cargo can mean the difference between jail time and slipping past the authorities to smuggle another day. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Custom models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] as an action while in the cockpit or cargo bay to eject everything currently stored in the cargo hold. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RAPIDCARGOEVAC"}},"_id":"YjgEjABGPp5xndXh"}
{"name":"High-Output Ion Turbine","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]High-Output Ion Turbine[h3]\n\nA fast, powerful sublight engine, high output ion turbines increase a ship's raw, straight-line speed at the cost of slightly lower reliability. May be installed on any airspeeder or starship. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Girodyne Ter40 High-Output Ion Turbine, Sienar Fleet Systems SFS-220 Ion Drives, Koensayr Manufacturing R800 Ion Ramjet.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5300,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"IONTURBINE"}},"_id":"YpAv5GUqF1oBzlEj"}
{"name":"Retractable Garrote","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Retractable Garrote[h3]\nThis simple mod adds a garrote to any suitable item, typically a briefcase, comlink, bracelet, or shoe, but it can even be used on a stimpack or fusion lantern.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Equips the item with a retractable garrote. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RETRACGARROTE"}},"_id":"Yrn3zFyWKM9JcK5b"}
{"name":"Sorian Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Sorian Crystal[h3]\n[P]Though none can confirm accurately from which planet these mysterious stones originate, many traders recognize these gems by their radiance. Sorian crystals are said to reflect light in swirling, intricate patterns reminiscent of dancing flames. Because of these gems' relative scarcity, few realize that they are in fact kyber crystals. The energy blade formed by a sorian crystal surges briefly with the power whenever it comes into contact with another object moving at high speed - such as another lightsaber. The slight but sudden jolt  that emanates from the blade is often enough to throw an attacker off balance, giving the wielder a chance for a counterstrike. While this dded resistance also makes it harder to slice apart an opponent in a single stroke over the course of a long duel between skilled fighters, the unique edge it provides can make the difference between life and death. A sorian crystal is a lightsaber crystal.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 6</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 3</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>When used with the Parry talent, add [BO] to next combat check made against attacker before the end of the next round. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":16000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"xh4i95amzcs5mqsr"},{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"stwsbs91j845w94j"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SORIAN"}},"_id":"ZBHXJbpAjC5HZiSZ"}
{"name":"Energy Dispersion System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Energy Dispersion System[h3]\n\nThis minute metallic wiring is designed to distribute electrical shocks across the armor while grounding the user against the energy, reducing the potency of such attacks. It protects against electricity as well as weapons' Stun settings, although it does not effectively disperse blaster fire. This attachment can be installed on any armor. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Atlas Corp Model 88 Electric Shield, Merr-Sonn AEGIS Nanoarray.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When reducing strain damage by soak, count soak as two higher </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENERDISP"}},"_id":"ZCrq4DLKE1MpwYaX"}
{"name":"Under-Barrel Micro-Rocket Rack","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Under-Barrel Micro-Rocket Rack[h3]\nMicro-rockets can be fired in a plethora of ways, and some hunters mount them on their other weapons, giving these arms a deadly secondary fire mode (see [B]Micro-Rockets[b] on page 46). This attachment can be installed on any ranged weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Blastech \"Finisher\" Rocket Rack, TaggeCo Under-Barrel Rocket Battery.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Enables weapon to fire loaded micro-rockets. </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"y7cpuTEB0oOqRA5q","name":"Limited Ammo Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Some weapons fire particularly large or complex projectiles that cost significant amounts of credits, or are themselves a complete weapon that once launched is expended. A weapon with the Limited Ammo quality may be used to make a number of attacks equal to its Limited Ammo rating before it must be reloaded with a maneuver. In addition, each shot expends one of a limited number of rounds of ammo, which must be purchased or otherwise obtained before the weapon can be used. This also applies to grenades and other “one use” weapons which have the Limited Ammo 1 quality (here, the user is not “reloading” the grenade, but drawing another to use—but mechanically they are equivalent).","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LIMITEDAMMO"}},"id":"60i1xirwgdxex6sv"},{"_id":"oYIf6fg6qw9ccPdH","name":"Remove Setback Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Remove [SETBACK] from all attack checks when using this weapon","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SETBACKSUB"}},"id":"f022nfb2p9mkas7p"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MICROROCKRACK"}},"_id":"ZWLIJp1yGHsA8qzp"}
{"name":"Reinforced Shield Generator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reinforced Shield Generator[h3]\n\nA good defense is crucial to keeping a starship operational in the rough and tumble space of the Outer Rim. P-K's AEGIS Shield Generators and other reinforced shield generators upgrade a ship's stock particle and ray shielding so as to make it stronger and to make the shields easier to manage. While the AEGIS improves only one defense zone at a time, further tinkering with these units has resulted in improved shield strength. This may be added to any ship or vehicle. \n\n[P][B]Models include:[b] Phoah-Kingsmeyer 721a AEGIS Shield Generator, KDY 880 Palisade Shield Generator, Sienar SH-2/a.Z Shield Reinforcement.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Defense Zone Mod - Increases Defense Zone by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Q5hF8yx2DdQIR38p","name":"Increase Defense Zone Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Defense Zone by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFZONEADD"}},"id":"ej9cyx8001io1cbd"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RSG"}},"_id":"ZrWrtQxFcgZwV2py"}
{"name":"Enhanced Optics Suite","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Enhanced Optics Suite[h3]\n\nBuilt into a helmet, this system provides an individual with a host of specialized optical and audio sensors. Each system is equipped with passive light amplification, thermal signature readers, ultrasound pickups, millimeter wave emitters, video capture, and common optical enhancements. This may be installed on any armor. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BioTech MULTI Enhanced Vision System, Atlas Corp Full-Spectrum Optical Enhancer, Neuro-Saav Anq-Y Enhanced Optics Suite.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Removes up to [SETBACK][SETBACK] added to all Perception,\n          Vigilance, and combat skill checks\n          due to darkness, smoke, or other environmental effects\n          that obscure vision. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"EOS"}},"_id":"ZssZnJVgDfEqYMqO"}
{"name":"Hardened Circuits","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hardened Circuits[h3]\n\nThe demands put on a ship or vehicle's electrical system, both by the systems connected to it and by daily wear-and-tear, are enormous. Anything that draws power from a ship or vehicle's reactor, from the pilot's datapad charger to the onboard weapon systems, puts strain on every cable, every breaker, every bus plate between the system and the power source. Hardened circuits covers a variety of electrical transmission gear that, when installed, improve a vehicle or ship's power system and allow it to handle heavier-than-normal power loads. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Santhe/Sienar Model 30 Heavy-Duty Dielectric Power Bus, Fabritech Triple-Phase Thermal-Magnetic Circuit Breakers, Corellian Engineering Corporation SF/6 Hybrid Switchgear Module.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Stay on Target[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases System Strain Mod - Increases System Strain by 1 Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"kfUbhrn82nL9vXku","name":"Increases System Strain Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADD"}},"id":"yeckmbavukrrraob"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HARDCIRC"}},"_id":"ZwNSYop9vVFWn7jX"}
{"name":"Hardened","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hardened[h3]\n[P]Power armor relies on its energy source to maintain functionality. If this flow of energy is interrupted by a powerful electromagnetic burst or exposure to ion weapons, the armor loses both its mobility and its ability to enhance the wearer.  With the armor's vital systems \"hardened\" against such effects, power armor becomes immune to these attacks. Such hardening modifications are weighty, however. Adjustments must be made to nearly every subsystem to prevent even partial shutdowns from taking place. This attachment can only be applied to power armor.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Prevents deactivation of power armor by electromagnetic or ion weapons. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":900,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HARDENED"}},"_id":"a9ej7ZUCh5k1ApXF"}
{"name":"\"Accu-Strike\" Integrated Targeting Computer","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]\"Accu-Strike\" Integrated Targeting Computer[h3]\n\nComplex and sophisticated attachments, targeting systems integrate an advanced targeting computer and sensor suite, providing a constant stream of data to the user. Depending on the model, this information may be delivered by audio or on a visor HUD. Some particularly advanced systems incorporate small vibro-motors installed in the armor's gloves or gauntlets and wired to the helmet system, which subtly adjust the user's hands to enhance accuracy.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add [BOOST] to all Ranged attacks at long or extreme range. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"TARGCOMP"}},"_id":"a9qQMeNZj7FjZjiO"}
{"name":"Interior Broadcast Suite","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Interior Broadcast Suite[h3]\n\nAs a result of their transient lifestyles, most smugglers must bring their own entertainment with them wherever they go. For many species, music is a primary form of amusement in addition to being an important cultural touchstone, and so many smugglers install systems that let them broadcast their chosen auditory entertainment across the vessel. While this can have a soothing effect if everyone aboard the ship agrees with the selection of music, it can also be a source of considerable fric-tion between crewmates, such as if one crewmember is extremely dedicated to Gammorean opera and the rest of the crew does not share that unique taste. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Celta-corp Shipboard Music Suite, TaggeCo. Interior Broadcaster System.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases the strain threshold of each crewmember by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTBROAD"}},"_id":"aAzLn7tn9qTojOxF"}
{"name":"Ion Turbine Engine","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Ion Turbine Engine[h3]\nReliable and compact, these engines are often found in freighters seeking power without sacrificing space.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 82 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod - Increases System Strain by Silhouette Count 10</div><div>Increase Forward Defense Mod - Increase Forward Defense by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"TfqDzg8fQd6VBG9V","name":"Increase Speed Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Speed by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPEEDADD"}},"id":"82waeuwjtjv32b95"},{"_id":"WzEhZZQs7ZiJaqsh","name":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":5},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADDSIL"}},"id":"ou0g91b1n4i4x4gt"},{"_id":"26uEwvWhVxzeWHvY","name":"Increase Forward Defense Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png