{"name":"Concealment Alteration (Weapon)","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Concealment Alteration (Weapon)[h3]\nHoldout blasters and vibroknives are easy enough to hide, but when characters wish to pack a bit more of a punch, they need a more powerful (and usually larger) weapon. The simplest way to make a more obvious weapon or other item easier to conceal is to remove unnecessary parts or minimize its size. This is called a concealment alteration. Concealment alterations can include cutting weapon barrels, removing panels, and any other small physical changes that do not prohibit the item's primary function.\n[P]PCs wishing to make a concealment alteration need to make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b] and spend one hour per point of the item's encumbrance (with a minimum duration of one hour) in applying the changes. A successful check reduces the item's encumbrance by 1 (to a minimum of 1) and adds [SE] to any Perception checks to notice or search for the item; [TR] can be spent to make this [SE][SE] instead. Items with an encumbrance of 3 or higher are more difficult to modify, however, and so the difficulty to perform a concealment alteration increases by one for each point of encumbrance over 2. This means that making a concealment alteration to a typical ion blaster (encumbrance 3) would require a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b], while doing so to a standard disruptor rifle (encumbrance 5) would require a [B]Formidable ([DI][DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b]. Items with an encumbrance of 6 or higher cannot receive a concealment alteration. \n[P]A character can only attempt a concealment alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 80 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>PCs wishing to make a concealment alteration need to make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b] and spend one hour per point of the item's encumbrance (with a minimum duration of one hour) in applying the changes. Items with an encumbrance of 3 or higher are more difficult to modify, however, and so the difficulty to perform a concealment alteration increases by one for each point of encumbrance over 2. Items with an encumbrance of 6 or higher cannot receive a concealment alteration. </div><div>A successful check reduces the item's encumbrance by 1 (to a minimum of 1) and adds [SE] to any Perception checks to notice or search for the item; [TR] can be spent to make this [SE][SE] instead. </div><div>A character can only attempt a concealment alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONCEALALTERWEAP"}},"_id":"babaXPsCyAzeS6IU"}
{"name":"Reinforced Armor Plating","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reinforced Armor Plating[h3]\nOver the millennia, manufacturers and shipwrights across the galaxy have developed countless esoteric methods of protecting a vehicle or starship, from deflector screens to proton shields to ion diffusers. Still, for many Alliance engineers, it's hard to beat extra durasteel layers for cost-effective protection.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 61 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 2</div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"98Fa4BI2m8IVJdFp","name":"Increase Hull Trauma Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Hull Trauma by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HULLADD"}},"id":"184ux9xj7jaguj52"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REINARMPLATE"}},"_id":"bdNvitg39xYa3f2r"}
{"name":"Enhanced Carbon-Durasteel Armor","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Enhanced Carbon-Durasteel Armor[h3]\n\nProduced by numerous starship manufacturers, these armor plates are made from a complex lattice of carbon nanotubes embedded with spun threads of durasteel. Molecularly bonded to a ship's hull, they provide extra armor protection at the cost of a ship's maneuverability. This may be applied to all starships and vehicles. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Ferro-Magnesium Armor Plate, Cerro-Ablative Sheets.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ECDA"}},"_id":"bv7UEYhNANx178Zx"}
{"_id":"cDgfIhoA2MQAewhB","name":"Pannier Modular Cargo Handling System","type":"itemattachment","img":"systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Pannier Modular Cargo Handling System[h3]\nDesigned by Piccatech Ltd., the Pennier system is designed to fit as much cargo on a beast as it can carry in an efficient and secure manner. Its base is a specially designed load-bearing harness equipped with quick-release hardware. From this harness, a beast handler or teamster can hang a variety of secure, hard sided cargo containers. Made from either plasteel or reinforced fiberweave, the cargo containers are built in a variety of shapes and sizes to suit individual users' needs. The containers are equipped with an environmentally sealed locking lid that secures cargo and protects it from dirt, water and other contaminants.\n[P]The Pannier Modular Cargo Handling system comes with two cargo containers and can only be worn by riding or working animals of silhouette 2 or larger. It increases the creature's encumbrance threshold by 6, plus an additional 3 points of encumbrance threshold for each additional cargo containers added to the system (to a maximum increase of 12).[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 46 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Threshold by 3 Mod - Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 3 Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0,"isrestricted":false},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"4y4On9WZrhuo2N3I","name":"Increases Encumbrance Threshold by 3 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Increase Encumbrance Threshold by 3","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":10},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCTADD3"}},"id":"iss063yul7any564"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"all"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MODCARGOCONT","loaded":false}}}
{"name":"Hidden Compartments in Armor","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hidden Compartments in Armor[h3]\nUsually formed from rigid plates or packed with protective padding, most types of armor rarely facilitate the stowing of small objects. However, with some careful work, a character can add hidden pouches, concealed holsters, and unseen sheaths. \n[P]A character typically shaves down or hollows out a section of armor plating, or thins out protective mesh and padding, to make space for the hidden compartment. To make this change, he must spend a number of hours equal to the armor's encumbrance, pay a number of credits equal to 5% of the armor's price, and make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. Each [SU] or [TR] provides one encumbrance point's worth of hidden space in the armor. The armor cannot gain more encumbrance points for hiding objects than the suit's own encumbrance value, and items concealed in this way do not count towards the user's encumbrance threshold. Add [SE][SE] to all Perception checks made to notice items hidden in this manner. \n[P]No matter how many [SU] are rolled, though, a suit of armor cannot conceal any single item with an encumbrance value greater than 2. This means that if a character rolls [SU][SU][SU] and thus has space for items totaling 3 encumbrance, the character could conceal a heavy blaster pistol (encumbrance 2) and a vibroknife (encumbrance 1), but not a blaster carbine (encumbrance 3). This is because while it is possible to hollow out a compartment in a chest plate and perhaps a second in a boot, there is no single location on a suit of armor large enough to accommodate a particularly large or unwieldy item. \n[P]Each point of encumbrance value for concealed space gained in this fashion reduces the armor's hard points by one, to a minimum of 0. Any armor with no hard points, such as padded armor or heavy clothing, can still have enough concealed space for an item with an encumbrance value of 1.\n[P]For every two encumbrance points' worth of concealed space created, an armor's soak is reduced by one. However, each net [AD] on the initial Mechanics check to modify the armor cancels out one point of soak reduction.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 82 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>[B]Price:[b] 5% of armor's price. </div><div>To make this change, he must spend a number of hours equal to the armor's encumbrance and make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. Each [SU] or [TR] provides one encumbrance point's worth of hidden space in the armor. The armor cannot gain more encumbrance points for hiding objects than the suit's own encumbrance value, and items concealed in this way do not count towards the user's encumbrance threshold. Add [SE][SE] to all Perception checks made to notice items hidden in this manner. </div><div>No matter how many [SU] are rolled, though, a suit of armor cannot conceal any single item with an encumbrance value greater than 2. </div><div>Each point of encumbrance value for concealed space gained in this fashion reduces the armor's hard points by one, to a minimum of 0. Any armor with no hard points, such as padded armor or heavy clothing, can still have enough concealed space for an item with an encumbrance value of 1. </div><div>For every two encumbrance points' worth of concealed space created, an armor's soak is reduced by one. However, each net [AD] on the initial Mechanics check to modify the armor cancels out one point of soak reduction. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HIDCOMPARMOR"}},"_id":"crTpJh6k607Igh8l"}
{"name":"Electronic Counter-Countermeasures Suite","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Theater Command and Control System[h3]\n“Electronic counter-countermeasures” (ECCM) is\na catchall term for a number of techniques, such as\nFAST ECM detection, frequency hopping, pulse compression,\nand polarization filtering, used to prevent or\nbreak comms and sensor jamming caused by enemy\nelectronic countermeasures. ECCM suites require large\namounts of energy and often reduce the effectiveness\nof a ship or vehicle’s sensors. On smaller ships like\nfighters and shuttles, as well as in ground vehicles and\nairspeeders, ECCM suites are installed in line with the\nvehicle’s active sensors, and they can be activated or\ndeactivated quickly by the pilot or electronic systems\noperator. On larger ships of gunship size or bigger,\nECCM suites are complex affairs composed of numerous\ncompartments and staffed by a dedicated crew.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Fabritech 830 “Stutterer” ECCM system,\nMiradyne A5x.4 “Oracle” ECCM suite (starfighters\nand shuttles only), KDY Advanced Capital ECCM suite\n(gunships, cruisers, and battleships only).[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Lead by Example[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Computers check[b] to cancel all effects of an electronic countermeasures suite. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ELCOUNTCOUNT"}},"_id":"d0mls2nMTXwYetb6"}
{"name":"Integrated Holsters","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Integrated Holsters[h3]\nBy mounting their holsters into the framework of their armor, combatants can ensure no one can catch them unarmed. Not only does the wearer have easy access to these weapons at all times, but powered servos an other systems can be set up to assist the wearer in drawing or stowing these weapons more rapidly. A character with  a fully tooled set of integrated holsters has access to a hidden arsenal that can overwhelm most foes.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech \"Personal Armory\" Gear.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Holster Weapon up to Encumbrance 3 Mod - Holster Weapon up to Encumbrance 3 Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":300,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,{"_id":"KYuIW207cLRWJ2RP","name":"Holster Weapon up to Encumbrance 3 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"Holster Weapon up to Encumbrance 3","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"armor","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HOLSTER3"}},"id":"5odv5hgwzah8r6yp"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTHOLST"}},"_id":"d3FFrl22AdFZ7Kcd"}
{"name":"Filed Front Sight","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Filed Front Sight[h3]\n\nAn old assassin's trick, this is the simple act of removing the front sight of a blaster pistol by filing it off. A common modification to holdout blasters (along with removing their serial numbers), filing down the weapon's front sight allows it to be drawn more quickly from its holster, and reduces the possibility of it becoming snared on clothing. Unfortunately, while this modification makes for easy concealment and drawing, it also reduces the weapon's accuracy, as it effectively makes it impossible to aim with any amount of precision. This modification may only be applied to pistol-sized weapons. Applying it oneself requires an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]; the cost is paying others to perform the modification.\n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases the difficulty of combat checks to hit targets at\n          ranges beyond Short range by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":25,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"FFS"}},"_id":"dFTo1xeteZjdW03s"}
{"name":"Jump Boots","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Jump Boots[h3]\nJump boots are, essentially, a single-use jetpack built into a thick boots and allows a user to leap over tall obstacles and even fly for a very limited time. This attachment can be applied to any armor with an encumbrance of 4 or less. It is good for only one use and cannot be used again until the rockets are refueled, which costs 100 credits and takes 30 minutes.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Zim Systems LO-44.a micro-rockets.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduce difficulty of all Athletics checks to jump up or over obstacles by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"JUMPBOOTS"}},"_id":"dMeEp9HOzuGaYaKj"}
{"name":"Concealment Alteration (Gear)","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Concealment Alteration (Gear)[h3]\nHoldout blasters and vibroknives are easy enough to hide, but when characters wish to pack a bit more of a punch, they need a more powerful (and usually larger) weapon. The simplest way to make a more obvious weapon or other item easier to conceal is to remove unnecessary parts or minimize its size. This is called a concealment alteration. Concealment alterations can include cutting weapon barrels, removing panels, and any other small physical changes that do not prohibit the item's primary function.\n[P]PCs wishing to make a concealment alteration need to make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b] and spend one hour per point of the item's encumbrance (with a minimum duration of one hour) in applying the changes. A successful check reduces the item's encumbrance by 1 (to a minimum of 1) and adds [SE] to any Perception checks to notice or search for the item; [TR] can be spent to make this [SE][SE] instead. Items with an encumbrance of 3 or higher are more difficult to modify, however, and so the difficulty to perform a concealment alteration increases by one for each point of encumbrance over 2. This means that making a concealment alteration to a typical ion blaster (encumbrance 3) would require a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b], while doing so to a standard disruptor rifle (encumbrance 5) would require a [B]Formidable ([DI][DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b]. Items with an encumbrance of 6 or higher cannot receive a concealment alteration. \n[P]A character can only attempt a concealment alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 80 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>PCs wishing to make a concealment alteration need to make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Skulduggery check[b] and spend one hour per point of the item's encumbrance (with a minimum duration of one hour) in applying the changes. Items with an encumbrance of 3 or higher are more difficult to modify, however, and so the difficulty to perform a concealment alteration increases by one for each point of encumbrance over 2. Items with an encumbrance of 6 or higher cannot receive a concealment alteration. </div><div>A successful check reduces the item's encumbrance by 1 (to a minimum of 1) and adds [SE] to any Perception checks to notice or search for the item; [TR] can be spent to make this [SE][SE] instead. </div><div>A character can only attempt a concealment alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONCEALALTERGEAR"}},"_id":"dbM0NDlM2TqHF5cU"}
{"name":"(AD-1S) Hyperdrive Class 8 Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hyperdrive Class 8 Module for AD-1S[h3]\nInstalling a hyperdrive, even a relatively low-grade one, in an AD-IS takes up a good deal of space inside of the craft, but also allows\nit to operate independently. For many mercenaries, bounty hunters, and other frequent travelers, such an upgrade is well worth the cost.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Class 8 Hyperdrive Mod - Add Class 8 Hyperdrive </div><div>Add astromech droid socket. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"0HibaLcBPREmA3Wv","name":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of .5 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVESUB5"}},"id":"n5x1p3ontobn90mo"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD1SHYPER8"}},"_id":"ddK551rHD7TLWOuP"}
{"name":"Magnetic Weapon Tether","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Magnetic Weapon Tether[h3]\n[P]A magnetic weapon tether is a relatively simple modification that consists of a small magnetic device built into the weapon. The magnetic weapon tether allows the wielder to snap the weapon back to a readied position with a press of a button, rather than having to scramble to retrieve it. While many Force users might scoff at this ability - after all, why use a device for what they can do with the force anyway - others prefer to have the extra layer or safety, or wish to avoid using their Force powers openly in places where the Empire's presence is strong. This attachment can be applied to any weapon wielded in one hand that could logically benefit from a weapon tether.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Wielder may recover engaged weapon as incidental. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MAGTETH"}},"_id":"dtoKcadTB2prjEN2"}
{"name":"Encrypted Computer","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Encrypted Computer[h3]\nA skilled Slicer knows how to protect a computer system from others skilled in electronic skulduggery, and is likely to take steps to do just that. Whether consisting of modifications and programming by a crew member or of specialized software purchased on the black market, encrypted systems can protect a ship against slicing attacks at port and during battle. In addition to preventing catastrophes during skirmishes, the extra security is of great use to any group that wants to keep its data private. This attachment can be applied to any vehicle or starship.\n[B][P]Models Include:[b] Numerous Custom Variants[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 65 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Upgrade difficulty of all Computers checks made to slice the ship's computer system once. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCRYCOMP"}},"_id":"e0Y07AuACknO7lCN"}
{"name":"Threat Monitor","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Threat Monitor[h3]\n\nA threat monitor is a suite of motion detectors, electroreceptors, and photoreceptors that constantly monitors the armor wearer's vicinity and, through direc-tional auditory or electrical cues, warns the wearer of imminent threats and incoming attacks. While many find threat monitors somewhat annoying to wear, they can provide a critical edge in life-or-death situations. This attachment can only be used on armor and is typically integrated into the helmet, visor, or another place where the user can easily see it at all times. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Atlas Corp Pan-directional Alert Scanner, Galactic Electronics Z-12 Threat Assessor.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Lords of Nal Hutta[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Advantage to Initiative Check Mod - Add One [ADVANTAGE] to Initiative Check </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"NfiIwVg2EI2mtCER","name":"Add Advantage to Initiative Check Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Add One [ADVANTAGE] to Initiative Check","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ADVADDINIT"}},"id":"o9pme9bjb5ax8lmm"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"THREATMON"}},"_id":"e3VPg4AmPy8KYcFu"}
{"name":"Decoy Buoy","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Decoy Buoy[h3]\nA favorite of scoundrels and pirates, decoy buoys are often devices cobbled together from salvaged parts, including transponders and comm systems. Although it might visually resemble nothing so much as a cylinder - or amalgamation of scrap parts - a meter or so across, a well constructed decoy bot transmits a transponder signal, emits ion streams and outputs other data and signals associated with starships. This attachment can be applied to any starship.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Numerous custom variants[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 65 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Buoy may be jettisoned as an action. </div><div>Buoy can be programmed with a specific transponder code with a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Computers check[b]. </div><div>Buoy can be set to transmit a distress signal or other data. </div><div>A character operating ship sensors must make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Computers check[b] to identify that the buoy is not an actual ship. </div><div>After being jettisoned, buoy no longer counts as being attached to the ship until it is reattached. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DECOYBUOY"}},"_id":"e5izrUGXfkKvzPdc"}
{"name":"Whipcord Thrower","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Whipcord Thrower[h3]\nA whipcord thrower quickly deploys a length of high-tensile strength cable, firing it over a distance in order to secure a target. Its convenient armor mounting allows the user to act quickly, whether to arrest their own freefall, secure a loose object, or entangle a surprised opponent.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Collapse of the Republic[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Whipcord throwers can be used as climbing gear to assist the wearer in climbing a steep vertical surface, reducing the difficulty to climb by one. they may support a weight up to 200 kilograms. Further, the thrower may be used as a weapon with the following profile: {Melee, Damage +1, Critical 5; Range [Short]; Ensnare 2) </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":600,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WHIPCRDTH"}},"_id":"eSqZyaupypCTubzA"}
{"name":"Strength Enhancing System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Strength Enhancing System[h3]\n\nStrength enhancing systems easily converts a suit of full armor into a power-assisted suit. Composed of a matrix of electrically controlled myomer synthetic muscle fibers backed up with nano-hydraulics, the MSES increases a wearer's raw physical strength, allowing him to lift more and carry more for longer periods of time. This attachment can only be used with laminate armor or similar full-body hard armor suits. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Industrial Automaton Xr5 Power Assist, BioTech \"Brute Strength Enhancer, Atlas Corp Myomer Strength Enhancing System.","attributes":{"Brawn":{"mod":"Brawn","modtype":"Characteristic","value":1}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SES"}},"_id":"eUuucBZPKqCJuEPM"}
{"name":"Spoofing Scanners","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Spoofing Scanners[h3]\nSome physical alterations, no matter how extensive, can't fool the piercing eyes of scanners and electronic detection devices. However, clever Rebels aren't without hope. By reducing the energy output of a weapon or by installing jury-rigged scramblers to shield a device from sensory devices, a character can potentially allow the item to evade detection. \n[P]Characters attempting such an alteration must make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. This adds [SE] to Perception checks that operators using a scanning device make to detect the item. They may spend [TR] from the Mechanics check to have the difficulty of such detection checks upgraded once.\n[P]Unfortunately, the reduction of a weapon's energy output does diminish its effectiveness. Each net [SU] from the check for reducing a weapon's energy output also reduces its damage by one, to a minimum of 1. Characters may spend [TR] from the Mechanics check to halve this reduction in damage, rounding up. \n[P]Only weapons that use energy-based attacks or other advanced devices can have their energy output reduced or signature concealed. This means that slugthrowers and traditional explosive devices cannot be modified in this fashion. In addition, items that require extensive power (such as repeating blasters) cannot have their energy signature reduced. Note that this differs from the scanner-proof hardware weapon attachment, which requires no check for use once it is installed and is more a customization of the weapon than a mechanical alteration.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 82 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Characters attempting such an alteration must make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. This adds [SE] to Perception checks that operators using a scanning device make to detect the item. They may spend [TR] from the Mechanics check to have the difficulty of such detection checks upgraded once. </div><div>Each net [SU] from the check for reducing a weapon's energy output also reduces its damage by one, to a minimum of 1. Characters may spend [TR] from the Mechanics check to halve this reduction in damage, rounding up. </div><div>Only weapons that use energy-based attacks or other advanced devices can have their energy output reduced or signature concealed. This means that slugthrowers and traditional explosive devices cannot be modified in this fashion. In addition, items that require extensive power (such as repeating blasters) cannot have their energy signature reduced. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPOOFSCAN"}},"_id":"edidGhfZdZCFI5nc"}
{"name":"Repulsor Pack","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Repulsor Pack[h3]\nWhile lacking the range and power of a true jetpack, a repulsor pack provides a reliable-and less terrifying-alternative for those new to the realm of personal flight devices. A repulsor pack allows for controlled descents from nearly any height, as well as hovering speeds of up to thirty-five kilometers per hour, its name being something of a misnomer, a repulsor pack actually consists of a number of small, relatively low-powered repulsor lifts mounted to the user's torso and limbs. Although the sight of an experienced user gliding through the air is quite impressive, the learning curve is steep. Perhaps due to the importance of leg movement in most packs for controlling movement and speed, the devices are sometimes disparagingly called \"jet pants.\"[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 53 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows user to function as vehicle:  Speed 1, Handling -1, System Strain 2, Silhouette same as user. </div><div>Pack can only travel in atmosphere up to 75 meters in altitude. </div><div>Operator uses Coordination skill for any relevant checks. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REPULSPACK"}},"_id":"f6zy3tZyNpbVL6MQ"}
{"name":"Underslung Scattergun","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Underslung Scattergun[h3]\n\nAn ungainly attachment, an underslung scattergun is a single-shot slugthrower that can be attached to another weapon. While hardly what one would call subtle, it nonetheless has found a ready market amongst some bounty hunters and gunslingers due to its low cost and impressive effect. This attachment can only applied to pistol and rifle-sized weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka \"Leveller\" Under-barrel Scattergun, Merr-Sonn XZ03 Scattershell Slugthrower Attachment, Goseia Heavy Industries Concern \"Troubleshooter\" Underslung Slugthrower.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds a scattergun to the weapon. </div><div>Cumbersome Quality - A Cumbersome weapon is large, unwieldy, awkward, or heavy. To wield a Cumbersome weapon properly, the character needs a Brawn characteristic equal to or greater than the weapon’s Cumbersome rating. For each point of Brawn the character is deficient, he must increase the difficulty of all checks made while using the weapon by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"UNDERSCATTER"}},"_id":"fAp8HDGo22IOvrSH"}
{"name":"Plasma Drill","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Plasma Drill[h3]\nOriginally developed for asteroid mining, a plasma drill is a superheated auger capable of boring through virtually any material, given enough time. Although a plasma drill is rarely effective as a weapon, commanders and engineers alike have recognized myriad other uses for a vehicle mounting one, from tunneling under enemy fortifications to excavating hidden underground facilities for their own use.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 61 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 Count 2</div><div>Can tunnel through solid rock and most metals at speed 1. </div><div>May be employed as a weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"bNGCMxHyQem1bD7S","name":"Increases Handling Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Handling by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HANDLINGADD"}},"id":"2ixz7gcunruapk7m"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PLASMADRILL"}},"_id":"fNOukADtaVwz9vej"}
{"name":"\"Bantha's Eye\" Laser Sight","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]\"Bantha's Eye\" Laser Sight[h3]\n\nAn extremely simple gun sight, a laser sight emits a low-power light beam to place a visible \"dot\" that marks the weapon's precise target. A laser sight can help even an amateur shooter hit a target. One drawback to this upgrade is that the laser can alert an otherwise unaware target to the shooter. For these reasons, laser sights are rarely used by sharpshooters and snipers. This attachment can be used with any Ranged (Light) or Ranged (Heavy) weapon that do not possess the Blast quality.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Advantage to Successful Check Mod - Add One [ADVANTAGE] to Successful Check </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LASERSIGHT"}},"_id":"fiGfuk7mP5bFSn0V"}
{"name":"Biofeedback System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Biofeedback System[h3]\n\nThis system closely monitors the vital signs of the person wearing the armor. It can immediately identify when the user is hurt or experiencing elevated levels of adrenaline and administer minor sedatives, healing chemicals, and other drugs as needed. This attachment can be installed on any full-body armor suit. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BioTech \"Autodoc\" Monitoring Network, Atlas Corp NG-7 Vital System.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Strain Mod - Increases user's strain by one Count 4</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3300,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BIOFEED"}},"_id":"flVghJSzLGHcZx0Y"}
{"name":"Upgraded Firepower","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Upgraded Firepower[h3]\n\nA very common practice on starships and in more violent, less reputable races, upgraded weapons are actually something of a liability in the Cloud City Grand Prix. Given that the destruction of enemy vessels is strictly prohibited, overly powerful weapons can result not only in disqualification but prosecution as well. Installing this attachment requires a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. This upgrade may only be attached to vehicles of silhouette 2 or lower.\n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Jewel of Yavin[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase damage of weapon system by one Mod - Increase damage of weapon system by one </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"UPGFIRE"}},"_id":"fw1g8lCTcYVuAd0X"}
{"name":"Nightshadow Coating","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Nightshadow Coating[h3]\n\nA special sensor-baffling coating manufactured by Arakyd Industries, nightshadow can make a vessel very difficult to detect. Highly-restricted by the Empire, nightshadow coating is much sought after by smugglers who can obtain it. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Arakyd Industries Nightshadow vehicle coating.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduces range of enemy ship's passive sensors by 1 (minimum of close range) for detecting a vessel with nightshadow coating. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"NIGHTCOAT"}},"_id":"g5HEB2siYZ1ZwBus"}
{"name":"Hydraulic Control Circuits","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hydraulic Control Circuits[h3]\n\nHydraulic control circuits are a throwback to an earlier era of shipbuilding. Instead of using traditional conductive material pressed into composite wafer boards to transfer electromagnetic energy, HCCs use countless, near-microscopic transparisteel tubes full of highly conductive liquid metal similar in its composition to mercury. Held under pressure and regulated by a series of valves, this metal controls the flow of energy. Bulky, antiquated, and difficult to work with, these circuits do have an incredible resistance to the effects of ion weapons, a fact that has not gone unnoticed among spacers. This may be applied to non-fighter starships. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Corellian Engineering Hydraulic Control Circuits, Santhe/Sienar Hardened Circuitry, Fabritech Insulated Circuitry.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Half damage from weapons with Ion quality </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,{"_id":"kfUbhrn82nL9vXku","name":"Increases System Strain Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADD"}},"id":"lj2j0b11ax4phk78"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HCC"}},"_id":"g6itTfXxnGd09epr"}
{"name":"Theater Command and Control System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Theater Command and Control System[h3]\nFitted to ships or vehicles of silhouette 4 or larger, a\ntheater command and control system (TCCS) grants a\ncommanding officer and staff incredible control over\nlarge-scale conflicts. Using a combination of sensor\ntelemetry, tactical data links, and banks of powerful\nprocessors, a TCCS takes in and analyzes battlespace\ndata to provide Alliance commanders with all of the\ndata needed to make good strategic decisions in battle.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Lead by Example[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>While active, force commander on the bridge upgrades the ability of all Mass Combat checks twice </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":8500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"THEATCOMM"}},"_id":"gGqiVo7FC9BvLQ65"}
{"name":"Gravity Mine Launcher","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Gravity Mine Launcher[h3]\n\nGravity mine launchers, and their accompanying gravity mines, are small anti-vehicle mines produced by a number of arms manufacturers. While each brand uses its own patented gravitic technology, gravity mines and their launchers share a number of common traits. The mines range anywhere from the size of a slim datapad to a meter across, depending on their intended use, and are packed with advanced gravity well generation systems. When deployed, gravity mines create a localized area of intense gravity that can reduce the output of repulsorlift drives or even shut them down completely, stopping a speeder in its tracks. While they are often used in military installations to restrict ship or vehicle access to sensitive areas or to create firing lanes for weapon emplacements, they can also be used in sabotage or to lay traps for incoming ships or airspeeders. Gravity mine launchers are simple box-type launchers mounted on landspeeders that allow a vehicle crew to lay a minefield with relative ease. \n\n[P]The character piloting or operating the weapons on a vehicle equipped with a gravity mine launcher can deploy a single gravity mine anywhere on the ground within close range by spending an action. Once the mine is deployed, it automatically attaches to any other starship or vehicle using repulsorlifts that comes within close range of it. For every 1 mine attached to a vehicle that uses the Piloting (Planetary) skill, that vehicle reduces its speed by 1. For every 2 mines attached to a starship that uses the Piloting (Space) skill, that starship reduces its speed by 1. An attached mine can be removed with an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] SoroSuub X80a UltraMass Gravity Pulse Generator, Taim & Bak Model 19 micro-gravity well mines.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Stay on Target[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows vehicle to deploy gravity mines within close range </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GRAVMINE"}},"_id":"gib5RjQykzKEocqP"}
{"name":"Replusor-Assisted Lifting","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Replusor-Assisted Lifting[h3]\nAlthough more common among factory or warehouse labor crews than in battle, repulsor-assist systems have gained some popularity among bounty hunters who need to haul in heavy catches. The systems operate through a series of miniaturized repulsorlift generators placed at key joints throughout the armor, easing the weight of attached suits, as well as any loads they might support. Of course, the repulsorlift generators are tuned to reduce weight and pressure rather than exert force on their own, so some hunters prefer powered armor suits with lesser lifting capabilities but more general applications for their servos. This attachment can only be used with laminate armor and other full-body hard armor suits.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Guldak Heavy Industries Personal Repulsor Fitting.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Brawn for Determining Encumbrance Threshold Mod - Increase Brawn for Determining Encumbrance Threshold by 1 Count 5</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"CAIzlpIBsS1t5h4I","name":"Increases Brawn for Determining Encumbrance Threshold Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Increase Brawn for Determining Encumbrance Threshold by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCTBRADD"}},"id":"uq0abxszc7he28kf"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REPASSLIFT"}},"_id":"gkKhR7yMTAmrZFJM"}
{"name":"Superior Armor Customization","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Superior Armor Customization[h3]\n\nAny piece of armor can benefit from retooling at the hands of a superior craftsman. A skilled armorsmith can add improved plastoid or even durasteel plating to increase the protection a piece of armor offers even as he decreases its weight and bulk. Of course, such delicate and exacting work can make the armor less customizable in other respects. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Numerous Variants.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Superior Quality - A Superior item is a sterling example of its kind, representing masterful craftsmanship. A Superior weapon generates automatic [AD] on all checks related to its use, and has its base damage increased by one. Superior armor has its encumbrance reduced by one and its soak value increased by one. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SACUST"}},"_id":"gpxNN78mbjWBTsal"}
{"name":"Stealth Field Generator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Stealth Field Generator[h3]\nProduced by a number of stealth technology companies, stealth field generators are the final word in personal active stealth technology. They use a combination of optical camouflage, low-output cloaking technology, active electromagnetic dampers, electronic acoustic bafflers, and thermal shielding to make a user virtually invisible to both the naked eye and to most scanners. These systems are not perfect, however. Users still need to know how to move stealthily and how to use cover and shadows to their advantage. Users also cannot move faster than a walk, or the stealth field will break down. This attachment can be applied to any armor. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Fabritech XO-A \"Vanish l\" Personal Stealth Generator, Kerner Corp. \"Defel\" Cloaking Belt.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Upgrades the difficulty of all opposed Perception checks to spot the wearer once. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STEALTHFGEN"}},"_id":"gqsCeBuZ8lOkckAl"}
{"name":"Lightweight Frame","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Lightweight Frame[h3]\nThis mod reduces both the weight and bulk of ranged weapons to make them easier to handle and conceal. Along with a frame made of a lighter alloy, this mod also includes lightweight polycarbonate stocks, foregrips, and other pieces designed to lighten up a blaster pistol or slugthrower rifle. This attachment can be applied to any weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech \"Featherlite\" blaster frame.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 56 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Encumbrance Mod - Decrease Encumbrance by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":650,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FIcN4TkIpZPNEqah","name":"Decreases Encumbrance Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Decrease Encumbrance by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCSUB"}},"id":"w6ug3n2lp3dx9ea0"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LIGHTFR"}},"_id":"gtS8Kyaou90QyPVF"}
{"name":"Integrated Scanner","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Integrated Scanner[h3]\nA scanner incorporated into a weapon allows the user to keep a rifle readied while constantly monitoring the surrounding area for danger. Specialized units might detect life signs, movement, or the energy cells of weapons. The battlefield awareness added by such a device can make the difference between victory and defeat. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Heavy) weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Carbanti United Electronics Mk. II Omni-Scope, CryonCorp \"Heads-Up\" Scanner Suite[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Weapon incorporates a general-purpose scanner. </div><div>Wielder adds automatic [AD][AD] to Initiative checks while weapon is drawn. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":675,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTSCAN2"}},"_id":"hJeLINzcH57fypxu"}
{"name":"Kimber Stone","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Kimber Stone[h3]\n[P]Kimber stones are a type of kyber crystal produced by violent volcanic activity on the moon of Y'ness in the N'zoth system. They were once considered unsuitable for use in lightsabers due to the non-lethal nature of the blades they create. Certain Jedi Knights saw potential in kimber stones, and so a number were acquired from Y'ness prior to the destruction of the Jedi Order. Today, kimber stones are occasionally sold at auction on the black market, usually as mere trinkets by those who do not understand their true value as kyber crystals. A kimber stone is a lightsaber crystal.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 9</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating </div><div>Stun Damage Quality - Some weapons deal Stun damage instead of regular damage. In this case, the weapon deals damage as strain instead of wounds. This damage is still reduced by a target’s soak.\n\n[P]A variant of this is a Stun setting. As a free action, the wielder can choose to switch the setting of his weapon to “Stun.” In this case, it does stun damage as described above. When weapons with a stun setting are used to deal stun damage, their range changes to short and cannot be increased. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":6500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"amp5zc34a0lrq13l"},{"_id":"QQf8B9koRsupvLFr","name":"Concussive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"The weapon’s attack can leave the target shell­-shocked from mighty blows or punishing shockwaves, unable to perform any but the most basic actions. The target is staggered (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Concussive rating. A staggered target cannot perform actions.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONCUSSIVE"}},"id":"p87qetl8qmr1sg5q"},{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"1f9m16twnmdb7xxr"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"KIMBER"}},"_id":"hL8Fb4iweUzowRGK"}
{"name":"Containment Field","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Containment Field[h3]\nDesigned for permanent installation, a containment field generator consists of two flat, cylindrical generators—one bolted to the floor, the other to the ceiling— that hold a single individual captive in a powerful stasis field. Individuals held in a containment field. Individuals held in a containment field wear magnetic binders and are suspended in mid-air, completely isolated from the world around them. When held in  a containment field, individuals are usually fitted with bio-signs monitors due to the field's distressing habit of causing heart attacks, brain damage, or death if it is not tuned correctly. This attachment can be installed on any vessel of silhouette 4 or higher.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Gordarl Weaponsmiths A1 Containment Field.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 64 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Can hold one Silhouette 1 creature.  Creature can see, hear, and speak, but cannot move. </div><div>Operator can attack prisoner.  Prisoner must make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Resilience check[b] and suffers 1 damage per [FA] and one [TH] may be used to inflict 1 strain. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":7500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONTFIELD"}},"_id":"hP82NhW3vzC4pgM1"}
{"name":"Radiation Shielding","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Radiation Shielding[h3]\nThe galaxy contains many perils, but one of the most common is radiation. From the depths of space to polluted industrial zones, radiation hazards both natural and artificial are a frequent threat to spacers. Although spacesuits provide a degree of protection and specialized hazard suits are available, some individuals prefer to also be protected from blaster bolts and blades. A variety of polymers, reflective coatings, and energy dampeners can be fitted or applied to armour to provide protection from radiation. This attachment can only be applied to laminate armor, heavy battle armor, and any other armor that can be fully sealed.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Loronar Model 4 Hostile Environment Treatment, Neuro-Saav Radiological Hazard Shielding.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add [BO][BO] to Resilience checks to resist radiation. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RADSHIELD"}},"_id":"hY5kF6eH7vs8aD9H"}
{"name":"Autopilot Droid Brain","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Autopilot Droid Brain[h3]\nMore advanced and sophisticated than standard autopilot systems, a specialized autopilot droid brain has become a popular upgrade among smugglers and others. Capable of piloting a vehicle or ship with reasonable competence, autopilot droid brains can be communicated with remotely via a beckon call, allowing the user to summon the vehicle or ship from up to several hundred kilometers away. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Go-Corp CD-12a autopilot droid brain.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds a Droid Brain with Piloting Skills 2 and Intellect 0 </div><div>May summon vehicle via a beacon call. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":7500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PILOTBRAIN"}},"_id":"hkbuWTo0fc2YZGlw"}
{"name":"Dragite Gem","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Dragite Gem[h3]\n\nSmall, dull, and brittle, Dragite gems are found in the caves and caverns of the D'olop mountain range on M'haeli, an agriworld in the Expansion Region. In their natural state, dragite crystals are one of the most brittle kyber crystals, and they produce a loud ringing when struck. Worked into a suitable lightsaber crystal, a difficult task due to the dragite gem's distressing tendency to fracture or shatter easily, it produces a blade that pulses and hums loudly. In addition to this noise, when a lightsaber equipped with a dragite gem strikes a solid target, it produces a deafening crack and a shock wave that can disorient and even cause bodily harm to its target. A dragite gem is a lightsaber crystal. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 3</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Disorient Quality - A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs. </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":14000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"3hsa8gdedbdeieg5"},{"_id":"QQf8B9koRsupvLFr","name":"Concussive Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"The weapon’s attack can leave the target shell­-shocked from mighty blows or punishing shockwaves, unable to perform any but the most basic actions. The target is staggered (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Concussive rating. A staggered target cannot perform actions.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONCUSSIVE"}},"id":"5suky5tylv8zd85w"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"bxa0qncn1eiwj1c0"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DRAGITE"}},"_id":"howmxD5aAhpnik6g"}
{"name":"Shock Pulse Emitter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shock Pulse Emitter[h3]\nShock pulse emitters operate along principles similar to a blaster's stun setting, but at much shorter effective range—a range short enough to be of little use as weapons in themselves. However, when shock pulse emitters are integrated into weapons intended for close combat to begin with, they become effective combat tools to debilitate opponents and make a finishing blow easier to land. This attachment can be installed on any Melee or Brawl weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Corellian Personal Defense Stun Pad.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Stun Quality - A weapon with Stun causes strain to the target. When the Stun quality is activated, it inflicts strain equal to the weapon’s Stun rating. Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"aDvHhRgItEzT7XHl","name":"Stun Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Stun causes strain to the target. When the Stun quality is activated, it inflicts strain equal to the weapon’s Stun rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STUN"}},"id":"jvih8h9iv4g0au5e"},{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"yalxobggd8da5zg4"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SHOCKPULSEMIT"}},"_id":"hzJYIcIJQdCsWSKg"}
{"name":"Varpeline Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Varpeline Crystal[h3]\nVarpeline crystals are hard, super dense minerals found on the Outer Rim worlds of Mearalis II. Ranging in color from white to a rich gold, they are scattered throughout Mearalis II's extensive mountain ranges. When properly worked, varpeline crystals can be used to slice through nearly any substance known in the galaxy. While they are typically used in industrial cutting machinery or precision fabrication instruments, these stones are occasionally used to great effect as lightsaber crystals.\n[P]When installed in a lightsaber, this crystal produces a blade that emits a short, sharp ringing tone when it strikes an object. A lightsaber equipped with a varpeline  crystal can often cut through the thickest armor or toughest materials, and have a disturbing tendency to dismember living targets.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 8</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 3</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Vicious Quality - When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result. </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>When spending [TR] to inflict Critical Injury, may spend additional [TR] to automatically inflict Maimed Critical Injury. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":14000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"73jgjzgj3fxlcbow"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"ypilpw85msqsq9jy"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VARPCRYST"}},"_id":"i54zyhemQlG31iqX"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Speeder Bike/Swoop","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Speeder Bike/Swoop[h3]\n      Converts a speeder bike or swoop to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 </div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 </div><div>Adds a forward light repeating blaster </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARABIKE"}},"_id":"iECDbQrkvNt8zDGZ"}
{"name":"Environmental Adaption Kit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Environmental Adaption Kit[h3]\n      The varied and often hazardous environments found throughout the galaxy have a tendency to hinder and harm even the sturdiest, most well-built pieces of equipment. Ranged weapons, especially energy weapons like blasters, are particularly susceptible to environmental damage. Dirt, dust and sand can scratch fog lenses, reducing a blaster beam's cohesion and therefore its range and damage potential. Moisture can collect in barrels and receivers, corroding galven circuitry or rusting bolts and strikers. More exotic environments can wear away at weapons with heat, caustic gases, or damaging ionization.\n[P]To combat these dangers, most weapon and weapon accessory manufacturers produce Environmental adaption kits. Primarily just collections of seals and protective covers, these kits grant a weapon an added layer of protection against the wear and tear of regular use in hostile environments. While some are for general use, most of these kits are designed for specific environments: dusty, cold, caustic, etc. Environmental adaptation kits can be attached to any ranged weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models and manufacturers.\n[P][I]Note: If this kit is for a specific environment, rename the kit to specify the environment.[i][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 50 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Prevents a weapon from breaking down as a result of a specific type of environment. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENVADAPTKIT"}},"_id":"iGM8gzzCFrzbeih8"}
{"name":"Force-Attuned Resonator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Force-Attuned Resonator[h3]\n[P]When the Jedi artificer Sokiro Terebin set about reproducing the crystalline, force-attuned resonaters from the blasters she had unearthed at Site-145 on Filata, she first had to solve some numerous technical challenges. During this time, she created a number of internal resonaters that could be housed within a weapon the effectiveness of different technologies the ancients might have used. Though she meticulously recorded all of her efforts to create resonators that could be activated only by Force sensitives, the Empire's tumultuous rise to power led the destruction of many repositories of Jedi lore. During Terebin's lifetime, few Jedi considered these weapons to be serious armaments, but in the dark times of Imperial rule, some Force sensitives might find having a blaster that most people can't operate to be practical. The blueprints persist in certain scholastic records, and the aspiring Force sensitives might be able  to make a use of them. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Light) or Ranged (Heavy) weapon that has a trigger.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Must possess Force Rating 1+ to operate this weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":8,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"FORRESON"}},"_id":"iGO0SvGjjRAPW89p"}
{"name":"Integrated Illuminator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Integrated Illuminator[h3]\n[P]Operating in darkness is never ideal, but there are several ways to compensate for one's lack of night vision. The simplest, perhaps, is to integrate a simple spotlight, similar in most respects to a high-power glow rod, along the length of a ranged weapon's barrel. In addition to providing illumination in dark conditions, high-powered spotlights have the potential to blind enemies. This attachment can be applied to any ranged weapon that could logically benefit from a spotlight.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Removes up to [SE][SE] due to darkness on targets within short range. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,{"_id":"duT5sdvONggGT6Vi","name":"Disorient Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Disorient can daze an opponent. When Disorient is triggered, the target is disoriented (see page 218) for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Disorient rating. A disoriented target adds [SE] to all skill checks he performs.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DISORIENT"}},"id":"bz4arrqtch7vzpxy"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTILL"}},"_id":"igRDXBaxEaPX8d1y"}
{"name":"(AD-15) Hyperdrive Class 4 Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hyperdrive Class 4 Module for AD-15[h3]\nInstalling a hyperdrive, even a relatively low-grade one, in an AD-15 takes up a good deal of space inside of the craft, but also allows it to operate independently. For many mercenaries, bounty hunters and other frequent travelers, such an upgrade is well worth the cost.\n[P][H4]<font size=1>Please see page 63 of the Special Modifications Sourcebook for details.</font>[h4][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Class 4 Hyperdrive Mod - Add Class 4 Hyperdrive </div><div>Add astromech droid socket. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"0HibaLcBPREmA3Wv","name":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of .5 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVESUB5"}},"id":"ic4e5fc43zzb9iaa"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"USERATTACH3"}},"_id":"iqPvNZdM6DGtN4iE"}
{"name":"Jury Rigged (Armor)","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Jury Rigged (Armor)[h3]\n\nThe character chooses one personal weapon or piece of armor per rank of Jury Rigged. He may increase the damage of the weapon by one; decrease the Advantage cost on its Critical, or any single other effect by one to a minimum of one; or increase armor's ranged or melee defense by one. Alternatively, he can decrease the encumbrance of the item by two to a minimum of one. The bonus only applies so long as the character is using the item. If the item is ever loss or destroyed, the character may apply Jury Rigged to a new personal weapon or piece or armor.","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"HktIT1I433GplecZ","name":"Increase Melee Defense Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"Increases Melee Defense value by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"armor","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MELEEDEFADD"}},"id":"m5tu07z1rbkvfr4n"},{"_id":"bBX2AURAAn8diUG7","name":"Increase Ranged Defense Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"Increases Ranged Defense value by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"armor","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RANGEDEFADD"}},"id":"m