{"name":"Hyperdrive Class 4 Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hyperdrive Class 4 Module[h3]\nCompared to sublight engines, hyperdrive modules require less thrust ducting and other complex integration work. Thus, they are handled as a starship attachment.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 82 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Class 4 Hyperdrive Mod - Add Class 4 Hyperdrive </div><div>Add astromech droid socket (starfighters only). </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":6000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"0HibaLcBPREmA3Wv","name":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of .5 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVESUB5"}},"id":"mxp3y4uok4m0e6e2"},null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"FOHYPER4"}},"_id":"mMXPIjm0Efl7natz"}
{"name":"Passive Foliage Suit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Passive Foliage Suit[h3]\nFor those operating in the wilds, sometimes the simplest camoflage methods are the best. Given this, it's not surprising that hunters and other individuals who spend a lot of time in the wilderness often use passive foliage suits. These suits have patches of synthetic greenery designed to mimic natural flora. Clusters of open tie-lines also allow wearers to easily attach local foliage to the suit, allowing them to alter their camouflage when the surroundings change. This attachment can be applied to any armor that could logically integrate the necessary patches and tie-lines.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various types.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add [SE] to Perception or Vigilance checks made to detect a character wearing this armor in appropriate environment. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":75,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PASSFOLSUIT"}},"_id":"mQwoMlQCdJESSKVb"}
{"name":"Tracking System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Tracking System[h3]\nThrough a series of specialized computer systems and sensors, this attachment collects and processes data from the wearer's surroundings to follow and predict the movements of designated targets. A heads-up display integrated into a helmet or visor feeds the wearer this information onto an overly of their surroundings. The systems are not limited to local targets, either, but can follow signals from distant communicators or tags and process optimal routes towards them. Tracking systems in armor are typically designed to operate alongside similar equipment, and are often able to integrate with other systems to a greater effect than the sum of their parts. This attachment can be installed on any armor.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Galkor Solutions W-7 Locator Array.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As a maneuver, may designate a target for tracking.  Only one target may be designated at a time. </div><div>Upgrade the ability of checks to track a designated target once. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"TRACKSYS"}},"_id":"maoYaNamRqUsHwsg"}
{"name":"Galven Pattern Resequencing","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Galven Pattern Resequencing[h3]\nSome Alliance operatives would gladly trade a little\nreliability in exchange for the stopping power necessary to penetrate Imperial armor. This makes the Galven pattern resequencing a popular upgrade among\ntroops in service of the Rebellion. By focusing the Galven pattern into a tighter wavelength, more energy is\npacked into each blaster bolt, which increases damage output. Unfortunately, the added workload on\nthe blaster’s tiny circuitry makes the weapon much\nmore prone to failure. This attachment can only be\nused with blaster pistols and heavy blaster pistols.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 </div><div>Adds automatic [TH][TH] to all combat checks made using this weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"tbtbqgha3c881l98"},{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"n4wjc7z9maaagk97"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GALPATRES"}},"_id":"mitxp0kRErY4cjE3"}
{"name":"VX Hands-Free Weapon","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]VX Hands-Free Weapon[h3]\n\nBy modifying his armor to mount one or more weapons, a spacer can keep his hands free for whatever unexpected needs might arise in combat—or just to carry more weapons. While few weapons are intended for such use, most can be modified to mount on a properly-equipped suit of armor. The difficult part is modifying the weapon so that it can be aimed and fired hands-free. Methods range from voice-activation to a pressure-sensitive glove activated by certain hand movements to a direct neural link. Such systems almost always incorporate a sophisticated targeting computer or retinal tracking mechanism. The most common location for the weapon mount is on the shoulder, though other areas are possible. \n\n[P]A weapon must also be modified in order to be armor-mounted, requiring one hard point. This attachment can mount any Ranged (Light) or Ranged (Heavy) weapon with an Encumbrance of 4 or less, subject to the GM's discretion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Mounts single weapon on armor.  User can aim and fire without using his hands.  Use \"Notes\" feature to specify which weapon is mounted. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HANDSFREEWEAP"}},"_id":"mjhG0KUaRCF0jI0R"}
{"name":"Light Armored Hull","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Light Armored Hull[h3]\nThe improved armor in this hull increases survivability.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 83 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FoiIrJw9E5Rj1mtN","name":"Increase Armor Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Armor value by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ARMORADD"}},"id":"za22j6hl9817ymuw"},{"_id":"P75gU7FhziudROeP","name":"Increases Encumbrance Capacity by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Encumbrance Capacity by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCCADDSIL"}},"id":"jed8ojwrk9r6e4tz"},{"_id":"lY51wtno6V2QsEZM","name":"Increase Passenger Capacity by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Passenger Capacity by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PASSADDSIL"}},"id":"gk2sy9e0s3e1jfxh"},{"_id":"qzOIl6xENHjd36pO","name":"Increase Hull Trauma by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Hull Trauma by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HULLADDSIL"}},"id":"udvyxfdc08kr1htv"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRAFTHULLLTARMOR"}},"_id":"n3nbwVyIlxm64jkA"}
{"name":"Integrated Ascension Gear","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Integrated Ascension Gear[h3]\nIncorporating a grapnel launcher, line, clips and other climbing and rappelling equipment directly into a set of armor ensures that the user is always prepared to ascend or descend sheer surfaces in a hurry. Whether to escape from pursuers, follow a target, infiltrate a secure building or exfiltrate from a dangerous situation, ascension gear  can prove invaluable in a variety of situations. In addition, having the grapnel and line integrated directly into one's armor provides a high degree of safety and security. This attachment can be applied to any armor.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] TaggeCo Integrated Ascension Unit, VargeCorp ClimbAll Armor.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 57 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As an action, may make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Ranged (Light) check[b] to secure grappling hook to an object within medium range and reel in cord. </div><div>May pull another character aloft by making an [B]Easy ([DI]) Athletics check[b]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":350,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"INTASCGEAR"}},"_id":"n6Zk3Yx4TQel2cY0"}
{"name":"Slugthrower Suppressor","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Slugthrower Suppressor[h3]\nSuppressors are used by assassins and sharpshooters to make their weapons quieter and more difficult to detect when firing. Similar to energy dampers used to silence blasters, suppressors clip or screw onto the end of a weapon's barrel, redirecting sound and escaping gases to reduce the noise and muzzle flash a slugthrower produces when fired. While they don't make the weapon completely silent they do dramatically reduce its report, making a shooter more difficult to detect. The major downside of using a suppressor is that in reducing the weapon's report it also lowers the speed at which a round travels, diminishing the weapon's damage in the process. Suppressors can only be used on Ranged (Light) and Ranged (Heavy) slugthrower weapons.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Czerka Mk. I Suppressor, SoroSuub \"Whisperflite\" Slugthrower Silencer.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Savage Spirits[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds [SE][SE] to Perception or Vigilance checks made to locate a concealed shooter firing a silenced slugthrower. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SLUGSUPP"}},"_id":"n6kzQWpERwGkDBja"}
{"name":"Optical Camouflage System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Optical Camouflage System[h3]\n\nPopular with both military scouts and assassins, optical camouflage systems are a wonder of modern stealth technology. Using a series of phased array optical projectors combined with sound baffling equipment and thermal and radiation shielding, Merr-Sonn's \"Ghost\" OCS can render a wearer nearly invisible to the naked eye. The PAO projectors allow the wearer to blend in with his surroundings by mimicking them, similar to an animal with active camouflage abilities, and the different radiation shields hide the wearers body heat as well as any electromagnetic radiation from other sensors or communications gear. For all of its utility, however, this system is incredibly fragile and is not recommended for combat. This attachment can be equipped on any type of armor, but is nearly useless on laminate and plastoid heavy armor, which is often too bulky and loud to mask properly. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BioTech \"Flicker\" Displacement Field, Atlas Corp \"Smokescreen\" Stealth System, Merr-Sonn \"Ghost\" Optical Camouflage System.","attributes":{"Stealth":{"mod":"Stealth","modtype":"Skill Rank","value":0}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"OCS"}},"_id":"nDsopHlTeE8I7gwX"}
{"name":"Hilt Masking Kit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hilt Masking Kit[h3]\nOften, openly carrying a lightsaber causes undue comment and notice. Owners of such a weapon may have many reasons to want a subtler presence, yet still keep their lightsaber by their side. Perhaps they must enter an area known to be under heavy Imperial scrutiny, or the mere presence of an obvious weapon may sour delicate negotiations. Whatever the reason, Force users may make use of a hilt-masking kit to disguise their weapon.\n[P]Just as each lightsaber is unique to its user, so too is each hilt-masking kit; there is no \"universal\" kit. The needs of the moment, or the personal tastes of the Force user, dictate what form each kit takes. Sometimes a hilt may be disguised as a cane; at other time it could be hidden as a part of a more mundane weapon like a blaster rifle; it may even appear to be something much more ordinary, like  a pair of microbinoculars. The cost, rarity, and encumbrance of a hilt-masking kit are the same as that of the item it is meant to look like. Whatever form the masking takes, it provides two important qualities: it looks as little like a lightsaber as possible, and it provides quick and easy access to the full weapon when needed.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 50 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds [FA][FA] to any attempt to find or identify the lightsaber as a lightsaber. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HILTMASK"}},"_id":"nN2wgNimhkZczLBW"}
{"name":"Custom Grip","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Custom Grip[h3]\nA skilled tinkerer can tailor a weapon to perfectly fit its weilder's hand. A custom grip is crafted to uniquely match its owner, allowing the weapon to act as an extension of the wielder's body. While the weapon fits perfectly in the hands of its owner, others who try to use it find the grip uncomfortable or the weapon off-balance. A finely customized frip is the hallmark of a master weaponsmith. This attachment can be applied to any weapon with a handle.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Remove Setback Mod - Remove [SETBACK] from all attack checks when using this weapon </div><div>Anyone other than owner adds [SE][SE] to combat checks using this weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"p6v4vd6w8abvamjm"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CUSTGRIP"}},"_id":"nSsW1ewqoaZfKX25"}
{"name":"Reinforced Engine Cowlings","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reinforced Engine Cowlings[h3]\nPart of the thrill of Podracing is the near certainty of collisions, for many enthusiasts, a good race is measured by how many crashes occurred, not how fast the winner ran the circuit. Given the nature of these races, many pilots view it as foregone that they will be involved in collisions, no matter what effort they might take to avoid them. This leads to some adopting reinforced plating for their engines, the better to withstand \"accidental\" impacts as they occur during a race.\n[P]More tactically-minded pilots take this even further adding ridges, struts, and vanes designed to appear ornamental or to a aid in aerodynamics, but instead intended to cushion impacts when their vehicle rams into another. That those pilots who are frequently involved in collisions and still manage to cheat death race after race, garner large amounts of fame (and credits) certainly has a strong bearing on other pilots decision to adopt such modifications and alter their racing tactics accordingly.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various Models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduce Critical Hit result from collision by 20 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PODREICOWL"}},"_id":"nUWxodn43WwwOPRi"}
{"name":"Slave Circuit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Slave Circuit[h3]\n\nAn old shipbuilding technology perfected millennia ago, slave circuits allow ship owners to operate their ships, or various systems within their ships, via remote control. Occasionally referred to as the \"Electronic Co-Pilot\" or \"Instant Backseater,\" slave circuits run all of a ship's systems through a central system bus that can be activated and deactivated via voice command through a comlink-like device called a \"beckon call.\" Basic slave rigs allow a user to remotely activate a ship's systems and bring it to complete operational readiness, or to shut those systems down and lock out all users until a security code is entered. More advanced models allow the user to call the ship to his present location, and even allow it to fight its way there with moderate success. While popular in many circles, slave circuits are often mistrusted by ship owners. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Corellian Engineering Corporation \"Savant\" Ship Slave Rig, Incom ST-9x.4 \"Backseater\" Starfighter Slave System.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Stay on Target[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows a ship or vehicle to be activated or deactivated by remote control. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":10000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SLAVECIRC"}},"_id":"nUXfmPsJYz7nEMPa"}
{"name":"Proximity Detonator","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Proximity Detonator[h3]\nAlthough certain models of mines include proximity detonators as standard, some desire this feature for grenades and other explosive devices. A proximity detonator adds an alternative trigger method: rather than detonating via a timer or on impact, the grenade only detonates when it detects the movement of a being or creature nearby. With the addition of a proximity detonator, a simple frag grenade becomes a deadly trap. A well-placed concussion grenade can incapacitate an entire squad of pursuing stormtroopers, giving Rebels better chances for escape. This weapon attachment can be applied to any grenade or explosive device.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Weapon detonates when a silhouette 1 or higher creature comes within short or engaged range, as determined when placed. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":120,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PROXDET"}},"_id":"nc7JIzOQqqaLLoWT"}
{"name":"Forearm Grip","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Forearm Grip[h3]\n\nLittle more than a vertical handgrip affixed below the barrel of a rifle-sized weapon, forearm grips are a popular modification among mercenaries, designed to give the user better control over the weapon. This Attachment can only be used on rifles (but not heavy rifles) and carbines.\n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Galactic Arms Model 94 Forearm Grip, Dolmax 14A Detachable Pistol Grip, Merr-Sonn AG44S Ergonomic Tactical Foregrip.<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases the additional difficulty of making Ranged (Heavy)\n          checks with this weapon while engaged to an\n          additional [DIFFICULTY] (rather than [DIFFICULTY][DIFFICULTY]). </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"8073mpvtluryesx7"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"FAG"}},"_id":"ng17ufHseNCqZVDv"}
{"name":"(AD-1S) Fine-Tuned Microthrusters","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Fine-Tuned Microthrusters for AD-1S[h3]\nThe AD-1 S is already a relatively maneuverable craft, but installing and personalizing an array of small vector adjustment thrusters allows it to compete with many of the galaxy's nimblest starfighters.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Handling Mod - Increases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"bNGCMxHyQem1bD7S","name":"Increases Handling Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Handling by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HANDLINGADD"}},"id":"dkvalt2gi3fixqeo"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD1SMICROTHRUST"}},"_id":"o2BGON1pQOFem17n"}
{"name":"Reactive Plating","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reactive Plating[h3]\n[P]Reactive plating is a modification that attaches small explosive panels to the armors exterior plates. When hit by an attack, the explosives are designed to detonate outward, absorbing some of the attacks kinetic energy with the counter-explosion. It is not typically used on a personal scale, but microrepulsors and other, similar technologies allow it to be integrated into certain heavier varieties of personal armor and to function at considerable effectiveness without harming the wearer in the process. Employed properly, reactive armor can even deflect or dampen blows from weapons that would cleave through other defenses, like lightsabers. Besides the considerable weight it adds to any set of armor, an unfortunate side-effect of reactive armor is that it destroys itself as it protects the individual inside. It causes the armor to degrade far more rapidly than it would have otherwise would, which means that the wearer must repair it far more often. This attachment can only be applied to armor with a soak of 2 or higher.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 Count 4</div><div>First time wearer is hit each encounter, reduce damage by 10.  After, armor suffers minor damage and must be repaired to function again. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"FIcN4TkIpZPNEqah","name":"Decreases Encumbrance Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Decrease Encumbrance by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCSUB"}},"id":"sn3oygjxarhgr5d5"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REACPLAT"}},"_id":"o3nW0IUbazMANBy7"}
{"name":"Holo Converter","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Holo Converter[h3]\nHolo converters are common holo scrambling devices that allow users to alter a holoprojector's outgoing signal. Using powerful alteration technologies, holo converters allow users to change their species, age, gender, and any other identifying features on camera to hide their identity. This can be used with any holographic recording/projecting device, and the converter can store four different alter egos in its database. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows a user to create disguises within holographic recording/projecting systems </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":600,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HOLOCONVERTER"}},"_id":"o8z3COfZPa3YldGB"}
{"name":"Overcharged Shields","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Overcharged Shields[h3]\nMost shield arrays have the potential to generate a stronger field. However, this has the potential to damage the array itself, leaving the ship with no protection. Despite the risks. some shipboard engineers modify the shields to allow for increased output with only a few moments' tinkering in the midst of combat, banking on the extra defense to allow them to escape or defeat the enemy before suffering the repercussions.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 61 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Once per encounter, can make an [B]Average([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] to overcharge shields, adding 2 to all defense zones for 1 round + 1 round per [AD].  If [TH][TH] or [DE] is rolled, shields burn out and stop working until repaired. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"OVERCHSHIELD"}},"_id":"omWk0SWZi2FSnYVU"}
{"name":"Handling Upgrades","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Handling Upgrades[h3]\nPodracer handling upgrades encompass a wide array of systems and technologies designed to make Podracers easier to pilot. These upgrades can be tiny, variable pitch jets and movable repulsor fields to brute force counterweights that slide into special compartments to counteract inertia. While such upgrades do increase a Podracer's handling capabilities, no amount of modification is likely to likely to make the exceedingly fast and fragile race vehicle easy enough to handle for a human pilot.\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Incom ETX Mk. I Etheric Rudder, Slayn & Korpil Vitus-Series Attitude Thrusters, Bespid Motors PinPoint II Targeted Repulsor Generator.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Handling Mod - Increases Handling by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"bNGCMxHyQem1bD7S","name":"Increases Handling Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Handling by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HANDLINGADD"}},"id":"fwlecmt4enpcdaor"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PODHAND"}},"_id":"orKQQ63K6fut3HQU"}
{"name":"Comlink Bug","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Comlink Bug[h3]\nComlink bugs are tiny listening devices implanted into an otherwise normal comlink. When active, they allow an operator to listen in on whatever is being broadcast over a specific comlink. These devices detect both incoming and outgoing signals and can record entire conversations. As they are active listening devices, comlink bugs can be detected with proper equipment, such as a surveillance scanner. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Broadcasts all incoming and outgoing signals from a comlink to a remote listener at medium range. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":150,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"COMLINKBUG"}},"_id":"oyLDXLRLDZmA254y"}
{"name":"(AD-15) Shield Generator Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shield Generator Module  forAD-15[h3]\nMany fightercraft lack shields, including most of the Galactic Empire's TIE Series. Of course, many pilots view going into battle without shields as a sure sign of a death wish, Soldiers of fortune and others who fight for credits rather than ideology tend to prefer the thought of living to get paid to the prospect of dying gloriously for some intangible ideal, and so the highly customizable AD-15 can be fitted with shield generators to improve its durability.\n[P][H4]<font size=1>Please see page 63 of the Special Modifications Sourcebook for details.</font>[h4][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 63 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Defense Zone Mod - Increases Defense Zone by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":8000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Q5hF8yx2DdQIR38p","name":"Increase Defense Zone Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases Defense Zone by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DEFZONEADD"}},"id":"yafhg0tyo9bgu4f3"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD15SHIELD"}},"_id":"pC9hcoqAQKybjEnU"}
{"name":"Ion Drive Array","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Ion Drive Array[h3]\nIon drive arrays provide excellent speed as well as plenty of opportunities for modification.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 82 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 Count 4</div><div>Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod - Increases System Strain by Silhouette Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"TfqDzg8fQd6VBG9V","name":"Increase Speed Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Speed by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPEEDADD"}},"id":"23oqp0ogg2ht011i"},{"_id":"WzEhZZQs7ZiJaqsh","name":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by Silhouette","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADDSIL"}},"id":"0zvd4l1iirwb48yw"},{"_id":"26uEwvWhVxzeWHvY","name":"Increase Forward Defense Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Forward Defense by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier