{"name":"Predictive Targeting Array","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Predictive Targeting Array[h3]\n\nWhen making an auto-fire attack with the ship's auto-blasters, do not increase the difficulty of the attack by one.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Suns of Fortune[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When making auto-fire attack, do not increase difficulty by 1. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PTA"}},"_id":"pOzAh86UIxwiOhOq"}
{"name":"Dual-Phase Modification","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Dual-Phase Modification[h3]\n\nConsidered antiquated and outdated by the time of the Clone Wars, the dual-phase modification is an artifact of an older, more violent time. Designed to catch an opponent off guard, this modification allows the wielder to change the length of a lightsaber's blade with the push of a button. This causes an opponent's guard to falter momentarily as he adjusts to the new blade length, allowing the Jedi to press the advantage while his opponent is confused. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>May change blade length once per encounter as an incidental.  Next attack that turn ignores target's melee defense. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DUALPHASE"}},"_id":"plouXZuukcjHypC7"}
{"name":"Oversized External Weapons Mount","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Oversized External Weapons Mount[h3]\n\nThe search for ever-increasing firepower often leads to the installation of weapons systems larger than were intended for a given vehicle. The oversized weapons mount is a custom-built rack enabling the vehicle to carry a weapon meant for one silhouette larger than the vehicle itself. However, the CM is the final arbiter of feasibility of such designs and may impose additional penalties for the weapon's use.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Vehicle can carry a weapon for craft 1 silhouette larger Mod - Vehicle can carry a weapon for craft 1 silhouette larger </div><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 Count 4</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"OEWM"}},"_id":"qD7NbBatn9UPg93y"}
{"name":"Gunnery Droid Brain","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Gunnery Droid Brain[h3]\nMuch more than a simple targeting computer, a specialized droid brain can be installed on a ship to operate its weapons independently or assist a sentient gunner. Although GoCorp's CD-14c model continues to prove popular with Technicians who want their ship to defend itself when necessary, some users complain of the droid's overly hostile antagonistic behavior. GoCorp continues to deny rumors of so-called \"unanticipated activations\". This attachment can be applied to any vehicle or starship.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] GoCorp's CD-14c[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 66 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add a droid brain with Gunnery 2 and Agility 0. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":7000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GUNNBRAIN"}},"_id":"qggEUZQWxwPya1I6"}
{"name":"Walking Stick Hilt Disguise","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Walking Stick Hilt Disguise[h3]\nOften, particularly elderly Jedi constructed their lightsabers in the body of a sturdy walking stick. If the blade is a Jedi's life, why shouldn't it make things a little easier? The pure utility of this practice fell out of favor with the Jedi Order. Most elderly Jedi did not, after all, survive the Purge. Survivors, though, found a similar technique could hide their weapons in plain sight. This concealment does come with a cost. The awkward size and inconsistent weighting often interferes with use in heated combat.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Unlimited Power[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Unless ignited, must pass [B]Formidable ([DI][DI][DI][DI][DI]) Perception[b] or [B]Vigilance check[b] to notice it is not a regular walking stick. </div><div>Inaccurate Quality - Inaccurate weapons are weapons of a shoddy or inferior construction which means they are less likely to be accurate or precise. Alternatively, the weapon’s nature may inhibit accuracy. Inaccurate weapons add [SE] to the attacker’s dice pool equal to their Inaccurate rating. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"WALKHILT"}},"_id":"qoODOp95AYzwgEwO"}
{"name":"Reinforced Gauntlets","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Reinforced Gauntlets[h3]\nAdditional armor plating on the hands is a valuable upgrade for those who wear heavier armor, as well as those who do welding jobs on starships and desire to keep all of their fingers. Not only does such extra plating provide additional protection, but it ensures that the wearer is never unarmed; after all, the gauntlets are heavy enough to shatter bones when used to deliver a punch. It also helps protect the user's hands in case they are ever stuck closing a blast door or shocked by a loose wiring while performing battlefield repairs. This attachment can be applied to any  armor with soak 2 or higher.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>May use gauntlets as a melee weapon. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REINFGAUNT"}},"_id":"rSbSM1626OX7Qio9"}
{"name":"Shien Reverse Grip Customization","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shien Reverse Grip Customization[h3]\nPractitioners of Form V sometimes use a reverse grip on their lightsabers to assist in many of the techniques common to that form. Through a few careful adjustments to the grip and balance of their lightsabers, these practitioners can make the weapons more suited to wielding in this manner although the modifications make using a traditional grip somewhat unwieldy in the process.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None; users must custom make each lightsaber attachment.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Endless Vigil[h4]","attributes":{"Lightsaber":{"mod":"Lightsaber","modtype":"Skill Add Threat","value":1}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SHIENREVGRIP"}},"_id":"rSzT6oL0iQOBAhtc"}
{"name":"Vaksai Modification Package","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Vaksai Modification Package[h3]\nA pre-fabricated kit of starship modifications sold by TransGalMeg for their Kihraxz modular light starfighter, this package includes upgraded engines and flight control systems, a heavier weapons loadout, and a higher-out-put shield generator. While expensive, those Kihraxz pilots who can afford it swear by the added surivability and firepower it provides, allowing the fighter to engage heavier targets and emerge victorious.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Vaksai Modification Package.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 60 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Sets Armor Mod - Sets Armor value Count 3</div><div>Sets Handling Mod - Sets Handling </div><div>Sets Aft Defense Mod - Sets Aft Defense </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":45000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"XknqTBBtorLWs9dR","name":"Replace Light Blaster Cannons with Light Laser Cannons Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Replace Light Blaster Cannons with Light Laser Cannons","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VAKSAI"}},"id":"akkz6tkur8tph5lh"},{"_id":"26uEwvWhVxzeWHvY","name":"Increase Forward Defense Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Forward Defense by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ADDDEFFORE"}},"id":"ksr9ae2cwmpocpha"},{"_id":"kfUbhrn82nL9vXku","name":"Increases System Strain Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADD"}},"id":"vet5b9etlvierb5u"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VAKSAI"}},"_id":"rVKkHoVJHEYoZSt8"}
{"name":"Under-Barrel Grapnel Launcher","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Under-Barrel Grapnel Launcher[h3]\nOften seen among mercenary and special operations forces, an under-barrel grapnel launcher provides a quick way to scale sheer surfaces in the midst of a combat situation or during a covert infiltration. A durasteel hook, possibly with a mono-molecular point, can find purchase on nearly any surface, while a spool of synthrope or liquid cable provides up to 100 meters of length. A powerful motor automatically retracts the cable, pulling the user up - though holding onto any passengers who are along for the ride is a more difficult matter, and requires some effort on part of the user. This attachment can be used with any Ranged (Light) or Ranged (Heavy) weapons that could logically have a grapnel launcher mounted on it.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Merr-Sonn KR-2 Auxiliary Grapnel, TaggeCo \"Skysailer\" Grapnel Launcher[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 56 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As an action, may make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Ranged (Light) check[b] to secure grappling hook to an object within medium range and reel in cord. </div><div>May pull another character aloft by making an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Athletics check[b]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GRAPNEL"}},"_id":"rjfO0BxygsuJTGWZ"}
{"name":"Pistol Hilt","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Pistol Hilt[h3]\nWhile the Jedi of old disdained blasters, modern Force users often need every advantage they can get. By adding a customized secondary emitter to a lightsaber hilt, the wielder can release the energies of her weapon at a distance in a manner similar to that of a blaster bolt. Without the focused field produced by a regular lightsaber emitter, the beam rapidly loses coherency and stopping power, producing only a short-range stun bolt. A lightsaber used in this manner, though might not even be recognized for what it is, appearing to be an unusual or custom model of pistol instead of one of the legendary weapons of the Jedi. This additional layer of cover could mean as much protection as the new capabilities of the weapon.\n[P]The user must spend a maneuver to switch from one weapon mode to the other lightsaber function to pistol function, for example.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None; users must custom make each lightsaber attachment.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Includes a built-in blaster pistol. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PISTOLHILT"}},"_id":"rw1Fw7Ah1HsPXAsz"}
{"name":"Oxygen Unit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Oxygen Unit[h3]\nThis unit can provide an additional\ntwelve hours of oxygen when connected to any\nrebreather, breath mask, or environmentally sealed suit[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Forged in Battle[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds additional twelve hours of oxygen when connected to any rebreather, breath mask, or sealed suit. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":300,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MILMODBACKOXY"}},"_id":"s9Y4ahUonKtbhN4N"}
{"_id":"sAUh0Xs1UZMHyuOu","name":"Paired Weapons","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paired Weapons[h3]\n\nMany Gunslingers wield a pistol in each hand, and some flashy pirates and other scoundrels even prefer to pair a blade with a pistol. This weapon modification balances a pair of weapons, allowing the wielder to use them in perfect tandem. This attachment can only be applied to one-handed weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Custom variants.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduce [AD] required to hit with second weapon when two-weapon fighting by 1. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":300,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0,"isrestricted":false},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PAIREDW","loaded":false}}}
{"name":"Barab Ingot","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Barab Ingot[h3]\n\nRare variants of kyber crystals unique to the heavily irradiated world Barab I, home of the saurian Barabel people, Barab ingots are among the various crystals used in lightsabers. Found in small clusters in mountainous regions, Barab ingots are hot to the touch and glow with a fierce inner light. When installed in a lightsaber, they create a searing, fiery blade that bums so fiercely that it nearly loses cohesion. A lightsaber with an installed Barab ingot is slightly radioactive, and with a particularly good or lucky strike can set a target alight. A Barab ingot is a lightsaber crystal.\n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 8</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 3</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Burn Quality - Weapons with Burn inflict damage over time. If the attack is successful, the target continues to suffer the weapon’s base damage for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Burn rating. Damage is applied at the start of each of the target’s actions.\n\n[P]A victim might be able to stop the damage by rolling around on the ground and making an Agility check as an Coordination check action. This is an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Coordination check[b] on hard surfaces such as the hall of a spaceship, or an [B]Easy ([DI]) Coordination check[b] on grass or soft ground. Jumping into a body of water stops the damage immediately. Both situations assume the flame is from actual combustion rather than a chemical reaction. With the latter, there is usually little the victim can do. </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":15000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"UxVhTRp64V0tvmhT","name":"Burn Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Weapons with Burn inflict damage over time. If the attack is successful, the target continues to suffer the weapon’s base damage for a number of rounds equal to the weapon’s Burn rating. Damage is applied at the start of each of the target’s actions.\n\n[P]A victim might be able to stop the damage by rolling around on the ground and making an Agility check as an Coordination check action. This is an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Coordination check[b] on hard surfaces such as the hall of a spaceship, or an [B]Easy ([DI]) Coordination check[b] on grass or soft ground. Jumping into a body of water stops the damage immediately. Both situations assume the flame is from actual combustion rather than a chemical reaction. With the latter, there is usually little the victim can do.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BURN"}},"id":"bn1wcq1z0fslthi0"},{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"wxzvfkn245pbfe46"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BARABLS"}},"_id":"sGjk8N2qqLqcvN8E"}
{"name":"Pommel Cap","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Pommel Cap[h3]\nForce users, especially those walking a path closely attuned to the light side of the Force, often seek non-lethal means for incapacitating their opponents. The pommel cap provides just such a solution. The pommel cap is a small, weighted knob or other similar piece attached to the base of a lightsaber's hilt. The increased weight and reinforcement provided by the pommel cap make pommel strikes with the lightsaber more effective, and less likely to damage the lightsaber itself, than a strike with a bare hilt. The pommel cap not only enhances the ability of a Force user to provide a stunning blow, but it can also be used to store small items of necessity-most often an additional backup power cell, though any number of small items can prove useful to a Force user in need. The pommel cap screws into the base of a lightsaber, and competent wielders often incorporate its use into their fighting style as a matter of course. This attachment can be applied to lightsabers or any Melee weapon with a hilt.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 51 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Stun Quality - A weapon with Stun causes strain to the target. When the Stun quality is activated, it inflicts strain equal to the weapon’s Stun rating. Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"aDvHhRgItEzT7XHl","name":"Stun Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Stun causes strain to the target. When the Stun quality is activated, it inflicts strain equal to the weapon’s Stun rating.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"STUN"}},"id":"72uq3e0rrkykuzvt"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"POMMELCAP"}},"_id":"sHFph95x4hhbYnEj"}
{"name":"Optimized Energy Cell","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Optimized Energy Cell[h3]\nAn optimized energy cell or expanded gas reserve allows a blaster to achieve a much higher number of shots before needing to reload, thanks to more efficient use of resources. Such modifications are often the result of excessive tinkering, rather than off-the-shelf models. This attachment can be applied to any energy weapon.\n[P][B]Models Include:[p] Czerka Arms Model 4 Expanded Gas Reservoir, Blastech X-3 Extended Energy Cell[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 54 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When GM spends [DE] or [TH] to cause the weapon to run out of ammo, it requires an additional [TH]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"OPTENERGCELL"}},"_id":"sUvCQub69Jw0CRx7"}
{"name":"Repulsorlift Enhancement","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Repulsorlift Enhancement[h3]\n\nA repulsorlift enhancement increases the output of a standard airspeeder's repulsorlift engine considerably. Vehicles with this upgrade deplete their fuel cells at a dramatically increased rate. Since most races are relatively short in duration, and those that are longer have the opportunity to use a pit crew to recharge their cells, this makes them an extremely popular choice with most racing teams. Installing this attachment requires an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. Repulsor enhancements may only be attached to vehicles of silhouette 2 or lower.\n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Jewel of Yavin[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As a maneuver, suffer 1 system strain to add +1 maximum speed for one round. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REPENH"}},"_id":"stQb9KOTdZKQ2XIC"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Landspeeder","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Landspeeder[h3]\n      Converts a landspeeder to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Handling Mod - Decreases Handling by 1 </div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 3</div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 2</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 </div><div>Adds a medium laser turret </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARALAND"}},"_id":"t2LAbbd9p8tXLtLx"}
{"name":"Shaped Nozzle","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Shaped Nozzle[h3]\nBy adding a metal cone to an ion thruster, a Technician can dramatically increase its potency as a weapon, focusing the energy into a sharp beam rather than letting it disperse in a wide arc.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 45 - Special Modifications[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":75,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":5},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"nt43y4lkjni4s1xl"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"IONTHRUSTSHAPEDNOZ"}},"_id":"t7pZalzUo7GxgWo3"}
{"name":"Slicing Computer","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Slicing Computer[h3]\nAlthough most starships include sophisticated computers and comm equipment capable of slicing into the systems of enemy vessels, such electronic warfare tactics are usually overlooked in favor of more  conventional attacks. However, some crews undertake efforts to upgrade their on-board systems for precisely the kind of work. With the right equipment  and software, a skilled computer expert can become one of the most valuable crew members in a space battle. Many Technicians continue to tinker with and add to the ship's computer systems over time, sometimes to the confusion and frustration of other crew. This attachment can be applied to any starship.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various Custome Models[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 67 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Counts as slicer gear that can be used by one passenger. </div><div>Add automatic [AD] to Computers checks made to slice enemy ships' systems. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":5000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SLICCOMP"}},"_id":"tEVhr9Z21kz9yGzy"}
{"name":"Overcharged Actuating Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Overcharged Actuating Module[h3]\nAn overcharged blaster actuating module provides for a more powerful shot at the cost of a greater use of gas as well as increased wear and tear on the weapon. For some spacers, these drawbacks are worth the extra firepower. Although some kits are available for purchase many Technicians achieve the same result by scavenging parts from higher yield blaster. This attachment can be applied to any blaster pistol or carbine.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech Mk. II Actuating Module, SoroSuub BlastPro[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 </div><div>GM may spend [TH][TH] to damage weapon by one step. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":650,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"oksx0ef4nlkzmkeq"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"OVERACTMOD"}},"_id":"tRmDSJ0awVBujeul"}
{"name":"Utility Arm","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Utility Arm[h3]\nFor some species, it's a mystery how humans and their ilk get by with only two arms. In fact, it's often said that the first armor-mounted utility arm was invented by a Dug Engineer, although another tale attributes its origin to a cybernetics manufacturer with a product surplus. Regardless of its origin, the utility arm is now a common tool for Engineers and technicians of all species. Mounted on a harness or suit of combat armor, a utility arm is a mechanical appendage similar in function to many cybernetic and droid arms and ending in a manipulating \"hand.\" Although utility arms are most often used to increase workshop productivity, combatants of all kinds have found them useful on the battlefield.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 53 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Provides character with an additional mechanical arm that can function as one of the character's normal limbs. </div>","attributes":{"Mechanics":{"mod":"Mechanics","modtype":"Skill Boost","value":1}},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"UTILARM"}},"_id":"uBLrbeHWwAnPkDoN"}
{"name":"Collision Avoidance System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Collision Avoidance System[h3]\nDue to their speed and the primitive nature of their handling systems, Podracers are notoriously difficult to control. While a Podracer is blindingly fast in a straight line, getting one around corners with any accuracy or reliability is almost impossible, making crashes a common sight at races. As a result, many pilots equip their Podracers with collision avoidance systems to reduce the risk of crashes. While common collision avoidance systems are often barred from use in race series and are frowned upon by veteran racers, who consider them \"electronic nannies\".\n[BR][B]Models Include:[b] Aratech 8pz-X Constant Active Array, Fabritech \"Co-Pilot\" Adaptive Anti-Collision System, SoroSuub LX-19 Automatic Spot Thrusters.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 58 - Endless Vigil[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Reduce silhouette by 1 for purposes of determining difficulty of Piloting checks. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"COLLAVOID"}},"_id":"uMi0VAhwdlrrkKf1"}
{"name":"Armor Spikes","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Armor Spikes[h3]\n[P]While armor serves a largely defensive role for its wearers, that needn't be the rule. With the addition of spikes, blades, and other protrusions on areas covering shoulders, knuckles, feet, knees or elbows, armor can be turned into a deadly weapon of last resort. The majority of such modifications are scratch-built, though a handful o f armor manufacturers mass-produce kits for the armor sets they sell. Largely popular with criminals, mercenaries, and bounty hunters, armor spikes lend an intimidating mien to anyone equipped with them. Some professionals prefer to keep such deadly modifications concealed and retractable, and these are perhaps the most dangerous of them all. This attachment can be attached to any armor that covers the arms or legs.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Mod - Increase Encumbrance by 1 Count 2</div><div>When wearer suffers a hit from a Melee, Brawl, or Lightsaber combat check, may spend [TH][TH][TH] or [DE] to inflict one hit for 6 damage on attacker. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ARMSPIKE"}},"_id":"uN3TNgfmi2bTX3bk"}
{"name":"Cracked Crystal","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Cracked Crystal[h3]\nWith the destruction of the Jedi, the Empire has begun to horde kyber crystals for itself, capturing and controlling traditional sources of the crystals in order to develop strange new weapons. Force users must look for non-traditional sources of lightsaber crystals wherever they may be found, regardless of their condition. For example, with the destruction of the Death Star, a new, if difficult to access, source of crystals has been revealed. At the heart of the great battle stations lay a giant kyber crystal powering the lasers that destroyed Alderaan. When the Alliance destroyed Alderaan. When the Alliance destroyed the Death Star, the crystal shattered in the resulting explosion and scattered itself across the open space of the Yavin system. Most of the shards are unusable, either too small or too damaged to function, and many of them succumbed to the gravity wells of the planets of the Yavin system. However, some few remain, quietly circling among the remaining debris fields, cracked and unstable, but functional. Special lightsaber modifications are needed to use such crystals properly, but to the willing Force user, they can be made into distinctive blades. A cracked crystal is a lightsaber crystal.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 52 - Disciples of Harmony[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 7</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating Count 3</div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). Count 2</div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Vicious Quality - When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result. </div><div>If a combat check results in a [DE], GM may cause crystal to shatter. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":10,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRITSUB"}},"id":"83kcscmd4syy8685"},{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"2smluz153htol6cq"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRACKEDCRYS"}},"_id":"uSHyMKR74yxp2E8P"}
{"name":"Bowcaster Re-Cocker","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Bowcaster Re-Cocker[h3]\n\nFew weapons in the galaxy are as indicative of their users as the Wookiee bowcaster. Bowcasters require an incredible level of raw physical strength to wield, especially when loading and cocking the weapon to fire. A time-consuming and labor-intensive process, reloading a bowcaster is made much simpler and easier by use of the automatic re-cocker. This attachment entails upgrading the basic weapon with a number of power-assist systems as well as a magazine feed system that allows the weapon to fire, re-cock, and reload all in one smooth, quick movement. These attachments are only for use on Wookiee bowcasters, and they cannot be purchased; they must be built either by the owner of the bowcaster with an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] or the weaponsmith who built the weapon for him. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Edge of the Empire Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Removes reloading maneuver requirement from bowcaster. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"KKRmqHBLDdM76JVf","name":"Auto-Fire Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"A weapon with Auto-fire can be set to shoot in rapid succession and potentially spray an area with bolts, flechettes, slugs, or other types of projectiles. The advantage in using Auto-fire is that it has the chance to hit multiple targets or hit a single target multiple times.\n\n[P]Attacking with a weapon on Auto-fire is generally less accurate and the attacker must increase the difficulty of the attack check by [DI]. The user may choose to not use the Auto-fire quality on a weapon; in this case, he cannot trigger the quality but also does not suffer the aforementioned penalty.\n\n[P]If the attack hits, the attacker can trigger Auto-fire by spending [AD][AD]. Auto-fire can be triggered multiple times. Each time the attacker triggers auto-fire, it deals an additional hit to the target. Each of these counts as an additional hit from that weapon, and each hit deals base damage plus the number of uncancelled [SU] on the check.\n\n[P]These additional hits can be allocated to the target, or to other targets within range of the weapon. If the attacker wishes to hit multiple targets, he must decide to do so before making the check. Furthermore, if he wishes to hit multiple targets, his initial target must always be the target with the highest difficulty and highest defense (if this is two separate targets, the GM chooses which target is his initial target). The initial hit must always be against the initial target, subsequent hits generated can be allocated to any of the other designated targets.\n\n[P]Auto-fire weapons can also activate one Critical Injury for each hit generated on the attack per the normal cost; the Critical must target the target of the specific hit.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AUTOFIRE"}},"id":"wyo9wkfmpiulrkod"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BOWREC"}},"_id":"uXgyIxdm3yd1lcue"}
{"name":"Amphibious Modification","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Amphibious Modification[h3]\nMany worlds are covered in cast oceans and no few species have evolved in aquatic environments. For those sentients without the evolutionary adaptation of gills, specialized equipment is necessary. With the addition of a sealed helmet and oxygen (or other appropriate gas) supply, nearly any suit of armor can be converted into an amphibious suit. Retractable flippers provide humanoids with improved mobility in water and other liquids. This attachment can be applied to any armor that could logically have an air tank attached.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b]Gandorthal Atmospherics Submerible 9, BioTech Mk. II Air Supply[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 57 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Provides up to five hours of oxygen in submersive or airless environments.  Does not protect against vacuum. </div><div>Removes [SE] from physical checks due to underwater conditions. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AMPHMOD"}},"_id":"uZfaiON0OQ6aiazv"}
{"name":"Cloaking Device","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Cloaking Device[h3]\nCloaking devices are exceedingly rare and typically only fitted to starships employed in gathering intelligence assignments. Fueled with either hibridium or stygium, these power-hungry systems render a ship completely invisible. Cloaking devices are illegal to own for non-military use, a fact that is largely lost on those few criminals, smugglers, and espionage freelancers who are wealthy enough to afford them. This attachment can be applied to any starship of silhouette 3 or larger.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Sienar Fleet Systems Mk Ill Stygium Cloaking Device, Kerner Corp Multi-Phase Hibridium Stealth System.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 62 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Provides a starship with a cloaking device which can be activated or deactivated by spending a maneuver. A character must make a [B]Daunting ([DI][DI][DI]) Perception[b] or [B]Vigilance check[b] to spot a cloaked ship. Ships with an active cloaking device have their speed reduced by half (rounded up) and can not use active sensors, comms, or weapons. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":29000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":9,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CLOAKDEV"}},"_id":"v1E5P4ajaXjCrTcx"}
{"name":"Electronic Countermeasures Suite","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Electronic Countermeasures Suite[h3]\n\nDesigned to blind and deafen enemy ships, electronic countermeasures suites such as Fabritech 995 ECM system transmits a dense stream of white noise and junk data that fogs sensors and jams comms traffic within close range of the broadcasting ship. While this makes the broadcasting ship hard to see or hit, the energy required to run the ECM suite tends to put undue strain on the ship's electrical systems. Other systems have focused modes that can target specific ships at longer ranges. This may be applied to all starships and vehicles. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Fabritech 995 \"Stormcloud\" Electronic Countermeasures Suite, Miradyne 4x_Phantom Short-Range Sensor Jammer (starfighters only), KDY 220-SIG Tactical Combat Jammer (capital ships only).<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Blocks sensors within range, counting the ship's silhouette as one smaller when being fired upon. </div><div>Immediately notifies all ships in a star system or within 100 kilometers if planetside to the ship or vehicle's existence. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ECMSUITE"}},"_id":"vXJMhybWDnElw6x4"}
{"name":"Jury Rigged (Weapon)","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Jury Rigged (Weapon)[h3]\n\nThe character chooses one personal weapon or piece of armor per rank of Jury Rigged. He may increase the damage of the weapon by one; decrease the Advantage cost on its Critical, or any single other effect by one to a minimum of one; or increase armor's ranged or melee defense by one. Alternatively, he can decrease the encumbrance of the item by two to a minimum of one. The bonus only applies so long as the character is using the item. If the item is ever loss or destroyed, the character may apply Jury Rigged to a new personal weapon or piece or armor.","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"voboygb4yhgzn7x5"},{"_id":"U1TXjNzhsgSeP2Hw","name":"Decrease Critical Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Decreases the weapon's Crit Rating by 1 to a minimum of 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRITSUB"}},"id":"edvah9dxndw3ohsr"},{"_id":"MSNRaZkTXNXaiKeG","name":"Decreases Encumbrance by 2 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-all.png","data":{"description":"Decrease Encumbrance by 2","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"all","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ENCSUB2"}},"id":"8hz0wdk132qa08z2"},{"_id":"Ze1TsRYNuibD17v2","name":"Quality Takes One Less Advantage to Activate Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Quality Takes One Less [AD] to Activate","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"QUALADVSUB"}},"id":"6ewll7bmxr276w4a"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"JURYRIGGEDW"}},"_id":"veCAyLtHcu8I2kXc"}
{"name":"Amphibious Modification","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Amphibious Modification[h3]\nMost starships, speeders and other vehicles not specifically designed for it are unfit for usage underwater. Starships are typically not hydrodynamic, and hills designed for zero gravity and atmospheric use can suffer damage from deep-sea pressure. However, with the addition of turbines, modifications to the engines and reinforcement of the structure  almost any vehicle can be made seaworthy. This attachment can be applied to any vehicle or starship that can enter an atmosphere.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various Custom Models[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 65 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Vehicle can operate underwater without penalty. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AMPHIBMOD"}},"_id":"vjop85Yhu934a8EW"}
{"name":"Top-Loading Magazine","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Top-Loading Magazine[h3]\nBy switching out the standard single-bolt loading system for a cobbled-together \"magazine\" containing numerous bolts, a skilled craftsperson can increase the number of rivets the gun can place per minute dramatically. Some use this to apply rivets more rapidly to other sentient beings, though all manufacturers consider this to be \"user error\".[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 46 - Special Modifications[h4]","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":50,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RIVETGUNTOPLOAD"}},"_id":"wAk8TALHmgrI48my"}
{"name":"Space Slug Abilities","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Space Slug Abilities[h3]\nAdditional Rules for Enormous Space Slug.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Strongholds of Resistance[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>When rolling for initiative, or attacking with its Insatiable Maw, a space slug rolls a [B]Coordination skill check[b], counting as having Coordination 3 and Agility 1 ([PR][AB][AB]). </div><div>A starship of silhouette 5 or lower attacked by a space slug, regardless of whether or not the attack hit, must make a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Piloting (Space) check[b] to avoid  being swallowed.  If swallowed, ship suffers 10 hull trauma daily from being digested. </div><div>The stomach of an space slug is also generally home to mynocks, which will waste no time attacking a swallowed starship. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SPACESLUGRULES"}},"_id":"wB3kTzDmaLlZgkrH"}
{"name":"Advanced Subspace Encryption Array","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Advanced Subspace Encryption Array[h3]\n\nThe Empire's tight grip on the HoloNet forces the Rebellion to rely primarily on subspace transceivers for communications. However. subspace transceivers have a much more limited range than HoloNet transmissions, requiring frequent relays across additional networks before reaching the intended recipient. Risk of interception of a relayed transmission limits Rebel operations, forcing them to rely on courier ships and secret comm stations for long-range communication. However, ships with advanced encryption algorithms can send coded transmissions that blend with normal traffic, rendering them nearly undetectable and all but indecipherable even if they are intercepted.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Desperate Allies[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Only the intended recipient can detect a transmission  sent with this attachment without a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Computers check[b]. </div><div>Upgrade the difficulty of any checks to intercept or decipher transmissions made from this attachment once. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":6000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ASEA"}},"_id":"wBibf1yvHSBpiOU1"}
{"name":"Low-Friction Coating","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Low-Friction Coating[h3]\nLow-friction coatings work by lowering the coefficient of friction against solid armor plates. With the addition of such a coating, the surface of armor becomes almost impossible to grip or seize. In addition, glancing blows from melee weapons are often unable to find purchase, which diminishes the damage they cause as they slide off. The only downside to the coating is that is can make working on the armor more difficult, as tools must scramble for a grip on its slick surface. This attachment can only be applied to armor with hard surfaces such as heavy battle armor, powered armor.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Melee Defense Mod - Increases Melee Defense value by 1 </div><div>Add [SE][SE] to Mechanics checks to modify of maintain armor. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2500,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":7,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"LOWFRIC"}},"_id":"wV7w7wjF0Kao7Yd3"}
{"name":"Rocket Guidance System","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Rocket Guidance System[h3]\nMost micro-rockets are fired directly at their target, relying on the firer's aim and the rocket's acceleration to ensure a direct hit. For those who prefer more insurance that their rockets land precisely where intended, packages of sensors, limited fuel cell expansions, and adjustable maneuvering fins allow for rockets to be modified into maneuvering fins allow for rockets to be modified into \"smart\" weapons that continue to seek their designated target in the event of an initial miss or misfire. These systems enable users to get more reliable performance out of their rockets while at the same time minimizing the collateral damage. This attachment can be installed on any micro-rocket.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Phar Co. \"Vornskr\" Guidance Package, Merr-Sonn \"Outreach\" Target Sensor.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 47 - No Disintegrations[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Guided Quality - Certain types of projectiles may benefit from course alterations after being fired—such as guided missiles. If a character misses while firing a Guided weapon and if Guided activates, he may make an attack check at the end of the round. The difficulty of the check is calculated by comparing the weapon’s silhouette of 0 to the silhouette of the target (see page 235), and the check’s Ability dice equal the weapon’s Guided rating. If the test is successful, the weapon strikes the target and damage is dealt normally.\n\n[P]Guided requires [AD][AD][AD] to activate, unless otherwise specified in the weapon’s description. Remember, the Guided effect can activate on its subsequent attacks, representing the projectile continuing to track the target.\n\n[P]“Spoofing” is a countermeasure designed to work against the particular projectile—such as flares designed to draw off an infrared missile. Spoofing directly increases the defense of the target against attacks with the Guided quality. Count 2</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":50,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"u9PCIWOHCUMMctDm","name":"Guided Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Certain types of projectiles may benefit from course alterations after being fired—such as guided missiles. If a character misses while firing a Guided weapon and if Guided activates, he may make an attack check at the end of the round. The difficulty of the check is calculated by comparing the weapon’s silhouette of 0 to the silhouette of the target (see page 235), and the check’s Ability dice equal the weapon’s Guided rating. If the test is successful, the weapon strikes the target and damage is dealt normally.\n\n[P]Guided requires [AD][AD][AD] to activate, unless otherwise specified in the weapon’s description. Remember, the Guided effect can activate on its subsequent attacks, representing the projectile continuing to track the target.\n\n[P]“Spoofing” is a countermeasure designed to work against the particular projectile—such as flares designed to draw off an infrared missile. Spoofing directly increases the defense of the target against attacks with the Guided quality.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"GUIDED"}},"id":"z66m3pvbtzz2fxrs"},{"_id":"8iSDMh1U3HQD0563","name":"Accurate Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Accurate weapons are easier to aim or wield, whether through design or technology. For each level of this trait, the attacker adds [BO] to his attack dice pools while using this weapon.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"ACCURATE"}},"id":"k2z13mpdh2r5489c"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"MICROROCKGUIDE"}},"_id":"weBeVZUsnsQWWnZI"}
{"name":"Custom Fit","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Custom Fit[h3]\nAlthough standard \"off-the-shelf\" armor can provide invaluable protection, it can also prove bulky or awkward, even after adjustments. For those who require their armor to feel like a second skin, personalized customization can make a drastic difference. Such  work requires a skilled armorer, but it can make body armor a much more enticing option for some. This attachment can be applied to any armor.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Numerous variants[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 57 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Removes [SE] from Athletics and Stealth checks. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":400,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CUSTOMFIT"}},"_id":"wzwLyHLPIbkIC4jM"}
{"name":"Component Alteration (Gear)","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Component Alteration (Gear)[h3]\nA more drastic, but more effective, option is to alter a weapon or other device so that it can be broken down into several smaller parts that can be reassembled later. This method is typically used when a Rebel needs to get a larger item into a secure location or to avoid scanning devices that are likely to detect standard weapons regardless of any concealment alterations. This is called a component alteration.\n[P]Characters wishing to break a weapon or other item down into several parts in this fashion need to spend time dismantling the device into smaller components. This requires a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] and takes a number of hours equal to the item's encumbrance, or a minimum of one hour. If the check is successful, the device is broken down into a number of components equal to its encumbrance plus 1. So, a blaster pistol is broken down into two components, while a blaster rifle is broken down into five.\n[P]Note that this differs from the more advanced componentization weapon attachment, which requires no check for use once it is installed and is designed to allow the user to openly carry a weapon, rather than consisting of a simple mechanical disassembly. Characters can try, though, to use component alteration to physically disguise these individual parts to look like code cylinders, comlinks, fusion lanterns, and other mundane objects. While this allows a part to take on the rough appearance of the desired object, it does not gain the functionality of that object. This is generally a taxing and tricky process, and so upgrades the difficulty of the Mechanics check once or more as per the GM's discretion.\n[P]Each [SU] or [TR] on the initial Mechanics check lets a character carrying the components from a component alteration add [BO] to [B]opposed Stealth vs. Perception checks[b] when an observer attempts to notice the true nature of the disassembled device. If the component alteration was designed to make the items appear mundane, he gains [BO][BO] instead.\n[P]Assembling a weapon or other item with a component alteration requires two maneuvers or two minutes of narrative time per component, and the character must make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. All components must be present to make the check. Failure means the components are damaged and the device requires a major repair to be properly reassembled again and returned to function. \n[P]Component alterations have a strong impact on a item's reliability, as most weapons or other complex devices simply aren't meant to be broken down into smaller pieces and reassembled. The GM may spend [TH][TH][TH] as [DE] when a character makes a skill check while using an item with this alteration. \n[P]A character can only attempt a component alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 80 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Characters wishing to break a weapon or other item down into several parts in this fashion need to spend time dismantling the device into smaller components. This requires a [B]Hard ([DI][DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] and takes a number of hours equal to the item's encumbrance, or a minimum of one hour. If the check is successful, the device is broken down into a number of components equal to its encumbrance plus 1. </div><div>Characters can try to use component alteration to physically disguise these individual parts to look like code cylinders, comlinks, fusion lanterns, and other mundane objects. While this allows a part to take on the rough appearance of the desired object, it does not gain the functionality of that object. This is generally a taxing and tricky process, and so upgrades the difficulty of the Mechanics check once or more as per the GM's discretion. </div><div>Each [SU] or [TR] on the initial Mechanics check lets a character carrying the components from a component alteration add [BO] to [B]opposed Stealth vs. Perception checks[b] when an observer attempts to notice the true nature of the disassembled device. If the component alteration was designed to make the items appear mundane, he gains [BO][BO] instead. </div><div>Assembling a weapon or other item with a component alteration requires two maneuvers or two minutes of narrative time per component, and the character must make an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. All components must be present to make the check. Failure means the components are damaged and the device requires a major repair to be properly reassembled again and returned to function. </div><div>The GM may spend [TH][TH][TH] as [DE] when a character makes a skill check while using an item with this alteration. </div><div>A character can only attempt a component alteration once on a given item, and doing so permanently reduces the item's available hard points by 1. Items that have no hard points may still be altered in this fashion. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"COMPALTERGEAR"}},"_id":"x1pQ9XtizX3JF7ll"}
{"name":"Concealed Climbing Cord","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-gear.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Concealed Climbing Cord[h3]\nThis mod consists of a small retracting spool wrapped with twenty-five meters of thin, high tensile strength climbing line, connected to a small, spring-loaded grappling hook. Typically built into a belt, sash, or other load-bearing strap, a concealed climbing cord can get an agent into and out of a lot of trouble in a variety of mission settings. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Various models.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 59 - Cyphers and Masks[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Grants the user a length of climbing cord with grappling hook. This counts as having the Right Tool for the Job for climbing and repelling. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":100,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"gear"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CONCCLIMBCORD"}},"_id":"xCHzBUmNhph3bngc"}
{"name":"Krayt Dragon Pearl","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Krayt Dragon Pearl[h3]\n\nHighly sought after by jewelers, artisans, and wealthy collectors for their luster, color, and refractive properties, krayt dragon pearls are perhaps the rarest of the crystals used in the construction of lightsabers. The terrible krayt dragons of Tatooine tend to live for an incredibly long time, and over the course of their lives will ingest stones to aid with digestion. While the caustic digestive juices of the krayt dragon can even break down stone over time, every once in a while these stones contain some form of kyber crystal. Incredibly resilient, they remain in the creatures' guts for the entirety of the dragons' lives, slowly being polished and smoothed into small, dense spheres of crystal. The resulting \"krayt dragon pearls\" are vanishingly rare, hard to acquire, and demand exorbitant prices. Since they are a type of kyber crystal, they can be worked into powerful lightsaber crystals—ones which produce an exceptionally savage and destructive blade that makes an unsettling howling noise when swung about. A krayt dragon pearl is a lightsaber crystal. \n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Base Damage Mod - Changes Base Damage Count 9</div><div>Base Critical Rating Mod - Changes Critical Rating </div><div>Breach Quality - Weapons with Breach burn through the toughest armor, and are often heavy weapons or starship weapons.\n\n[P]Breach weapons ignore one point of Armor for every rating of Breach (meaning they also ignore 10 points of soak for every rating of Breach). </div><div>Sunder Quality - When activated, the attacker chooses one item openly wielded by the target (such as a weapon, shield, or item on a belt). That item is damaged one step: to Minor if undamaged, from Minor to Moderate, or from Moderate to Major. If a weapon already suffering Major damage is the target of a successful Sunder, it is destroyed.\n\n[P]Sunder requires [AD] to activate. If activated multiple times in the same attack, each can be applied against the same weapon, potentially taking a weapon from undamaged to destroyed in a single attack. </div><div>Vicious Quality - When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":15000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":10,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3KtmTQoxAwZVERDU","name":"Vicious Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"When this weapon scores a critical injury or hit, the character adds ten times the Vicious rating to the critical roll. With Vicious 3, for example, the victim adds +30 to his critical hit result.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"VICIOUS"}},"id":"ezm4myga4z6hsfoy"},{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"ptlsk3rr8ywkk77a"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"KRAYT"}},"_id":"xryi1SeI0OXSUmmg"}
{"name":"In-Helmet Scanner","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]In-Helmet Scanner[h3]\n\nAn in-helmet scanner provides the usefulness of a general purpose scanner in a heads-up display splashed across the inside of the users helmet. This feeds the user a constant stream of information about the surrounding environment. Depending on the specific model, an in-helmet scanner can indicate the presence of life forms or droids and display heat signatures, radiation sources, acoustic emissions, and more. Many can also scan and listen to nearby comlink frequencies. In-helmet scanners can be added to any helmet. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] CryonCorp GoScan, CUE Optical Information System (Mobile), Chedak Mk. 7 HUD-INFO.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds a general purpose scanner\n          to the user’s helmet. The scanner allows the user to\n          remove [SETBACK] imposed on any checks due to darkness\n          or environmental conditions such as smoke or fog. It\n          also allows the user to detect heat sources and motion\n          within medium range. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HELMETSCAN"}},"_id":"xvMijZGfz3K43wIs"}
{"name":"Poison Reservoir","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Poison Reservoir[h3]\n\nMany assassins who use melee weapons choose to improve the lethality of their blades by adding a poison reservoir that releases a toxin through a channel in the blade at the push of a button in the hilt. While dipping a weapon in poison can be somewhat effective, a reservoir is a much more efficient delivery method. This attachment can only be used with Brawl and Melee weapons. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Numerous variants.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Lords of Nal Hutta[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows user to store one dose of neurotoxin, anesthetic, neuroparalytic, or similar toxins. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":400,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"3p8ORZlopfhfEGEg","name":"Increase doses by 1 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Increase doses by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"RESDOSE"}},"id":"fuqryqgd3ile2ywv"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"POISONRES"}},"_id":"y0crFc57ABsFWLyY"}
{"name":"Swoop Speed Modification","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Swoop Speed Modification[h3]\n\nBoosts the engines of a swoop and also removes excess weight from the chassis.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Suns of Fortune[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Speed Mod - Increase Speed by 1 </div><div>Decrease Hull Trauma Mod - Decreases Hull Trauma by 1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1200,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"kfUbhrn82nL9vXku","name":"Increases System Strain Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increases System Strain by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SSTRAINADD"}},"id":"0w7rp5bjn0zrneny"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"SWOOPSPEED"}},"_id":"y7yPO8V4wVeSa5rd"}
{"name":"Paramilitary Medium Transport","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Paramilitary Medium Transport[h3]\n      Converts a medium transport to a paramilitary vehicle.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 71 - Dangerous Covenants[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increase Defense Zone Mod - Increases Defense Zone by 1 </div><div>Increase Armor Mod - Increases Armor value by 1 Count 2</div><div>Increase Hull Trauma Mod - Increases Hull Trauma by 1 Count 3</div><div>Decreases System Strain Mod - Decreases System Strain by 1 Count 2</div><div>Adds two medium laser cannon turrets </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PARAMEDTRANS"}},"_id":"yCK7A5wwGwTTl6m0"}
{"name":"Bowcaster Accelerator Enhancement","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Bowcaster Accelerator Enhancement[h3]\n\nBuilt from scavenged blaster parts and the occasional piece from a repulsorlift generator, the bowcaster accelerator enhancement is the second-most common modification to Wookiee bowcasters after the automatic re-cocker. Essentially an upgrade of the weapon's bolt accelerators, this attachment allows the bowcaster to fire its highly destructive quarrels with more force than typical in a stock weapon. These attachments are only for use on Wookiee bowcasters, and they cannot be purchased; they must be built either by the owner of the bowcaster with an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b] or the weaponsmith who built the weapon for him. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Edge of the Empire Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Damage Mod - Damage +1 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"Wad1VjI7tf8WeCyS","name":"Additional Damage Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"Damage +1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"DAMADD"}},"id":"00r4w9amyfvel1dz"},{"_id":"zFzCvB6bUqEr4deZ","name":"Pierce Quality","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"An attack made with this weapon ignores one point of soak for each rank of Pierce. If the weapon has more ranks of Pierce than the target’s total soak, it completely ignores the target’s soak. For example, Pierce 3 against a soak of 2 ignores 2 points of soak, but the extra “point” of Pierce has no further effect.","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"weapon","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PIERCE"}},"id":"sjprsklgut1gzntb"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"BOWACC"}},"_id":"yK7skHVKUhV8rbS9"}
{"name":"Upgraded Comms Array","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Upgraded Comms Array[h3]\n\nThis upgrade reflects the simple act of mounting more or heavier weapons on a starship or vehicle. When replacing an existing weapon on the ship, the new weapon has the same firing arc as the original. When adding a weapon to a new location on the ship, the GM must decide what firing arc makes the most sense. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] Arakyd Flex Tube Proton Torpedo Launcher, ArMek SW-6 Heavy Ion Cannon.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Age of Rebellion Core Rulebook[h4][H4]Force and Destiny Core Rulebook[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Additional Comms Range Mod - Increase vehicle's communications range by one Range Band </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":4800,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":6,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"IflCxGiSpy59IEqK","name":"Additional Comms Range Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase vehicle's communications range by one Range Band","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"CRANGEADD"}},"id":"0jg3yp53qcon76li"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"UCA"}},"_id":"yN5871XmIL7aJrt1"}
{"name":"Hyperdrive Class 8 Module","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Hyperdrive Class 8 Module[h3]\nCompared to sublight engines, hyperdrive modules require less thrust ducting and other complex integration work. Thus, they are handled as a starship attachment.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 82 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Add Class 8 Hyperdrive Mod - Add Class 8 Hyperdrive </div><div>Add astromech droid socket (starfighters only). </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":3000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"0HibaLcBPREmA3Wv","name":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1, to a minimum of .5 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Decreases Hyperdrive Class by 1","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"HYPERDRIVESUB5"}},"id":"z5b1zc35ir1tk1w6"},null,null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"FOHYPER8"}},"_id":"yP3kAeiazSOLOVc1"}
{"name":"Integrated Load-Bearing Gear","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Integrated Load-Bearing Gear[h3]\n[B]EOD-Mk II Upgrade Options:[b] EOD-MK II suits lack any standard modification options, but can be upgraded with two valuable attachments. These attachments are integrated load-bearing gear and a data link for controlling EOD and demolitions remotes, such as the EOD-Mk IV. As the suits are designed for these upgrades, neither takes up any hard points for the armor, but each upgrade can only be taken once.\n[P]Integrated load-bearing gear reduces the suit's encumbrance by 3, and costs an additional 700 credits with a rarity of 3.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 43 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Decreases Encumbrance Mod - Decrease Encumbrance by 1 Count 3</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":700,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":3,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"EODMKIILOAD"}},"_id":"yVvs7qM7oq2AMrUX"}
{"name":"AX-108 \"Ground Buzzer\" Surface-Defense Blaster Cannon","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]AX-108 \"Ground Buzzer\" Surface-Defense Blaster Cannon[h3]\n\nDesigned to provide anti-personnel defense for a starship when on the ground, BlasTech's Ax-108 \"Ground Buzzer' is a popular modification on ships whose owners expect trouble. With a powerful blast and high rate of fire, the retractable Ax-108 folds into a hidden compartment on a vessel's hull. While the weapon can be manually operated from the cockpit, it can also be remotely activated. \n\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] BlasTech Ax-108 \"Ground Buzzer\" surface-defense blaster cannon.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Fly Casual[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds one AX-108 Surface Defense Blaster Cannon weapon </div><div>Can fire automatically with a Ranged (Heavy) skill of 2 and an Agility of 0 </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":2000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AX108BUZZER"}},"_id":"yWJtSp1oamVrkv55"}
{"name":"(AD-15) Cargo Pod","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Cargo Pod for AD-15[h3]\nThe cargo pods for this craft are large, cylindrical affairs, designed for efficiency, not aesthetics. These pods can even be retrofitted to carry passengers, though they do not make for comfortable quarters.\n[P][H4]<font size=1>Please see page 62 of the Special Modifications Sourcebook for details.</font>[h4][P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 62 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Increases Encumbrance Capacity Mod - Increase Encumbrance Capacity by 1 Count 50</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1400,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[{"_id":"8YgvY9ltV3k1b96u","name":"Increase Passenger Capacity by 2 Mod","type":"itemmodifier","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"Increase Passenger Capacity by 2","attributes":{},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"type":"vehicle","rank":3},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"PASSADD2"}},"id":"ppdpt67mxs2wuboy"}],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"AD15CARGOPOS"}},"_id":"yihoJzgkmK4EWuBk"}
{"name":"Removed Safety Features","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-weapon.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Removed Safety Features[h3]\nBy removing or deactivating weapon safeties and other features a gun can more easily be drawn and readied for combat. Of course, these safety features are in place for a reason, and weapons modified in such a way tend to be more accident prone. This attachment can be applied to any Ranged (Light) or Ranged (Heavy) weapon that could logically have such elements to remove.\n[P][B]Models Include:[b] None[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 55 - Special Modifications[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Adds [BO] to first combat check during an encounter. </div><div>GM may spend [TH][TH] to cause misfire.  Weapon runs out of ammo and inflicts 4 strain on wielder. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":250,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":2,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"weapon"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REMSAFFEAT"}},"_id":"ykIgGuUflkqvnsbA"}
{"name":"Data Link","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Data Link[h3]\n[B]EOD-Mk II Upgrade Options:[b] EOD-MK II suits lack any standard modification options, but can be upgraded with two valuable attachments. These attachments are integrated load-bearing gear and a data link for controlling EOD and demolitions remotes, such as the EOD-Mk IV. As the suits are designed for these upgrades, neither takes up any hard points for the armor, but each upgrade can only be taken once.\n[P]The data link allows the wearer to control a single EOD remote and costs an extra 300 credits with a rarity of 4.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 43 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Allows wearer to control a single EOD remote. Count 3</div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":300,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"EODMKIIDATALINK"}},"_id":"yzCx1rjDU4qwFnCE"}
{"name":"Repulsorlift Boost","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-vehicle.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Repulsorlift Boost[h3]\nSome obstacles are insurmountable for even the most versatile and powerful of factory-standard repulsor field generators. For tinkerers willing to ignore a whole host of safety warnings-and likely a few laws-most repulsor field generators can be pushed past factory limits, allowing for a drastic, if brief, increase in lift. Such an increase can allow the vehicle to \"jump\" over objects, gaps, or enemy vehicles or to higher ground. Some field mechanics have even been known to add specially overcharged repulsor fields to vehicles that rely on a different method of propulsion, just in case. More than one team of Rebel soldiers has escaped certain death in the face of overwhelming Imperial opposition, thanks to just such modifications.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Page 61 - Fully Operational[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>Once per encounter as an incidental, vehicle may suffer 2 system strain to double maximum altitute (or gain 100 meters, whichever is lower) and increase max speed by 1 for 1 round. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":1000,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":4,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[null],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"vehicle"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"REPULSBOOST"}},"_id":"z0wEJ1pu9CmPyrDx"}
{"name":"Quick Shed","type":"itemattachment","img":"/systems/starwarsffg/images/mod-armor.png","data":{"description":"[H3]Quick Shed[h3]\n[P]Armor, especially heavy armor, takes time to put on and take off. though putting armor on remains a chore, taking it off - especially in an emergency situation - is expedited with the quick shed attachment. By installing several quick-release latches at strategic locations, suits of armor can be quickly removed by the wearer. This attachment can only be applied to armor with an encumbrance of 3 or higher.[P][H3]Sources:[h3][H4]Keeping the Peace[h4]<h3>Base Mods</h3><div>As a maneuver, wearer by shed the armor.  Armor must be reassembled before donning again, requiring several minutes and an [B]Average ([DI][DI]) Mechanics check[b]. </div>","attributes":{},"quantity":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Quantity","abrev":"Qty"},"encumbrance":{"value":0,"type":"Number","label":"Encumbrance","abrev":"Encum","adjusted":0},"price":{"value":750,"type":"Number","label":"Price","adjusted":0},"rarity":{"value":5,"type":"Number","label":"Rarity","adjusted":0},"hardpoints":{"value":1,"type":"Number","label":"Hard Points","abrev":"HP","adjusted":0},"itemmodifier":[],"adjusteditemmodifer":[],"itemattachment":[],"type":"armor"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Itz0X4muSsVNH8FV":3},"flags":{"starwarsffg":{"ffgimportid":"QUICKSHED"}},"_id":"zzQvDqDJ7XYgdyCB"}
